title: Ten Freedom Summers
summary: The four-disc set from the jazz trumpeter was inspired by the Civil Rights Movement.

title: Fetch the Bolt Cutters
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the alternative singer-songwriter was self-produced and features contributions from Davíd Garza, Sebastian Steinberg, and Amy Aileen Wood.

title: SMiLE
summary: Well, better 37 years late than never. Originally intended to be the Beach Boys' 1967 follow-up to their legendary 'Pet Sounds,' 'Smile' was finally recorded as originally intended in April 2004 by Wilson and his current band, including co-songwriter Van Dyke Parks.

title: Van Lear Rose
summary: It's been over 40 years since she released her first album (and four since her last, 2000's 'Still Country'), but the coal miner's daughter returns to the spotlight with this 13-track effort (all Lynn-penned originals), produced by The White Stripes' Jack White.

title: To Pimp A Butterfly
summary: The third full-length studio release from the hip hop artist features guest appearances from Bilal, George Clinton, James Fauntleroy, Ronald Isley, Rapsody, Snoop Dogg, Thundercat, and Anna Wise.

title: Ghosteen
summary: The 17th full-length studio release for Australian rock band is influenced in part by the accidental death of Nick Cave's 15-year old son in 2015 and is considered the third and final part of trilogy of albums that includes 2013's Push the Sky Away and 2016's Skeleton Tree.

title: Histoire de Melody Nelson
summary: The US release of Serge Gainsbourg's 1971 album featuring Jane Birkin in the classic Ballade de Melody Nelson.

title: DAMN.
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Compton rapper features guest appearances from Rihanna, U2, and Zacari.

title: Stankonia
summary: Featuring the hit singles "B.O.B." and "Ms. Jackson," 'Stankonia' was a commercial and critical hit for the innovative Atlanta hip-hop duo of Dré and Big Boi.

title: Rough and Rowdy Ways
summary: The first new studio release of new music for the singer-songwriter in eight years.

title: Black Messiah
summary: The first release in 14 years for the R&B singer features songs co-written with Q-Tip and Kendra Foster as well as co-production from James Gadson, Pino Palladino,and Questlove.

title: Conflict Of Interest
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British grime artist features guest appearances from BackRoad Gee, Dave, Giggs, Hamzaaand, Jaykae, Aida Lae, Miraa May, Pa Salieu, Emeli Sande, Moonchild Sanelly, Ed Sheeran, Skepta, Stormzy, and Wretch 32.

title: Skeleton Tree
summary: Nick Cave's 15-year-old son died in an accident while he was working on the alternative rock band's 16th album. The recording sessions were filmed for Andrew Dominik's documentary, One More Time With Feel.

title: Savane
summary: 'Savane' is the final album from the acclaimed guitarist from Mali, who died in March 2006 after a three-decade recording career which found him injecting American blues into traditional African music.

title: My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy
summary: Breaking traditional mainstream hip-hop guidelines, Kanye West's latest release features epic raps and long instrumental variations for his most innovative album to date.

title: Madvillainy
summary: 'Madvillainy' is a collaboration between rapper MF Doom and producer Madlib.

title: A Crow Looked at Me
summary: The eighth full-length release for the music project of Phil Elverum was written after the death of his wife from cancer in July 2016.

title: Room 25
summary: The debut full-length release for the Los Angeles-based Chicago rapper was self-released.

title: Live At Reading
summary: The entire performance by Nirvana at 1992's Reading Festival is released both as a CD and DVD.

title: Love And Theft
summary: Picking up where 1997's resurgent 'Time Out of Mind' left off, 'Love And Theft' finds the 60-year-old Dylan self-producing the album's 12 tracks.

title: Ants From Up There
summary: The second full-length release for the British post-rock band Black Country, New Road is its last with frontman and co-founder Isaac Wood, who announced he was leaving the band in January 2022.

title: My Dusty Road
summary: The four-disc set includes Woody Guthrie's recordings from the mid-1940s in a definitive collection.

title: On the Impossible Past
summary: The third full-length release from the punk rock band from Pennsylvania is its first on Epitaph Records.

title: Prioritise Pleasure
summary: The second full-length solo release for Slow Club's Rebecca Taylor was produced by Johan Karlberg.

title: Lemonade
summary: The sixth solo studio album for the singer premiered as an hour-long HBO special before streaming on Tidal. A physical release is set for May 6.

title: Pull Up Some Dust and Sit Down
summary: The Grammy-award winning musician returns with a concept album about corruption in America.

title: Sunbather
summary: The second full-length studio release for the San Francisco-based black metal band formed by George Clarke and Kerry McCoy was produced by Jack Shirley.

title: Glow On
summary: The third full-length release for the Baltimore hardcore punk band features a guest appearance from Blood Orange and was recorded with producer Mike Elizondo.

title: Orphans: Brawlers, Bawlers & Bastards
summary: Unlike typical rarities compilations, this 3-disc set includes 30 brand-new recordings--in addition to the usual mix of covers, soundtrack selections, and other previously uncompiled material. It's like getting three new Waits albums at once.

title: Time Will Die and Love Will Bury It
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the British rock band was recorded and mixed by Lewis Johns.

title: Boy In Da Corner
summary: This is the debut disc for the 18-year-old London-based rapper (born Dylan Mills), who has been heralded by (among others) Uncut magazine as "good as any MC currently active on Earth."

title: You Want It Darker
summary: The 14th full-length studio release for the Canadian singer-songwriter was produced by his son.

title: Channel Orange
summary: Love and life in Los Angeles is the theme of the debut release on Def Jam for Frank Ocean, who earlier this month posted online the liner notes for this album describing a relationship he had with a man.

title: The Satanist
summary: The tenth studio release for the Polish black/death metal band was produced with Daniel Bergstrand, Slawek Wieslawscy and Wojtek Wieslawscy.

title: Elephant
summary: For their major label debut (and fourth LP overall), the Detroit-based duo of Jack and Meg White offer up 14 new tracks, all recorded in London and (fortunately) showing absolutely no trace of major label production values. Meg White takes a rare turn behind the microphone on a couple of tracks, as does guest Holly Golightly on the closing "It's True That We Love One Another."

title: We're All Alone In This Together
summary: The second full-length studio release for the British rapper features guest appearances from Snoh Aalegra, James Blake, Boj, Stormzy, and WizKid.

title: Titanic Rising
summary: The fourth full-length release for Natalie Mering was co-produced with Foxygen's Jonathan Rado.

title: Carnage
summary: The surprise release for the latest full-length collaboration between Nick Cave and Warren Ellis was recorded over a week.

title: Melodrama
summary: The second full-length release for the New Zealand pop singer-songwriter was produced with Jack Antonoff.

title: Speakerboxxx/The Love Below
summary: This Grammy-winning follow-up to their smash 2000 hit 'Stankonia' is an OutKast album in name only, as it is structured in the form of two solo discs: one each for Big Boi (Speakerboxxx) and Andre 3000 (The Love Below).

title: Set My Heart on Fire Immediately
summary: The fifth full-length release for Mike Hadreas as Perfume Genius was produced with Blake Mills.

title: Red (Taylor's Version)
summary: The new recording of Taylor Swift's fourth studio album features nine previously unreleased songs that include guest appearances from Phoebe Bridgers, Ed Sheeran, and Chris Stapleton.

title: Home, Like Noplace Is There
summary: This is the second full-length release for the Massachusetts indie rock quartet formerly known as The Hotel Year.

title: Good Kid, M.A.A.D City
summary: The official major label debut studio album for the Compton rapper features guest appearances from Dr. Dre, Drake, Jay Rock, And MC Eiht.

title: A Grand Don't Come For Free
summary: Mike Skinner returns with the inenviable job of following up his genre-smashing debut 'Original Pirate Material,' which was an enormous critical and commercial hit in the UK and paved the way for the success of later acts such as Dizzee Rascal.

title: The Myth of the Happily Ever After
summary: The latest full-length release for the Scottish alternative rock band was produced with Adam Noble.

title: Canto
summary: The second release from the Latin-folk supergroup, featuring members of Los Lobos.

title: Grey Area
summary: The third full-length release for the British rapper Simbi Ajikawo features a guest appearances from Cleo Sol.

title: Sex, Death & The Infinite Void
summary: The second full-length release for the British punk rock band led by Will Gould was produced by Xandy Barry.

title: The ArchAndroid
summary: The second full-length album for the singer born in Kansas City is a continuation of the story of Cindi Mayweather, the android introduced in the 2007 EP, "Metropolis Suite I of IV: The Chase."

title: Gold & Grey
summary: The fifth full-length release for the hard rock/metal band is the first with new guitarist Gina Gleason (Peter Adams left the band in 2017).

title: Blue Weekend
summary: The third full-length release for the British rock band was produced by Markus Dravs.

title: The  Guitar Song
summary: Jamey Johnson's latest album is a 25-track double album with the first half, The Black Album, devoted to dark emotions and the other half, the White Album, devoted to more positive songs.

title: Is This It?
summary: This is the debut album from New York indie-rockers The Strokes, who have been hyped by the British music press following the release of "The Modern Age" EP in early 2001. It almost goes without saying, but the group is frequently compared to the Velvet Underground, among others, thanks in part to singer-songwriter Julian Casablancas' Lou Reed-esque vocals.

title: We Got It From Here...Thank You 4 Your Service
summary: Phife Dawg passed away in March 2016 before the final studio release for the rap group that includes guest appearances from such artists as Anderson Paak, Andre 3000, Busta Rhymes, Consequence, Elton John, Talib Kweli, Kendrick Lamar, and Jack White.

title: From Here We Go Sublime
summary: This is the full-length debut for Stockholm, Sweden trance producer Axel Willner.

title: Illinois
summary: The folk singer-songwriter's ambitious attempt to chronicle all 50 states in song continues with this second installment, dedicated to the Prairie State.

title: Carrie & Lowell
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Thomas Bartlett, Sean Carey, Casey Foubert, Ben Lester, Nedelle Torrisi, and Laura Veirs.

title: Jimmy Lee
summary: The first full-length release of new material from the R&B artist/producer was inspired by his late brother's struggle with drug addiction and features guest appearances from Rob Bacon, Reverend E. Baker, Ernest Turner, and Daniel J. Watts.

title: No Cities to Love
summary: The first release in ten years for the indie rock trio of Carrie Brownstein, Corin Tucker, and Janet Weiss was produced by John Goodmanson.

title: Eve
summary: The third full-length studio release for the North Carolina rapper features guest appearances from J. Cole, D'Angelo, GZA, JID, Leikeli47, Mereba], PJ Morton, Queen Latifah, K.Roosevelt, SiR, and Elle Varner.

title: Punisher
summary: The second full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Julien Baker, Lucy Dacus, Christian Lee Hutson, Jim Keltner, Warpint's Jenny Lee Lindberg, Blake Mills, Conor Oberst, Bright Eyes' Nathaniel Walcott, and the Yeah Yeah Yeahs' Nick Zinner.

title: Send Them To Coventry [Mixtape]
summary: The debut mixtape from the British rapper features guest appearances from Mahalia, M1llionz, BackRoad Gee, Boy Boy, Eight9FLY, Lz Dinero, Ni Santora, Shakavellie, and Stizee.

title: Original Pirate Material
summary: This is the debut album by the London garage (or in this case, bedroom) band, which consists solely of 21-year-old Mike Skinner. Whether or not this style of music (very English rapping over garage/house beats) will translate well overseas remains to be seen, but garage (and especially Skinner) is the current flavor of the month with the UK music press.

title: Candi Staton
summary: This 26-track disc compiles (for the first time on CD) songs from the acclaimed soul singer's 1969-1973 Muscle Shoals period when she recorded for Fame Records--a period that netted her 12 consecutive Billboard R&B hits.

title: Alice
summary: One of two Waits releases in May 2002 ('Blood Money' is the other), 'Alice' was originally written as an opera and actually performed live during an 18-month engagement in Hamburg in the early 1990s. However, this is the first recording of these 15 tracks, culled from recent studio sessions.

title: Funeral
summary: The Montreal band founded by husband and wife Win Butler and Régine Chassagne make their full-length debut with this highly anticipated disc.

title: Holy Hell
summary: The eighth full-length release for the British metalcore band is its first without Tom Searle, who passed away in August 2016.

title: London Zoo
summary: The third album for the artist/music producer Kevin Martin as The Bug.

title: Jama Ko
summary: The third release for Bassekou Kouyate introduces a new group of ngoni players and was co-produced with Howard Bilerman.

title: Sir Lucious Left Foot: The Son of Chico Dusty
summary: OutKast's Big Boi goes solo with an album featuring guest appearances from such artists as Jamie Foxx, Janelle Monae, B.o.B., Gucci Mane, Too Short, and George Clinton.

title: Psychodrama
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the British rapper features guest appearances from Burna Boy and J Hus.

title: Untrue
summary: The second album for the London-based anonymous dubstep artist.

title: græ
summary: The double album (released also as two separate EPs] for the experimental artist features a guest appearance from Jill Scott and elements of folk, jazz, indie rock, pop, and soul music.

title: XTRMNTR
summary: Bobby Gillespie & co. expand on the harder-edged punk/electronica sound of their previous effort, 'Vanishing Point,' with their most violent effort to date, earning rave reviews in the process and perhaps matching the success of their classic 'Screamadelica.' Contributors here include David Holmes, Bernard Sumner, Kevin Shields and the Chemical Brothers.

title: Spaces
summary: Described as a field recording, this latest release from the Berlin-based composer was recorded over two years at various locations with different methods including cassette recordings.

title: Z
summary: For their fourth album, produced by John Leckie, the Kentucky band sports a new keyboardist and guitarist.

title: St. Vincent
summary: The fourth full-length release for the indie artist was produced by John Congleton and includes contributions from Dap-Kings drummer Homer Steinweiss and Midlake's McKenzie Smith.

title: The Dusk in Us
summary: The ninth full-length release for the Massachusetts metalcore band was mixed by the band's guitarist, Kurt Ballou.

title: Like a Rose
summary: The second solo album for the Pistol Annies member includes songs co-written with such artists as Sally Barris, Guy Clark, Vince Gill, Lori McKenna, and Jon Randall.

title: RTJ2
summary: The latest release from Killer Mike and El-P features collaborations with Travis Barker of Blink-182, Diane Coffee, and Zack de la Rocha formerly of Rage Against the Machine.

title: Rounds
summary: The sample-based indietronica LP 'Rounds' is the third solo effort for Fridge's Kieran Hebden.

title: Neon Golden
summary: This breaktrhough sixth album for the German band combines a variety of disparate elements, most notably moody indie rock and glitchy electronica (think Hood's Cold House), to great effect.

title: Since I Left You
summary: This sample-driven Austrialian dance outfit scored a hit in its homeland with this, its debut full-length release (following three EP releases since 1997). The UK music press created a publicity avalanche for the band in the Spring of 2001, as the album picked up strong reviews (quotes from some appear below) and was featured in numerous articles. Packed with over 600 samples of recordings dating from the 1950's to the present (each one credited in the liner notes!) as well as original instrumentation, 'Since I Left You' is a varied and unique record.

title: Honey
summary: The first full-length release in eight years for the Swedish  artist features contributions from with Joseph Mount of Metronomy, Klas Åhlund, Adam Bainbridge, Mr. Tophat, and Zhal.

title: Eternity, In Your Arms
summary: The debut full-length release for the British punk rock band is a concept album about a paranormal investigator.

title: Kiwanuka
summary: The third full-length release for the indie singer-songwriter was produced by by Danger Mouse and Inflo.

title: Modern Times
summary: Dylan's first studio release since his 2001 hit 'Love And Theft' is his 44th album overall.

title: LEGACY! LEGACY!
summary: The second full-length release for the Chicago R&B artist features guest appearances from Jasminfire, Nitty Scott, Saba, Nico Segal, and theMIND.

title: Apex Predator - Easy Meat
summary: The 15th studio release for the British grindcore band was produced by Russ Russell.

title: HoboSapiens
summary: Produced by Nick Franglen of Lemon Jelly, 'Hobo Sapiens' finds the 61-year-old Cale still willing to explore new musical territory. Note that none of the 12 songs here were on the "5 Tracks" EP released earlier in 2003.

title: Miss E... So Addictive
summary: This is the third album for Missy "Misdemeanor" Elliott, and it again features the acclaimed production work of Timbaland. Guests include Busta Rhymes, Redman, Method Man, Ludacris, Eve, Jay-Z, and Ginuwine.

title: Bloodmoon: I
summary: The debut full-length collaboration between Converge, Chelsea Wolfe, Ben Chisholm, and Steve Brodsky began recording in 2019 but was completed remotely due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

title: RTJ4
summary: Released a few days early (for free on their website), the fourth full-length studio album for the rap duo features guest appearances from 2 Chainz, Zack de la Rocha, DJ Premier, Josh Homme, Greg Nice, Mavis Staples, and Pharrell Williams.

title: Sawayama
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the Japanese-British pop artist features production from Clarence Clarity, Nate Company, Bram Inscore, and Nicole Morier.

title: Black Origami
summary: The second full-length release for the electronic producer features contributions from William Basinski, Dope Saint Jude, Fawkes, and Holly Herndon.

title: Bachelor No. 2 (or, the last remains of the dodo)
summary: The third solo release from the former 'Til Tuesday leader finally made it to record stores in May 2000, after a long journey that saw Interscope refuse to release the album and Mann issue it on her own SuperEgo label (after selling it through mail order and at her live performances). All's well that ends well, though, as Mann gained widespread acclaim for her soundtrack to P.T. Anderson's film "Magnolia" and even better reviews for this album, which contains four of the tracks from the soundtrack as well as nine additional songs.

title: All Mirrors
summary: The fourth full-length studio release from the North Carolina-based indie folk singer-songwriter features arrangements and production by Ben Babbitt, Jherek Bischoff, and John Congelton.

title: For Those I Love
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the solo project of Dublin-based producer David Balfe.

title: Shortly After Takeoff
summary: The final release for Brian Christinzio's "Manchester Trilogy" features contributions from Adam Dawson and Francesca Pidgeon.

title: Safe In The Hands Of Love
summary: The surprise release from the experimental artist from Tennessee features a guest appearance from James K.

title: The Fade in Time
summary: The second full-length release for the Mercury-nominated singer-songwriter was produced by Arthur Jeffes and Jamie Orchard-Lisle.

title: Hand.Cannot.Erase.
summary: The fourth solo release for the British artist was inspired by a news article about the discovery of a young woman's dead body in her apartment three years after her death.

title: Coloring Book [Mixtape]
summary: The third mixtape from the Chicago rapper (an Apple Music exclusive for two weeks) features gospel elements as well as guest appearances from such artists as 2 Chainz, Justin Bieber, Francis and the Lights, Future, Jay Electronica, Lil Wayne, Kanye West, and Young Thug.

title: Big Fish Theory
summary: The second full-length studio release for the rapper features contributions from such artists as A$AP Rocky, Damon Albarn, Kilo Kish, Juicy J, Ty Dolla Signn, and Bon Iver’s Justin Vernon.

title: Ignorance
summary: The fifth full-length studio release Tamara Lindeman project was co-produced with Marcus Paquin, who also mixed the record.

title: The  Order of Time
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Brooklyn-based singer-songwriter features guest vocals from Norah Jones.

title: Fed
summary: Originally released in Japan, the sophomore album for Liam Hayes as Plush is finally released wide.

title: Golden Hour
summary: The seventh full-length release for the country singer-songwriter was co-produced with Daniel Tashian and Ian Fitchuk.

title: Chris
summary: The second full-length release for the French pop artist features a guest appearance from Dâm-Funk.

title: A Seat at the Table
summary: The third full-length studio release for the R&B singer features guest appearances from Nia Andrews, BJ The Chicago Kid, The Dream, Kelela, Lil Wayne, Q-Tip, Kelly Rowland, Sampha and

title: Last Exit
summary: This is the first full-length release from the hard-to-pin down Canadian synth-pop trio led by Jeremy Greenspan.

title: Pink Noise
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British artist features a guest appearance from Simon Neil.

title: When I Get Home
summary: The fourth full-length album for the R&B singer is a surprise release.

title: We Are Not Your Kind
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the metal band was produced by Greg Fidelman.

title: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More than Ropes Will Ever Do
summary: The singer-songwriter began recording her fourth studio album in secret in 2008 or 2009.

title: Merriweather Post Pavilion
summary: The ninth album from the rock group was produced by Ben Allen.

title: Songs For The Deaf
summary: Stoner metal is back in the form of the third LP from Queens of the Stone Age, who are supplemented for this release (and supporting tour) by drummer Dave Grohl (Foo Fighters, Nirvana) and former Screaming Trees vocalist Mark Lanegan.

title: Bright Green Field
summary: The debut full-length release for the British post-punk band was produced by Dan Carey and features a guest appearance from Martha Skye Murphy.

title: Wearemonster
summary: Frankfurt, Germany IDM artist Rajko Mueller (who records under the name Isolee) drew critical acclaim for this, his second LP and first in five years.

title: Ali & Toumani
artist: Ali Farka Toure And Toumani Diabate
summary: Recorded in 2005, this is the second album from Ali Farka Toure and Toumani Diabate, who won a Grammy for their previous effort together. Ali Farka Toure passed away from cancer in 2006.

title: They're Calling Me Home
summary: The second full-length release from Rhiannon Giddens with Francesco Turrisi was recorded over six days in Ireland during the COVID-19 pandemic.

title: Hell Hath No Fury
summary: This long-delayed second album for Virginia brothers Malice and Pusha T was produced in full by The Neptunes.

title: The Greatest Story Never Told
summary: The long-awaited debut album by the Brooklyn-based rapper is produced by Just Blaze and features guest appearances from Q-Tip, Jay-Z and other notable artists.

title: Push Barman To Open Old Wounds
summary: This 2-disc set collects 25 non-LP tracks that previously appeared on the band's early singles and EPs for Jeepster.

title: Women in Music, Pt. III
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles trio of sisters was produced with Rostam Batmanglij, Ariel Rechtshaid and Buddy Ross.

title: Same Trailer Different Park
summary: After three self-released albums, the country singer releases her first major label debut produced by Shane McAnally and Luke Laird.

title: We're New Again: A Reimagining by Makaya McCraven
summary: The final release of Gil Scott-Heron is reimagined by Makaya McCraven with contributions from Jeff Parker, Junius Paul, Brandee Younger, as well as samples from Agnes Zimondi and the Stephen McCraven Quartet.

title: folklore
summary: The 16-track surprise release from the pop artist features contributions from Jack Antonoff, Bon Iver, William Bowery, and Aaron Dessner of the National.

title: Chutes Too Narrow
summary: Phil Ek produced this sophomore effort for the Albuquerque-based group led by James Mercer (also of Flake), who wowed critics in 2001 with their 1960s-flavored debut 'Oh, Inverted World.'

title: Yours, Mine & Ours
summary: Joe Pernice and company return with ten new indie-pop gems.

title: To Be Kind
summary: The third release since the Michael Gira-led band reformed in 2010 was recorded by John Congleton and has a run time of over two hours.

title: Valentine
summary: The second full-length release for the Lindsey Jordan's indie rock project was co-produced by Brad Cook.

title: War Music
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the Swedish hardcore punk band was produced by Martin Ehrencrona.

title: American Band
summary: The 11th full-length release for the Southern rock band formed by Mike Cooley and Patterson Hood features songs about such topics as immigration, gun violence, politics, and race.

title: Hypermagic Mountain
summary: The abrasive bass/drums duo of Brian Gibson and Brian Chippendal return with a follow-up to 2003's 'Wonderful Rainbow.'

title: Only Built 4 Cuban Linx... Pt. II
summary: The Wu-Tang Clan-member releases his fourth solo album featuring such artists as his fellow Wu-Tang Clan members, Jadakiss, Beanie Sigel, Lyfe Jennings, Styles P, Busta Rhymes, and Slick Rick.

title: Memorial
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Chicago post-rock trio features a guest appearance from Chelsea Wolfe.

title: Song for Our Daughter
summary: The seventh full-length solo release for the British singer-songwriter was produced with Ethan Johns and Dom Monks.

title: Future Nostalgia
summary: The second full-length release for the British pop singer-songwriter features contributions from such artists as Ghosted, Stuart Price, Shakka, Tove Lo, and samples INXS's "Need You Tonight."

title: The Witmark Demos: 1962-1964
summary: The ninth volume from Bob Dylan's Bootleg Series contains the 47 songs he recorded in 1962-64.

title: Divers
summary: The fourth full-length release for the singer-songwriter features the Prague Philharmonic Orchestra and arrangements by Nico Muhly and David Longstreth.
The first full-length release from Adele in six years features production from Ludwig Göransson, Inflo, Tobias Jesso Jr., Greg Kurstin, Max Martin, and Shellback.

title: 69 Love Songs
summary: The title says it all. This 3-disc set indeed contains 69 love songs, all penned by Stephin Merritt (whose other projects include The 6ths, Future Bible Heroes, and the Gothic Archies). The Magnetic Fields have evolved into a real "band," including keyboardist Claudia Gonson (also Merritt's manager) and multi-instrumentalist John Woo, and Merritt alternates on vocals with Gonson and additional singers. Despite the almost encyclopedic variety of styles and huge volume of songs, there is surprisingly little filler here.

title: Caligula
summary: The third full-length release for Rhode Island artist Kristin Hayter was mixed by Seth Manchester features contributions from Mike Berdan, Lee Buford, Ted Byrnes, Noraa Kaplan, Sam McKinlay, and Dylan Walker.

title: Ta Det Lugnt
summary: This is the third album of psychedelic-rock tunes from Swedish multi-instrumentalist/vocalist Gustav Ejstes.

title: Long Lost
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Los Angeles-based indie folk band features a duet with Allison Ponthier.

title: Loud City Song
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles artist was influenced in part by the film "Gigi."

title: Charity Starts at Home
summary: The latest album for the rapper who also is a member of Little Brother and The Foreign Exchange features guest appearances by 9th Wonder, Big K.R.I.T., Evidence, Elzhi, and Pharoahe Monch.

title: Bad as Me
summary: The latest album for the singer-songwriter is the first album of all new songs since 2004's Real Gone.

title: A Moon Shaped Pool
summary: This is the surprise release of the ninth full-length studio album from the British rock band. A physical release is scheduled for 17 Jun 2016.

title: Masseduction
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Grammy-winning singer-songwriter was co-produced with Jack Antonoff and features contributions from Tuck & Patti Andress, Thomas Bartlett, Rich Hinman, Greg Leisz, Jenny Lewis, Sounwave, and Kamasi Washington.

title: Accelerando
summary: The third album from pianist Vijay Iyer with bassist Stephen Crump and drummer Marcus Gilmore includes several original compositions as well as cover songs from jazz, disco, R&B, and electronic music.

title: Saint Cloud
summary: The fifth full-length release for the indie music project of Katie Crutchfield was produced by Brad Cook.

title: Dear Science,
summary: The fourth album for the New York band was produced by Dave Sitek.

title: Sometimes I Might Be Introvert
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British rapper was produced by Inflo and features guest appearances from Obongjayar and Cleo Sol.

title: Return To Cookie Mountain
summary: David Bowie guests on the highly-anticipated second LP (and major-label debut) from the distinctive NYC band.

title: Call Me If You Get Lost
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from 42 Dugg, Daisy World, Domo Genesis, Brent Faiyaz, Fana Hues, Lil Uzi Vert, Lil Wayne, NBA YoungBoy, Teezo Touchdown, Ty Dolla $ign, and Pharrell Williams.

title: Sometimes I Sit And Think, And Sometimes I Just Sit
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Australian indie singer-songwriter.

title: Run the Jewels 3
summary: Available as a free download, the third LP (not including cat-related material) from the duo of El-P and Killer Mike includes contributions from Danny Brown, Zack de la Rocha, Tunde Adebimpe (TV on the Radio), Boots, and Kamasi Washington. Originally scheduled for release in January 2017, it arrived as a surprise on Christmas Day in 2016.

title: Persona
summary: The latest release for the British electronic artist was inspired by Ingmar Bergman's film of the same name.

title: POST-
summary: The third full-length solo release for the Long Island singer-songwriter features contributions from Chris Farren, Dan Potthast, PUP, Laura Stevenson, and Antarctigo Vespucci.

title: Up In Flames
summary: The second LP from Canadian electronic artist Dan Snaith is more song-oriented (and quite a bit more psychedelic) than efforts from similar artists, with Snaith even providing vocals on some tracks. [This release was originally credited under the name Manitoba before being re-released under the name Caribou after the name change]

title: Wicked Grin
summary: Tom Waits produced the album and wrote 12 of the 13 tracks.

title: Stories from the City, Stories from the Sea
summary: PJ Harvey's fifth, and possibly best, album sees her venturing away from the electronic experimentation of 1998's 'Is This Desire?' and returning to the purer rock sound prevalent on her early releases. Radiohead's Thom Yorke guests on the duet "This Mess We're In." Winner of the 2001 Mercury Music Prize.

title: Heaven to a Tortured Mind
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for Sean Bowie as Yves Tumor was co-produced by Justin Raisen.

title: Alfredo
summary: The latest collaboration between Freddie Gibbs and The Alchemist features guest appearances from Benny the Butcher, Conway the Machine, Rick Ross, and Tyler, The Creator.

title: That's the Spirit
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the British metal band was produced by band members Oli Sykes and Jordan Fish.

title: Black America Again
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the hip hop artist features guest appearances from Marsha Ambrosius, Bilal, BJ the Chicago Kid, Tasha Cobbs, John Legend, PJ, Syd tha Kyd, and Stevie Wonder.

title: Destroyer's Rubies
summary: Dan Bejar's seventh Destroyer record is as lyrically dense as ever, but marks a shift to a full-band, guitar-oriented sound after 2004's more eclectic 'Your Blues.'

title: Designer
summary: The third full-length release for the New Zealand singer-songwriter was produced by John Parish.

title: Magdalene
summary: The second full-length studio release for the British experimental R&B artist Tahliah Barnett features a guest appearance from Future.

title: Where Shall You Take Me
summary: The fifth full-length for the Seattle-based singer-songwriter returns with ten new mostly-acoustic tales about America's heartland, including live favorite "Texas to Ohio."

title: Letter to You
summary: The 20th full-length studio release for the rock artist was recorded over five days with the E Street Band and producer Ron Aniello.

title: Undun
summary: The 13th studio album is a concept album about the life of Redford Stephens, a fictional character who gets involved with drugs.

title: From A Basement On The Hill
summary: The late singer-songwriter was nearly done with this highly anticipated album at the time of his death in 2003.

title: Rejoicing In The Hands
summary: The second LP from the New York-based artist/musician/crazy hippie Devendra Banhart (who studied at the San Francisco Art Institute) includes 16 of the 32 lo-fi tracks recorded in the living room of veteran recording engineer Lynn Bridges. The remaining 16 will be released on a separate album later in 2004.

title: Vespertine
summary: Bjork's follow-up to 1997's 'Homogenic' and last year's soundtrack to Dancer In The Dark is closer in sound and mood to the latter, taking a quieter, more ambient approach. Produced by San Francisco-based electronic artists Matmos, 'Vespertine' utilizes mainly electronic instrumentation, much of which was recorded by Bjork in Iceland. The lead single is "Hidden Place."

title: Jubilee
summary: The third full-length release for Michelle Zauner was inspired in part by Bjork's Homogenic and Wilco's Summerteeth.

title: The Blueprint
summary: The now-legendary Brooklyn rapper follows 2000's 'The Dynasty Roc la Familia' with this 13-track disc.

title: Nine
summary: The fourth full-length release for the UK group is only available online for 99 days and features guest appearances from Little Simz and Michael Ofo.

title: From Kinshasa
summary: After leaving Staff Benda Bilili in 2013, Coco Ngambali and Theo Nsituvuidi started a new group and released this debut release produced by Liam "Doctor L" Farrell.

title: In Rainbows
summary: Radiohead releases their latest with a pay-what-you-want price.

title: The Woods
summary: The ubiquitous Dave Fridmann produced this latest outing for the veteran indie rockers, their first album for Sub Pop.

title: Lonerism
summary: The second release for the Perth, Australian band led by Kevin Parker was co-produce with Dave Fridmann.

title: Kill The Moonlight
summary: The Austin, Tex. indie rockers return with their fourth album, following 2001's critically acclaimed 'Girls Can Tell.'

title: Monoliths & Dimensions
summary: The metal band worked with composer Eyvind Kang on its seventh album, which features Australian guitar player Oren Ambarchi, vocalists Attila Csihar, Jessika Kenney, Earth's Dylan Carlson, and trombonists Julian Priester and Stuart Dempster as guest artists.

title: Jaime
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the Alabama Shakes frontwoman features contributions from Zac Cockrell, Shawn Everett, Robert Glasper, and Nate Smith.

title: Bandana
summary: The second full-length studio collaboration between Freddie Gibbs and Madlib features guest appearances from Anderson .Paak, Yasiin Bey, Black Thought, Killer Mike, and Pusha T.

title: Foundations of Burden
summary: The second full-length release for the doom metal band was produced by Billy Anderson.

title: The Graceless Age
summary: Co-produced with Tim Mooney, the debut full-length release for the San Francisco-based, Mississippi-born singer-songwriter speaks of his struggle against dug addiction.

title: Crown and Treaty
summary: The third full-length release for the British rock band is its first since adding American Jana Carpenter to the group and winning a Mercury Prize for its 2009 album, Twice Born Men.

title: All We Love We Leave Behind
summary: This is the eigth studio release from the Boston metalcore band led by Kurt Ballou.

title: Joy As an Act of Resistance
summary: The second full-length release for the British punk band was produced by Space and mixed by Adam Greenspan and Nick Launay.

title: Art Angels
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Canadian artist was self-produced and features guest appearances from Aristophanes and Janelle Monáe.

title: Dawn FM
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for The Weeknd features guest appearances from Jim Carrey, Lil Wayne, and Tyler, the Creator as well as contributions from Oscar Holter, Quincy Jones, Max Martin, and Oneohtrix Point Never.

title: Black Tambourine
summary: The compilation, which includes six unreleased songs, as well as tracks released earlier on 1999's "Complete Recordings," for the Washington, D.C.-area indie pop band which was originally formed as a side project for members of Whorl and Velocity Girl with Pam Berry as the lead singer.

title: Abattoir Blues / The Lyre Of Orpheus
summary: Nick Cave & The Bad Seeds' 13th album actually spans two separate discs, each produced by Nick Launay. And speaking of the Bad Seeds, longtime member Blixa Bargeld has been replaced by James Johnston (Gallon Drunk).

title: I Am A Bird Now
summary: The androgynous singer Antony is backed by the likes of Lou Reed, Devendra Banhart, Boy George and Rufus Wainwright on his sophomore release.

title: Fishscale
summary: MF Doom, Madlib and Pete Rock lend their production talents to the Wu-Tang member's fifth solo outing, which includes a collaboration with Ne-Yo.

title: No Devolucion
summary: The punk rock band from New Jersey, credited as one of the first bands to give birth to the genre of emo, celebrates 10 years with a new release.

title: Rooms of the House
summary: The third full-length album from the Michigan post-hardcore led by  Jordan Dreyer was co-produced with Will Yip.

title: I Loved You at Your Darkest
summary: The 11th full-length release for the Polish death metal band was self-produced and features a 17-piece Polish orchestra arranged by Jan Stoklosa.

title: Cadillactica
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Mississippi rapper features such guests as Bun B, Devin the Dude, E-40, Lupe Fiasco, Rico Love, Raphael Saadiq, and Wiz Khalifa.

title: Arular
summary: This short but wildly eclectic debut album from Maya Arulpragasam, a Sri Lankan-born, London-based artist and daughter of a Tamil Tiger revolutionary, is preceded by enormous buzz in both the U.K. and the U.S.

title: Negative Capability
summary: The 21st full-length studio release for the British singer-songwriter features contributions from such artists as Warren Ellis, Nick Cave, Rob Ellis, Ed Harcourt and Mark Lanegan.

title: You're Dead!
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the Los Angeles-based artist/producer features guest appearances from Captain Murphy, Angel Deradoorian, Kendrick Lamar, Niki Randa, Snoop Dogg, and Thundercat.

title: Science Fiction
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Long Island rock band was a surprise digital release and was produced by Mike Sapone. A physical release is expected in October.

title: Remedy
summary: This long-awaited debut LP from the London, England house production duo of Simon Ratcliffe and Felix Buxton has since been recognized as one of the better dance recordings of all time. It was named by Spin as one of the 90 Best Albums of the 90's.

title: Homegrown
summary: The previously unreleased album for the singer-songwriter was originally set to be released in 1975 before it was cancelled. It features contributions from Tim Drummond, Emmylou Harris, Levon Helm, Karl T Himmel, Ben Keith, and Robbie Robertson.

title: Shepherd in a Sheepskin Vest
summary: The first new release in six years for the Austin-based singer-songwriter was recorded and mixed by Brian Beattie.

title: Exit
summary: The latest album from the Japanese musician includes more than 50 instruments.

title: For Emma, Forever Ago
summary: The debut album from ex-DeYarmond Edison member Justin Vernon.

title: Complicated Game
summary: The first studio release in six years for the singer-songwriter was co-produced by C.C. Adcock and Mike Napolitano.

title: Pacific Ocean Blue [Reissue]
summary: Beach Boy Dennis Wilson's solo album is rereleased with songs from his unreleased "Bambu" album and one unfinished track sung by the Foo Fighters' Taylor Hawkins.

title: Plunge
summary: The second full-length solo release for Karin Dreijer is her first in over eight years.

title: Leaves Turn Inside You
summary: The first album in three years for the indie rockers is an epic 2-CD set.

title: Have You in My Wilderness
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Los Angeles-based singer-songwriter was recorded with Cole M. Greif-Neill.

title: Fleet Foxes
summary: This is the debut album from the Seattle area quintet.

title: Dirty Computer
summary: The third LP (and first in five years) from the actress and recording artist features appearances by Brian Wilson, Pharrell Williams, Zoë Kravitz, and Grimes, plus musical contributions from Prince just prior to his death.

title: Fetch
summary: The four tracks combine elements from jazz and dub-techno with the help of guest artists Marc Muellbauer, Jonas Schoen, and Sebastian Studnitzky for the Moritz Von Oswald Trio's latest release.

title: Blue Record
summary: The second full-length album for the Georgia-based rock band is its first with new guitarist Peter Adams.

title: Person Pitch
summary: The third solo album from Animal Collective's Noah Lennox (aka Panda Bear) is completely unlike its predecessor, as it is both upbeat and electronic, sounding like a spacey, 21st century Beach Boys album.

title: College Dropout
summary: The in-demand Chicago-based producer makes his debut with the help of guests Ludacris, Jay-Z, Mos Def, Dirt McGirt, and more.

title: Twin Fantasy
summary: Will Toledo re-recorded songs from his Bandcamp-released 2011 album of the same name with a full-band for this release.

title: Music For the Quiet Hour/The Drawbar Organ EPs
summary: The box set contains three vinyl LPs featuring sounds made from an Italian drawbar organ and a CD with an hour of experimental electronic music featuring Vengeance Tenfold.

title: Upland Stories
summary: The latest release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Shad Cobb, Flatlanders guitarist Robbie Gjersoe, Alex Hall, Wayne Horvitz, Fats Kaplin, Todd Phillips, Jenny Scheinman, and was recorded by Steve Albini.

title: Blackstar
summary: The 25th full-length studio release for the art-rock artist is a seven-track album featuring contributions from Mark Guiliana, Jason Lindner, Donny McCaslin, Ben Monder, LCD Soundsystem's James Murphy, and Tedeschi Trucks Band's Tim Lefebvre.

title: Something More Than Free
summary: The fifth full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter was produced by Dave Cobb.

title: M B V
summary: The long-awaited follow-up to My Bloody Valentine's 1991 classic shoegaze album Loveless was made available on its website.

title: U.F.O.F.
summary: The third full-length release for the Brooklyn indie rock band led by Adrianne Lenker was produced by Andrew Sarlo.

title: My Woman
summary: The third full-length release for the North Carolina-based singer-songwriter was produced by Justin Raisen.

title: In These Silent Days
summary: The seventh full-length release for the singer-songwriter features a guest appearance from Lucius and was co-produced by Dave Cobb and Shooter Jennings.

title: Microshift
summary: The third full-length release for the British rock band features electronic elements such as samples, loops, and synths.

title: Flock
summary: The latest full-length solo release for the British singer-songwriter is said to be inspired by "Lebanese torch songs, 1980s Russian Aerobics records, and Australian Punk."

title: A Billion Heartbeats
summary: The sixth full-length release for the British indie rock band was inspired by recent protests and produced with Matt Twaites.

title: Laila’s Wisdom
summary: The second full-length release for the North Carolina rapper feature guest appearances from  BJ The Chicago Kid, Black Thought, Gwen Bunn, Busta Rhymes, GQ, Kendrick Lamar, Lance Skiiiwalker, Terrace Martin, Moonchild, Musiq Soulchild,  Amber Navran, and Anderson .Paak.

title: John Howard & the Night Mail
summary: This is the latest release from the British singer-songwriter with Andy Lewis and Ian Button.

title: Ten Love Songs
summary: The fifth studio release for the Norwegian singer-songwriter features contributions from Anthony Gonzalez of M83, Lars Horntveth of Jaga Jazzist, Svein & Torbjorn from Röyksopp, and the Trondheimsolistene Chamber Ensemble.

title: The Wonder Years
summary: The fourth solo album for the hip-hop producer features such guests as Erykah Badu, Khrysis, Talib Kweli, Kendrick Lamar, Murs, Phonte, Raekwon, and Warren G.

title: Silent Movies
summary: The guitarist's latest solo album is inspired by film scores he had written for others or for himself.

title: Microphones in 2020
summary: The first album in 17 years for Phil Elverum under the name The Microphones features one track that is nearly 45 minutes long.

title: Decoration Day
summary: The Southern rock band led by Patterson Hood  follow up their 2-disc concept album about Lynyrd Skynyrd ('The Southern Rock Opera') with this less conceptual but equally rocking LP.

title: The Argument
summary: Though Washington D.C. hard rockers Fugazi have been together for almost 15 years, this is just their eighth full-length release.

title: Showtime
summary: The UK rapper follows his Mercury Music Prize-winning debut 'Boy In The Corner' with this sophomore release.

title: Blonde
summary: Just a a day after he released his Visual album Endless, Ocean releases a 17-track album on Apple Music (and a 12-track version at pop-up stores included a Boys Don't Cry artbook/magazine) featuring contributions from Beyonce, Jonny Greenwood of Radiohead, Kendrick Lamar, Rick Rubin, and Kanye West.

title: Cusp
summary: The sixth full-length release from the singer-songwriter features contributions from Peter Broderick, Heather Woods Broderick, Rob Burger, Ryan Francesconi, Daniel Hunt, and Luke Ydstie.

title: Dig!!! Lazarus Dig!!!
summary: The latest album for the alternative rock band from Australia was inspired by the story of Lazarus rising from the dead, as well as Harry Houdini.

title: Angel Tears in Sunlight
summary: The posthumously released album was the first new music in over 30 years for the San Francisco-based composer.

title: The Thin Black Duke
summary: The seventh full-length release for the San Francisco experimental rock band is its first in a decade.

title: Choose Your Weapon
summary: This is the second full-length release for the Grammy-nominated Australian band led by Nai Palm.

title: Henki
summary: Historic plants are the theme of the full-length collaboration between Richard Dawson and Circle.

title: Cocoon Crush
summary: This is the second full-length release for Berlin-based electronic producer TJ Hertz.

title: Southeastern
summary: Produced by David Cobb, the latest solo release for former Drive-By Truckers guitarist includes guest appearances by Kim Richey and his wife, Amanda Shires.

title: Reward
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the Welsh singer-songwriter features contributions from Huw Evans, Sweet Baboo's Stephen Black, Samur Khouja, Josh Klinghoffer, and Warpaint's Stella Mozgawa, and Josiah Steinbrick.

title: You Won't Get What You Want
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Rhode Island noise-rock band is its first since the quartet reunited in 2013.

title: The Dirty South
summary: No, the Drive-By Truckers haven't gone all gangsta rap on us; the title is just one example of the southern rockers' playful side. Founders Patterson Hood and Mike Cooley remain, although their surrounding cast has changed a bit since the acclaimed 'Decoration Day.'

title: Forfolks
summary: The latest full-length solo release from Tortoise guitarist Jeff Parker features six originals and two covers he recorded over two days at his home studio.

title: The River & the Thread
summary: The first release of new material in eight years for the singer-songwriter was inspired by her travels in the South.

title: Painted Shut
summary: Originally a solo project Frances Quinlan under the name Hop Along, Queen Ansleis, the second full-length release sees the addition of three members, a shorter name, and co-production from John Agnello.

title: Historicity
summary: Pianist Vijay Iyer debuts his first album as part of a classic trio of jazz musicians.

title: An Overview on Phenomenal Nature
summary: The second full-length solo release for the New York folk artist was produced by Josh Kaufman.

title: Pain Olympics
summary: The latest release for the post-punk Canadian collective was self-produced.

title: Too Bright
summary: The third full-length release from Seattle singer-songwriter Mike Hadreas as Perfume Genius was co-produced with Adrian Utley and John Parish.

title: Guppy
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the New York pop rock band led by Eva Hendricks.

title: The Town And The City
summary: The follow-up to 2004's 'The Ride' is a timely 13-track song cycle about American immigration.

title: Workaround
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the London-based electronic producer features contributions from such artists as Batu, Kuljit Bhamra, Laurel Halo, Kadialy Kouyaté, Jonny Lam, Lucy Railton, and Untold.

title: World Without Tears
summary: Recorded live in studio with her band and co-produced by Mark Howard, 'World Without Tears' marks the follow-up to Williams' acclaimed 2001 release 'Essence.'

title: Cold House
summary: This is the Leeds, England indie-rock band's first American LP release in four years. Akin to recent Radiohead, this disc incorporates experimental electronica elements, and also adds guest vocals from members of hip-hop outfit cLOUDDEAD.

title: Things We Lost In The Fire
The Seer
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Michael Gira project includes the 32-minute title track and guest appearances by Akron/Family), Karen O, Alan Sparhawk, and Mimi Parker of Low

title: Purple Mountains
summary: Just over 10 years after Silver Jews' David Berman announced his retirement, he returns with a new project produced by Jarvis Taveniere and Jeremy Earl of Woods.

title: Puberty 2
summary: The fourth full-length release for the New York indie artist was produced by Patrick Hyland.

title: Arca
summary: The third full-length release for the London-based electronic producer is the first to feature him singing in Spanish.

title: You Will Never Be One of Us
summary: The third full-length release for the California metal trio was produced by Kurt Ballou.

title: Summertime '06
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the Long Beach rapper features production from Clams Casino, DJ Dahi, Brian Kidd, No I.D., and Christian Rich.

title: Raising Sand
summary: The Led Zeppelin singer pairs up with Bluegrass singer Alison Krauss.

title: Now, More Than Ever
summary: The third solo disc from the Canadian singer-songwriter and member of Royal City features members of Hidden Cameras, Royal City and The Constantines.

title: And Their Refinement Of The Decline
summary: The Austin-based duo releases its first new album in six years.

title: Let's Stay Friends
summary: The New York City-based band's fourth studio album.

title: Vulnicura
summary: Originally scheduled for a March release, the ninth studio release for the Icelandic singer-songwriter was released early on iTunes after an illegal leak of the songs was available.

title: Edna
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the British rapper features guest appearances from Aitch, Bugsey, Haile, M Huncho, Ivorian Doll, Mahalia, Kaash Paige, Skepta, Stormzy, AJ Tracey, Young Adz, and Young T.

title: Reaching for Indigo
summary: The sixth full-length release for Haley Fohr as Circuit des Yeux was co-produced with Cooper Crain.

title: Airtight's Revenge
summary: The soul singer returns with his first release on indie label Plug Research after Interscope Records shelved what would have been his second album, Love for Sale, in 2006.

title: Franz Ferdinand
summary: The most hyped band to come out of the UK in early 2004 is Glasgow, Scotland's Franz Ferdinand, an art-rock quartet who make their full-length debut with this self-titled release, the winner of the UK's coveted Mercury Music Prize in 2004.

title: I Love You, Honeybear
summary: The second full-length release from Josh Tillman as Father John Misty was co-produced with Jonathan Wilson.

title: Virgins
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Canadian experimental electronic producer was recorded live in Montreal, Reykjavik, and Seattle.

title: Be the Cowboy
summary: The fifth full-length release for the New York City indie rock artist was recorded with producer Patrick Hyland.

title: xx
summary: This is the debut album for the South London quartet.

title: Let Me Do One More
summary: The latest full-length release for the Sarah Tudzin project features guest appearances from Buck Meek and Alex Menne.

title: World Music
summary: This is their debut album for the seven-man collective hailing from the tiny village of Korpilombolo in northern Sweden.

title: Ohms
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the Sacramento alternative metal band was produced by Terry Date.

title: Ágætis Byrjun
summary: This sophomore effort from Icelandic quartet Sigur Ros (which translates to "Victory Rose") appeared on numerous year-end Best Of lists in 2000, despite not receiving an official release in the United States until the following year. Imagine one of Radiohead's recent albums -- or better yet, Spiritualized or My Bloody Valentine -- but with everything sung in Icelandic. This album garnered the band the 2001 Shortlist Prize for Artistic Achievement In Music.

title: Random Access Memories
summary: The fourth studio release for the electronic duo features guest appearances by Julian Casablancas, Todd Edwards, Panda Bear, Paul Williams, and Pharrell Williams.

title: Soil
summary: The debut full-length release for the New York-based alternative R&B artist features production from Clams Casino, Paul Epworth, and Katie Gately.

title: Neon Bible
summary: One of the most anticipated releases of 2007 is this second album from Montreal's Arcade Fire, the Win Butler- and Regine Chassagne-led band that won over bloggers, critics, and, ultimately, fans with their 2004 debut 'Funeral.'

title: Remembering Mountains: Unheard Songs By Karen Dalton
summary: Isobel Campbell, Diane Cluck, Sharon Van Etten, Josephine Foster, Patty Griffin, Larkin Grimm, Laurel Halo, Julia Holter, Marissa Nadler, Tara Jane O'Neil, and Lucinda Williams give voice to lyrics and poems written by folk singer-songwriter Karen Dalton.

title: Yankee Hotel Foxtrot
summary: The long wait for this fourth album from Jeff Tweedy & co. is partially the result of the tumultuous recording process that left the band without its guitarist (Jay Bennett) and its record label (Warner/Reprise). Fellow Chicagoan Jim O'Rourke mixed the 11 tracks.

title: Norman Fucking Rockwell!
summary: The sixth full-length release for the pop singer-songwriter was produced with Jack Antonoff and features contributions from Louis Bell, Zach Dawes, Rick Nowels, and Andrew Watt.

title: Congotronics
summary: The first installment of a series of "Congotronics" releases features seven tracks by 30-year old Kinshasa-based band Konono No. 1, whose unconventional, homemade amplification brings an almost experimental edge to traditional African trance music.

title: Stumble Into Grace
summary: Still going strong at 57, the Grammy-winning artist offers 12 new tracks, with some A-list backing from the likes of Linda Ronstadt, Jill Cunniff, Jane Siberry, and Kate and Anna McGarrigle.

title: Phrenology
summary: The groundbreaking Philadelphia rap outfit returns with 13 new tracks and guest contributions from Jill Scott, Nelly Furtado, Talib Kweli and Musiq.

title: Celestial Lineage
summary: The Washington state metal band's fourth studio album seeks to envision a place full of cedar trees for the listeners.

title: Shall We Go on Sinning So That Grace May Increase?
summary: The latest release for Drew Daniel project features vocals from Angel Deradoorian, Jana Hunter and Colin Self.

title: In a Poem Unlimited
summary: The sixth full-length release for Meg Remy as U.S. Girls was recorded with a live band and was co-produced with Steve Chahley.

title: Annie Up
summary: The second release for the country trio of Miranda Lambert, Ashley Monroe, and Angaleena Presley was produced by Frank Liddell, Glenn Worf, and Chuck Ainlay.

title: Is Survived By
summary: The third full-length release for the five-piece hardcore band led by Jeremy Bolm was produced by Brad Wood.

title: Innocence is Kinky
summary: Produced by John Parish, the Norwegian artist's latest release was influenced by a sound and light installation commissioned in 2011.

title: Cocoa Sugar
summary: The third full-length release for the Edinburgh-based trio was recorded in the band's studio.

title: The Suburbs
summary: The Montreal band return with their third studio album of soaring anthems and varied instrumentation, a pairing that has successfully secured their place as indie rock royalty.

title: Beautiful Africa
summary: John Parish produced the Malian–born singer-songwriter's fifth release featuring songs sung in English, French, and Bambara.

title: In Colour
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the xx's Jamie Smith features guest appearances from Popcaan, Young Thug, as well as his xx bandmates Romy Croft and Oliver Sim.

title: Gone Away Backward
summary: The 11th release for the Chicago-based singer-songwriter was produced by Steve Albini.

title: Favourite Colours
summary: The Toronto, Canada country-surf-rockers led by the Good brothers (Dallas and Travis) return with a self-produced effort. Robyn Hitchcock guests on one track.

title: The Creek Drank The Cradle
summary: Written, recorded and performed entirely by Miami, Fla-based Samuel Beam, 'The Creek Drank The Cradle' is the debut album for Iron & Wine, a largely lo-fi, acoustic affair with a darker take on folk and bluegrass.

title: Children Running Through
summary: Mike McCarthy produced this fifth studio album for the singer-songwriter, her first in three years.

title: House of Balloons
summary: The mixtape by Canadian artist Abel Tesfaye was released as a free download.

title: Shore
summary: The surprise release of the fourth full-length album for the indie folk band led by Robin Pecknold was recorded in California, New York and Paris, France.

title: Seven Swans
summary: The indie singer-songwriter's fourth solo album, produced by Danielson Famile's Daniel Smith, follows on the heels of his critically-lauded 2003 effort 'Greetings From Michigan.'

title: Kala
summary: The UK rapper returns with her second album, which was recorded in several countries.

title: Bouger le Monde!
summary: The second album from the Congolese band with four paraplegic members sees the addition of a new drummer and lead guitarist.

title: Freedom
summary: The fifth full-length release for Damon McMahon features contributions from Delicate Steve, Parker Kindred, Gus Seyffert , Jordi Wheeler,  Nick Zinner and was produced by Chris Coady.

title: V
summary: The fifth full-length release for the British rock band was produced with Paul Epworth.

title: Sound Ancestors
summary: The latest full-length release for the Los Angeles-based hip-hop artist was edited, arranged and mastered by Kieran Hebden (Four Tet).

title: Use Me
summary: The third full-length release for the Massachusetts band led by Lynn Gunn was produced with JT Daly.

title: Isolation
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the Virginia artist features guest appearances from BIA, Bootsy Collins, Steve Lacy, Reykon, Jorja Smith and Tyler, The Creator as well as production from BadBadNotGood, Gorillaz, Greg Kurstin, Kevin Parker, Dave Sitek, and Thundercat.

title: Death of a Cheerleader
summary: The debut full-length release for the Brooklyn-based quartet led by Mia Berrin was produced and mixed by Sarah Tudzin.

title: 22, A Million
summary: The third full-length release for Justin Vernon was produced by Chris Messina.

title: Phantom Power
summary: The quirky Welsh quintet's sixth album was produced by Mario Caldato Jr. (Beastie Boys).

title: Colfax
summary: This is the debut release for the new band formed by Richmond Fontaine's Willy Vlautin with Amy Boone and Sean Oldham.

title: Springsteen on Broadway
summary: The two-CD set features the complete audio of Springsteen's one-man Broadway show at Walter Kerr Theatre recorded on July 17 and 18, 2018 for Netflix.

title: Nashville Obsolete
summary: The second full-length release for the guitarist features Paul Kowert, Brittany Haas, Jordan Tice, Willie Watson, and Gillian Welch (who also co-wrote the songs and sings with Rawlings).

title: DFA Remixes: Chapter 1
summary: This volume collects 9 remixes by the production team The DFA (the duo of Tim Goldsworthy and James Murphy) of songs by Gorillaz, Hot Chip, Chemical Brothers, Le Tigre, Radio 4 and more.

title: Mass Romantic
summary: This Vancouver, Canada-based indie-rock supergroup features members of Limblifter, Zumpano and Destroyer and is fronted by Neko Case.

title: Let England Shake
summary: Polly Jean Harvey takes a political approach on her latest album, as a singer-songwriter speaking on the casualties of war, the cruelty of life and the condition of being human.

title: Sound Of Silver
summary: Dance-punk producer (and one-half of The DFA) James Murphy returns with his second LCD Soundsytem album.

title: Fatigue
summary: The second full-length release for the Brooklyn-based experimental artist was  produced with Andrew Lappin.

title: CTRL
summary: The debut full-length release for the New Jersey alternative R&B artist features guest appearances from James Fauntleroy, Kendrick Lamar, Isaiah Rashad, and Travis Scott.

title: Nightmare Logic
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Texas trash metal band was produced by Arthur Rizk.

title: Róisín Machine
summary: The fifth full-length solo studio release for the Irish electro-pop artist was recorded with Richard Barratt (also known as DJ Parrot or Crooked Man).

title: Body Talk

title: Hollowed
summary: This is the fifth full-length for British electronic producer Alan Myson.

title: Bécs
summary: The sixth full-length solo release for the Austrian  electronic producer Christian Fennesz is considered a conceptual follow-up to 2001's Endless Summer.

title: Who Kill

title: This Is Still It
summary: This is a 19-track collection of songs from the rock band who were contemporaries from the Athens, Georgia, music scene that also included such artists as R.E.M., The B-52s, and Pylon.

title: One Word Extinguisher
summary: Underground producer Scott Herren (aka Prefuse 73) offers his second LP for Warp, which mixes experimental glitchtronica with more accessible hip-hop elements (including vocals on a few tracks provided by guests such as Mr. Lif).

title: Time (The Revelator)
summary: This is the third album for the California native. David Rawlings has replaced T-Bone Burnett as producer.

title: Comicopera
summary: The English singer's latest includes Brian Eno, Paul Weller, and Phil Manzanera as guests.

title: Remind Me Tomorrow
summary: The fifth full-length release for the singer-songwriter was produced by John Congleton.

title: thank u, next
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the pop singer features production from Charles Anderson, Tommy Brown, Michael Foster, Max Martin, Happy Perez, Ilya Salmanzadeh, and Andrew "Pop" Wansel.

title: Far from Over
summary: The latest release for the jazz pianist includes Stephan Crump, Graham Haynes, Steve Lehman, Mark Shim, and Tyshawn Sorey to form a sextet.

title: Welcome To Mali
summary: The African duo met at a school for the blind and have since written a song for the 2006 World Cup and their latest album features production by Damon Albarn.

title: A Sailor's Guide to Earth
summary: The third full-length release for the Grammy-nominated country artist features a cover of a Nirvana song and was self-produced.

title: Natalie Prass
summary: The debut full-length release for the singer-songwriter was co-produced by Matthew E. White and Trey Pollard.

title: Mirrored

title: For Sale: Live at Maxwell's 1986
summary: The unreleased live recording of the Minneapolis rock band's concert in Hoboken, New Jersey with its original line-up (Bob Stinson would be fired toward the end of that year).

title: Are We There
summary: The fourth full-length release for the singer-songwriter was self-produced.

title: Bon Iver
summary: The Wisconsin-based indie folk band, fronted by singer-songwriter Justin Vernon, follows up its highly acclaimed For Emma, Forever Ago with a new album.

title: How I Got Over
summary: The legendary Philadelphia posse returns with its first release since playing with Late Night With Jimmy Fallon's house band. Staying true to its roots with acoustic jazz grooves and elements of rock and soul, The Roots continue its reign as one of hip-hop's most innovative acts.

title: Afrique Victime
summary: The latest full-length release for the Tuareg guitarist is his first on the Matador label.

title: Love & Hate
summary: The second full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was produced by Danger Mouse.

title: Sparrow
summary: The fourth full-length release for the country singer-songwriter was produced with Dave Cobb.

title: New Energy
summary: The ninth full-length release for British electronic artist Kieran Hebden features contributions from Kaitlyn Aurelia Smith and Field Day co-founder Tom Baker.

title: From the Sea to the Land Beyond [OST]
summary: The indie band reworked some of its songs for the soundtrack to the Penny Woolcock's film about the history of the British coastline.

title: The  Blackest Beautiful
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles-based post-hardcore quartet was self-produced by the band with Kit Walters.

title: Book Burner
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Virginia grindcore/death metal band is its first with new drummer, Adam Jarvis.

title: Dead Cities, Red Seas & Lost Ghosts
summary: The second release from French electronica duo M83 takes shoegaze classics such as 'Loveless' as an inspiration, with synths taking the place of guitars.

title: Shade
summary: The 12th full-length studio release for Liz Harris features songs recorded in the past 16 years in Mount Tamalpais, Portland, and Astoria.

title: Hercules And Love Affair
summary: The debut album for the electronic group from New York.

title: Minute by Minute
summary: The first release in five years for the British soul singer was produced by Gabriel Roth.

title: Syro
summary: This is the first full-length studio release from Richard D. James as Aphex Twin in over 13 years.

title: Tracyanne & Danny
summary: The debut full-length release for the collaboration between Camera Obscura's Tracyanne Campbell and Crybaby's Danny Coughlan was produced by Edwyn Collins.

title: blackSUMMERS'night (2016)
summary: The fifth full-length release for the R&B singer is his first in seven years and was co-produced with Hod David.

title: Jericho Sirens
summary: The first new release for the San Diego post-hardcore band in 14 years was self-recorded and produced.

title: Young Man In America

title: Centres
summary: The ninth full-length release for the Canadian artist who uses cassette players, reel-to-reel machines and synthesizers to create his sound was recorded in a variety of places in Vancouver.

title: Life Is People
summary: The first new studio release from the British singer-songwriter in over 40 years was produced by Joshua Henry and features guest appearances by Wilco's Jeff Tweedy, Matt Armstrong, Matt Deighton, Mike Rowe, Ray Russell and Alan Rushton.

title: Teens of Denial
summary: The second full-length release (and the first recorded with a full band and studio production) for the indie rock band led by Will Toledo was produced by Steve Fisk.

title: Without a Net
summary: The third live release from the Wayne Shorter Quartet was recorded during the group's 2011 tour.

title: Midsommar [Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]
summary: The first solo film score for The Haxan Cloak's Bobby Krlic is for Ari Aster's 2019 horror film and features a 16-piece orchestra.

title: Narkopop
summary: This is the first full-length studio release in 17 years for Wolfgang Voigt's ambient techno project.

title: Estudando o Pagode
summary: Experimental Brazilian artist Tom Ze, now nearing 70 years old, continues to challenge with this concept album about the struggles of women in a male-dominated world.

title: King's Disease II
summary: The sequel to the rappers 2020 King's Disease album features guest appearances from A Boogie Wit da Hoodie, Blxst, Eminem, EPMD, Lauryn Hill, Hit-Boy, Charlie Wilson, and YG.

title: Robyn
summary: The fourth album for the Swedish singer was released in 2005 in her native Sweden.

title: Process
summary: The debut full-length release for the British R&B singer/producer was produced with Rodaidh McDonald.

title: Separation Sunday
summary: This is the second album from the New York City band led by Craig Finn.

title: The Decline Of British Sea Power
summary: Oft-compared to Joy Division, this unique British four-piece sports single-word names (Hamilton, Noble, Yan, and Wood), dons military apparel for their live shows, and tackles dark, weighty themes in their lyrics (Czech history, anyone)? 'The Decline' marks their full-length debut, drawing critical praise on both sides of the Atlantic.

title: You Forgot It In People
summary: The Toronto, Canada indie-rock collective generated a great deal of praise for this 2002 sophomore effort, which was released in the U.S. in June, 2003 for the first time.

title: Quicksand / Cradlesnakes
summary: Featuring basically the same lineup as the defunct Chicago band Red Red Meat, Califone makes their Thrill Jockey debut with this mix of country, blues, folk, and electronic elements.

title: Rings Around The World

It is the first album ever to be released simultaneously on DVD and CD (with the DVD containing a movie and a remix for each track on the album). Paul McCartney and John Cale have cameo appearances on the album.

title: The Night Chancers
summary: The sixth full-length solo release for the British indie artist was co-produced with Craig Silvey.

title: Deacon
summary: The second full-length release for the New York experimental R&B artist features a guest appearance from NAO.

title: Big Conspiracy
summary: The second full-length studio release for the British rapper features guest appearances form Burna Boy, iceè tgm, and Koffee.

title: Run the Jewels
summary: El-P and Killer Mike's latest collaboration was released as a free download features guest appearances from Big Boi, Prince Paul, and Until The Ribbon Breaks.

title: Minimum-Maximum [Live]
summary: This 2-disc set was recorded during the band's 2004 world tour.

title: Once I Was an Eagle
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the British singer-songwriter was produced by Ethan Johns.

title: Kaleidoscope Dream
summary: The second full-length release for the R&B singer includes six songs from two EPs released earlier in the year and features guest appearances from Alicia Keys and Wiz Khalifa.

title: Thunder, Lightning, Strike
