title: Heart's Ease
summary: The latest full-length release for the British singer-songwriter features four non-traditional songs.

title: Remain In Light
summary: The Beninese singer-songwriter covers the entire Talking Heads' 1980 album Remain In Light.

title: House of Sugar
summary: The latest full-length release for the Philadelphia artist features contributions from Samuel Acchione, Molly Germer, John Heywood, Tom Kelly, Jacob Portrait, and Emily Yacina.

title: Promises
summary: The nine-part project from Floating Points, Pharoah Sanders and the London Symphony Orchestra was recorded in Los Angeles and London.

title: 50 Song Memoir
summary: Each song represents one year in frontman Stephin Merritt's life in this 50-song, five-disc set from the indie pop band.

title: Heaven & Earth
summary: The second full-length release for the Los Angeles jazz saxophonist features contributions from Tony Austin, Ronald Bruner, Jr., Brandon Coleman, Cameron Graves, Terrace Martin, Miles Mosley, Patrice Quinn, and Thundercat.

title: Halcyon Digest
summary: The Atlanta-based quartet's fourth album combines calm shoegaze pop and noisy punk rock to create a dreamy, psychedelic sound.

title: Dissociation
summary: The sixth and final full-length studio release for the New Jersey mathcore band.

title: Dark Energy
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Gary, Indiana electronic producer.

title: Radyo Siwèl
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Canadian-born artist was influenced by her Haitian heritage.

title: Floreat
summary: The British singer-songwriter's second album produced by Dan Carey was delayed for three years after EMI took over her previous record label.

title: 'Sno Angel Like You
summary: The Giant Sand leader is backed by an eight-member gospel choir on this 14-track set.

title: Beautifully Human: Words And Sounds Vol. 2
summary: The soul singer returns with a follow-up to her Grammy-nominated debut.

title: Welcome Interstate Managers
summary: The New York-based indie-pop band, led by Adam Schlesinger and Chris Collingwood, returns with a long-awaited third LP.

title: Midwest Farmer's Daughter
summary: The debut full-length release for the country singer-songwriter was recorded at Sun Studios in Memphis.

title: Assume Crash Position
summary: The Democratic Republic of Congo group releases its latest album featuring such guests as Kasai All stars and guitarist Manuaku Pepe Felly.

title: Luxury Problems
summary: After two EPs last year, the Manchester producer releases a full-length electronic release featuring the operatically trained vocalist Alison Skidmore.

title: Space Is Only Noise
summary: The electronic producer who attends Brown University releases the first full-length album of his brand of sub-100-bpm house music.

title: Midlife: A Beginner's Guide To Blur
summary: The two-disc set contains some biggest hits, band favorites, and rare singles.
Originally conceived for Nike as a workout mix and released on iTunes, the physical release includes three songs previously available only in the UK.

title: Platinum
summary: The fifth full-length release for the country singer features guest appearances from Little Big Town, the Time Jumpers (a Grammy-nominated western swing ensemble that includes Vince Gill), and Carrie Underwood.

title: Dogrel
summary: The debut full-length release for the Irish indie rock band was produced and mixed by Dan Carey.

title: LCD Soundsystem
summary: Hipsters, rejoice! James Murphy, one-half of the in-demand indie-rock production duo The DFA (The Rapture, et al), finally makes his full-length debut as an artist as LCD Soundsystem.

title: A Kind Revolution
summary: The 13th full-length solo studio release for the British singer-songwriter was co-produced with Jan "Stan" Kybert and features guest appearances from PP Arnold, Madeleine Bell, Boy George, The Strypes' guitarist Josh McClorey, and Soft Machine's Robert Wyatt.

title: Elwan
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Tuareg blues-rock band features guest appearances from Alain Johannes, Mark Lanegan, Matt Sweeney, and Kurt Vile.

title: Double Negative
summary: The 12th full-length release for the indie rock trio was produced by B.J. Burton.

title: The Blade
summary: The second full-length release for the country singer-songwriter (who is also a member of Pistol Annies) was produced by Vince Gill and Justin Niebank.

title: This Is Where I Live
summary: The first release in 10 years for the soul artist was produced by John Leventhal.

title: It's Great to Be Alive! [Live]
summary: The three-disc live album collects 35 tracks from its three-night stand at the San Francisco's Fillmore Auditorium in November 2014.

title: Dragon New Warm Mountain I Believe in You
summary: The fifth full-length release for Brooklyn indie rock band Big Thief was recorded it was recorded in California, Colorado, upstate New York, and Tucson.

title: 3 Pears
summary: The first studio album in seven years for the country singer-songwriter features two songs produced by Beck and a song co-written with Robert Ritchie (aka Kid Rock).

title: Every Bad
summary: The second full-length release for the British indie rock band led by Dana Margolin is its first on the Secretly Canadian label.

title: Black Sheep Boy
summary: This is the fourth album for the Austin band led by singer-songwriter Will Sheff.

title: Seek Magic
summary: This is the debut album for Dayve Hawk as Memory Tapes.

title: Cosmogramma
summary: Thom York, Ravi Coltrane, and Laura Darlington appears as a guests on the experimental producer/artist's third full-length album.

title: Close Ties
summary: The latest release for the country singer-songwriter features guest appearances from Rosanne Cash, Sheryl Crow and John Paul White.

title: Koi No Yokan
summary: The seventh studio release for the Sacramento alternative metal group was produced by Nick Raskulinecz.

title: Shields
summary: The fourth album for the Brooklyn rock band was recorded in New York after a recordings session in Texas was largely scrapped.

title: Beyond the Pale
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the band that includes Pulp's Jarvis Cocker, Serafina Steer, Emma Smith, Andrew McKinney, Jason Buckle and Adam Betts.

title: Off Off On
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Kate Stables-led band was produced by Josh Kaufman.

title: U Kin B The Sun
summary: The third full-length solo release for the Canadian singer-songwriter was produced with John Raham.

title: Joy of Living: A Tribute to Ewan Maccoll
summary: The two-disc tribute to the British folk artist features such artists as Paul Brady, Bombay Bicycle Club, Billy Bragg, Paul Buchanan of the Blue Nile, Eliza Carthy, Martin Carthy, Jarvis Cocker of Pulp, Steve Earle, David Gray, Dick Gaughan, The Unthanks, Norma Waterson and Rufus & Martha Wainwright.

title: LP1
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the British experimental R&B artist Tahliah Barnett.

title: Throes of Joy in the Jaws of Defeatism
summary: The 16th full-length studio release for the British grindcore band was produced by Russ Russell.

title: Stone Rollin'
summary: The soul singer continues his 1960's-inspired music with a fourth album, blending vintage R&B sounds and smooth soul-pop.

title: What Does It All Mean? 1983-2006 Retrospective
summary: The two-disc set includes the 28-track "Nothing to Fear" on disc two.

title: Feast of Wire
summary: The Tucson, Arizona-based duo of Joey Burns and John Convertino return with their fourth full-length album.

title: The Futureheads
summary: This debut LP from the English band certainly recalls English bands from the early 80s, most notably XTC.

title: From All Purity
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Chicago doom metal band was produced by Sanford Parker.

title: Sick!
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for rapper Earl Sweatshirt features guest appearances from Armand Hammer and Zelooperz.

title: To the Sunset
summary: The sixth full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter was produced by Dave Cobb.

title: Locked Down
summary: The latest album for Mac Rebennack, the multiple Grammy-winning singer-songwriter from New Orleans, was produced by Dan Auerbach of the Black Keys.

title: The Earth Is Not A Cold Dead Place
summary: This five-song album is the second release from the Austin, Texas instrumental quartet known for their fierce live shows.

title: Soul of a Woman
summary: The final album for Sharon Jones (who passed away in 2016 from cancer) & The Dap-Kings was recorded on eight-track tape in Brooklyn.

title: Kitchen Sink
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was produced by Ben Hillier.

title: (After) [Live]
summary: The live recording of some of Phil Elverum's songs from A Crow Looked At Me and Now Only performed in a 13th century Gothic church during 2017's Le Guess Who? festival in the Netherlands.

title: DAYTONA
summary: The third full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from Rick Ross and Kanye West.

title: Phantom Thread [Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]
summary: The ninth soundtrack from the Radiohead guitarist is his fourth for a Paul Thomas Anderson film.

title: Present Tense
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the British four-piece was co-produced by Lexxx and Leo Abrahams.

title: Empros
summary: The fourth full-length album for the Chicago instrumental metal band was produced by Brandon Curtis of The Secret Machines.

title: I See The Sign
summary: The singer-songwriter worked with Nico Muhly on his album of traditional and untraditional songs reworked into folk music.

title: Harps And Angels
summary: The first studio album for the singer-songwriter since 1999's "Bad Love" was produced by Mitchell Froom and Lenny Waronker.

title: Fortress
summary: The sophomore album for the post-hardcore/metal band from Whitby, Ontario, Canada.

title: Chavez Ravine
summary: The guitarist's latest is a concept album about the residents of 1940's Chavez Ravine, a Mexican-American community near downtown Los Angeles that was famously bulldozed to make way for Dodger Stadium.

title: Boxer
summary: Sufjan Stevens is among the guests on the Brooklyn band's follow-up to their acclaimed 2005 release 'Alligator.'

title: Some Rap Songs
summary: The third full-length studio release for the Los Angeles-based rapper features guest appearances by Navy Blue and Standing On The Corner as well as vocal samples of his parents: Cheryl Harris and (the late) Keorapetse Kgositsile.

title: Reflection
summary: The second full-length release for the British electronic producer features guest appearance from Baths, Iceboy Violet, Le3 bLACK, Nova, Eden Samara, and Xzavier Stone.

title: Simple Songs
summary: This is the first solo release for the experimental artist since 2009's The Visitor.

title: Popular Problems
summary: The 13th studio release for the Hall of Fame singer-songwriter was co-written with Patrick Leonard, who also produced the album.

title: White Blood Cells
summary: The Detroit-based "brother-sister" (or, if you don't believe everything you read, ex husband and wife) indie duo of Jack (guitars) and Meg (drums) White continue their stripped-down sound on this, their third full-length.

title: In Time
summary: This is the first release in nearly ten years from the country rock band from Miami.

title: Ravedeath, 1972
summary: The latest release for the Montreal-based artist was recorded in a church in Iceland.

title: American Dream
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the rock band led by James Murphy is its first in five years (seven years for a studio album).

title: Cee-Lo Green Is The Soul Machine
summary: Like fellow Atlanta hip hoppers OutKast, Cee-Lo has trouble sticking to a single genre, as he mixes up styles throughout this sophomore release. Timbaland, The Neptunes and Ludacris guest.

title: The Lemon Of Pink
summary: The experimental collage artists combine samples, vocals (courtesy of Anne Doerner) and acoustic instrumentation on this second release.

title: The Wind
summary: Diagnosed with terminal lung cancer in 2002, veteran singer-songwriter Warren Zevon decided to record one final album. This 11-track effort includes contributions from numerous Zevon friends, including Ry Cooder, Bruce Springsteen, Jackson Browne, Don Henley, Tom Petty, and Dwight Yoakam.

title: All Hands On The Bad One
We Will Always Love You
summary: The third full-length release for the Australian electronic duo features guest appearances from such artist as Blood Orange, Leon Bridges, Vashti Bunyan, Neneh Cherry, Rivers Cuomo, Perry Farrell, Karen O, Jamie xx, Mick Jones, Sananda Maitreya (formerly known as Terence Trent D'Arby), Johnny Marr, MGMT, Oroño, Sampa the Great, Pink Siifu, Tricky, and Kurt Vile.

title: Far In
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for Roberto Carlos Lange under the name Helado Negro features guest appearances from Benamin, Buscabulla and Kacy Hill.

title: Punk
summary: This is the second full-length release for the Japanese quartet that includes Mana, Kana, Yuna and Yuki.

title: Acid Rap
summary: The second mixtape for the Chicago rapper features guest appearances from Action Bronson, Ab-Soul, BJ The Chicago Kid, and Childish Gambino.

title: All We Know of Heaven, All We Need of Hell
summary: The second full-length release for the Massachusetts alternative rock band led by Lynn Gunn was produced by Blake Harnage.

title: Surf
summary: The collaborative debut album from Chance The Rapper with Donnie Trumpet features Peter CottonTale, Nate Fox, and Greg Landfair, Jr., with guest appearances from Erykah Badu, Big Sean, Busta Rhymes, J. Cole, and Janelle Monae.

title: David Comes To Life
summary: The Toronto seven-piece release a four-act narrative album, as theatrical as it is musical.

title: Tell Tale Signs: The Bootleg Series Vol. 8
summary: The latest collection of unreleased and rare songs recorded between 1989 and 2006.

title: Lost In the Dream
summary: This is the third full-length release for the Philadelphia rock band led by Adam Granduciel.

title: Smiling With No Teeth
summary: The debut full-length release for the Ghanaian-born, Australia-based artist features folk, funk, pop, R&B and rap influences.

title: New Long Leg
summary: The debut full-length release for the British post-punk band was recorded in Wales with producer John Parish.

title: L'Enfant Sauvage
summary: The fifth album for the French metal band was co-produced with Josh Wilbur.

title: The Underside of Power
summary: The second full-length release for the quartet based in Atlanta was produced by Portishead's Adrian Utley and and Ali Chant.

title: Gold Record
summary: The seventh full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter was recorded with Matt Kinsey and Jamie Zurverza.

title: Happier than Ever
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Los Angeles pop singer-songwriter was produced by her brother, Finneas.

title: All at Once
summary: The seventh full-length release for the New Jersey punk trio was produced by Matt Bayles.

title: Nerissimo
summary: The second full-length release from the collaboration between Teho Teardo and Blixa Bargeld features English, German and Italian.

title: Way Out Weather
summary: The latest solo release for the Brooklyn-based singer-songwriter finds the guitarist backed by a larger group of musicians than 2013's Time Off.

title: Haw
summary: The fourth release for the band led by M.C. Taylor and Scott Hirsch, features contributions from such artists as The Black Twig Pickers’ Nathan Bowles, Megafaun’s Phil Cook, and William Tyler.

title: There is No Other
summary: The collaboration between the Carolina Chocolate Drops member with Francesco Turrisi was recorded over five days in Dublin and was produced by Joe Henry.

title: The Intercontinentals
summary: On his latest release, Bill Frisell takes an international approach to American folk music, assembling a cosmopolitan group of musicians that includes Malian vocalist/percussionist Sidiki Camara, Brazilian guitarist Vinicius Cantuaria, and Greece's Christos Govetas.

title: OST
