This is also the only album where you'll find the newest New Order single, "Here to Stay," a collaboration with the Chemical Brothers that failed to appear on either group's latest LP.

title: Ocean's Eleven OST
summary: Much as he did for another Steven Soderbergh film ("Out Of Sight"), David Holmes provides the score for Soderbergh's Rat Pack remake. Much of the album consists of Holmes originals (including "69 Police," which also appears on his 'Bow Down To The Exit Sign' LP), supplemented by songs from the likes of everyone from Handsome Boy Modeling School to Elvis Presley.

title: The Convincer
summary: The final installment in the 52-year-old Lowe's comback trilogy follows 1994's 'The Impossible Bird' and 1998's 'Dig My Mood.'

title: The  Weird and Wonderful
summary: The debut full-length release for the British alternative rock quintet formed by two set of siblings was produced by Larry Hibbitt.

title: untitled unmastered.
summary: The surprise release from the rapper features guest appearances from Bilal, Cee-Lo Green, Terrace Martin, Punch, Jay Rock, Thundercat and Anna Wise.

title: Poison Season
summary: The second full-length release for Dan Bejar's solo project was produced by John Collins.

title: When the Heart Emerges Glistening
summary: The second album for the jazz trumpeter from California was coproduced with Jason Moran.

title: The Mysterious Production Of Eggs
summary: You don't see many musicians described as a "whistler" but Chicago's Andrew Bird (who is also a singer-songwriter, guitarist, and originally, a violinist) fits the bill. This is his fifth release (and second for Ani DiFranco's record label), which finds him backed by several members of his group Bowl Of Fire.

title: Shaking the Habitual
summary: The fourth studio release for the Swedish electronic duo includes a 19-minute track.

title: BLACKsummers'night
summary: The first album for the singer since 2001's "Now" is part of a planned trilogy (the next two albums to be named BlackSUMMERS'night and Blacksummers'NIGHT).

title: Spiral Shadow
summary: The Savannah, Georgia, band's new album incorporates psychedelic experimentalism with heavy riffs and sludgy doom metal.

title: The Agent Intellect
summary: This is the third full-length release for the Detroit post-punk band.

title: Knock Knock
summary: The latest release for the German electronic artist features guest appearances from Eddie Fummler, José Gonzalez, Sophia Kennedy, Mano Le Tough, Róisín Murphy, Arrested Development's Speech, and Kurt Wagner.

title: Bedouine
summary: This is the debut full-length debut for Los Angeles-based artist Azniv Korkejian.

title: Pompeii
summary: The sixth full-length release for Welsh singer-songwriter Cate Le Bon was co-produced with Samur Khouja.

title: Rook
summary: The Austin-based band cofounded by Okkervil River's Jonathan Meiburg releases its fifth album.

title: Nick of Time
summary: The latest full-length release for the British R&B/soul artist was recorded and produced by Bosco Mann (aka as Daptone Records' Gabriel Roth) in California.

title: Badbea
summary: The ninth full-length release for the Scottish singer-songwriter was co-produced by Sean Read.

title: Stranger to Stranger
summary: The 13th full-length solo release for the folk rock singer-songwriter was produced by Andy Smith and Roy Halee.

title: Party Music
summary: Perhaps best known for being the album that depicted the World Trade Center towers in flames on its cover (before the events of September 11 necessitated a last-minute change of artwork), 'Party Music' is the fourth full-length for the ultra-political rappers.

title: Morbid Stuff
summary: The third full-length release for the Toronto punk band was recorded by Dave Schiffman and Darren McGill.

title: Life...The Best Game In Town
summary: This is the fifth album for the experimental rock band from Athens, Georgia.

title: Way Down in the Rust Bucket [Live]
summary: The latest archive release from the Canadian rock artist is the live recording from November 13, 1990 at a bar in Santa Cruz, California, where they played some songs from 1990's Ragged Glory for the first time live.

title: 50 Words for Snow
summary: Kate Bush's first new album in six years is influenced by snow and features Stephen Fry, Elton John , and Andy Fairweather Low as guest musicians.

title: Mermaid Avenue: The Complete Sessions
summary: Woody Guthrie's daughter Nora contacted Billy Bragg about using some of the songs her father wrote in the 1940s. Bragg in turn, recruited the band Wilco to help complete the project. The Complete Sessions collects the two previously released volumes with a new third volume of songs, and a documentary about the creating the music to go with the folk legend's lyrics.

title: Fox Confessor Brings The Flood
summary: Members of Calexico and Giant Sand help provide the music for the singer's first studio album in four years.

title: I'm Wide Awake, It's Morning
summary: 'I'm Wide Awake' is the more country/acoustic of Conor Oberst's twin January 2005 releases under the Bright Eyes name. Emmylou Harris provides vocals on three tracks.

title: Glass
summary: The latest collaboration between Ryuichi Sakamoto and Carsten Nicolai  was recorded at the Glass House in Connecticut in 2014.

title: Fires Within Fires
summary: The 11t full-length release for the Oakland-based post-metal was recorded by producer Steve Albini.

title: New Brigade
summary: This is the debut full-length album for the Danish punk rock band.

title: Silver Ladders
summary: The latest full-length release for the harpist was recorded over nine days with producer, Slowdive's Neil Halstead.

title: Malibu
summary: The second full-length release for the California rapper/singer-songwriter features guest appearances from BJ the Chicago Kid, The Free Nationals, The Game, Rapsody, Schoolboy Q, and the Timon Family Choir.

title: So Beautiful or So What
summary: The veteran singer-songwriter releases his 12th studio album, the first in five years.

title: Space 1.8
summary: The debut full-length release for London-based jazz/ambient artist features guest appearances from Nubya Garcia, Ahnansé and James Mollison.

title: Third
summary: The English rock band returns with its first studio album in 11 years.

title: Holopaw
summary: This Gainesville, Fla.-based five-piece band, which mixes indie rock and alt-country with a bit of electronica, features John Orth, who also appeared on the 2002 release by the Modest Mouse side project Ugly Casanova. Brian Deck produces.

title: Don't Give Up On Me
summary: The legendary 1960s soul singer, now a young 66 years old, is still going strong with this latest release, featuring brand-new songs penned by an impressive group of songwriters, including Elvis Costello, Brian Wilson, Tom Waits, Van Morrison, and Bob Dylan. No one will be giving up on him after this release.

title: Didn't It Rain
summary: With the word "blue" appearing in four out of the seven song titles, you get a general idea of Jason Molina's mood as he recorded this sixth proper LP under the Songs:Ohia name. The entire album was recorded live in a Philadelphia studio with Molina backed by a new full band, including co-vocalists Jennie Benford and Jim Krewson.

title: Daddy's Home
summary: The sixth full-length release for Annie Clark was inspired by her father's 1970s record collection and co-produced with Jack Antonoff.

title: The Overload
summary: The debut full-length release for the British band Yard Act was recorded with Ali Chant.

title: Girls Can Tell
summary: The Austin band's follow-up to 'Series of Sneaks' was a critical favorite in 2001, appearing on seemingly every year-end Top 10 list (and with good reason).

title: Late Registration
summary: The Grammy-winner returns with a highly-anticpated follow-up to 'The College Dropout,' marking the second installment in a planned four-part series of albums. Jon Brion co-produced, and Brandy, Common, Nas, The Game, Jamie Foxx and Maroon 5's Adam Levine guest.

title: Impossible Truth
summary: The second solo full-length release for the Nashville singer-songwriter was was produced by Mark Nevers.

title: Relatives in Descent
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Detroit post-punk band led by Joe Casey was produced with Sonny DiPerri and its first on the Domino label.

title: Stay Positive
summary: This is the fourth album for the Brooklyn, New York, indie rock quintet.

title: Iridescence
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Texan rap group was recorded in  Abbey Road Studios as well as Hawaii.

title: ZUU
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Florida rapper features guest appearances from Ice Billion Berg, Tay Keith, Kiddo Marv, PlayThatBoiZay, Rick Ross, and Sam Sneak.

title: Reality Show
summary: The third full-length studio release for the R&B singer feature a guest appearances from Meek Mill.

title: Bleach: Deluxe Edition
summary: The debut album for the grunge band is remastered and reissued with a 1990 live recording of a concert at Portland, Oregon's Pine Street Theatre.

title: All My Heroes Are Cornballs
summary: The third full-length studio release for the rapper from Baltimore was self-recorded and features guest appearances from Abdu Ali, Helena Deland and Buzzy Lee.

title: Sleep Well Beast
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the indie rock band was produced by band member Aaron Dessner with co-production by Bryce Dessner and Matt Berninger.

title: Geist
summary: The fourth full-length release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Sofia Arreguin, Ben Boye, Devin Hoff, Aaron Otheim, and Ty Segall.

title: Comfort To Me
summary: The second full-length release for the Australian punk band led by Amy Taylor was produced by Dan Luscombe.

title: Fire
summary: The latest full-length studio release for British electronic producer Kevin Martin as The Bug features guest appearances from Daddy Freddy, FFSYTHO, Flowdan, Irah, Logan_olm, Manga Saint Hilare, Moor Mother, Nazamba, and Roger Robinson.

title: Walk Through Fire
summary: Produced by Dan Auerbach, the debut full-length solo release for the British artist features influences from country, pop and soul music.

title: Christine and the Queens
summary: Chaleur Humaine, the 2014 French language release from the French synth-pop artist is reissued with songs redone in English and additional new songs featuring guest appearances from Tunji Ige and Perfume Genius.

title: Loyalty
summary: The third full-length release for the Canadian singer-songwriter Tamara Lindeman was recorded in France.

title: Murs 3:16 The 9th Edition
summary: The Los Angeles-based indie rapper's second Def Jux disc was produced by 9th Wonder.

title: Hail To The Thief
summary: Not quite the return to the "rock" side of Radiohead as originally believed (although pretty close), the band's sixth album (produced again by Nigel Godrich) retains some of the experimental electronica elements of its predecessors Kid A and Amnesiac. Note that each of the tracks on the album has an alternate title, as does the album itself (aka 'The Gloaming').

title: Magnolia Electric Co.
summary: Jason Molina rocks out a bit more on this latest offering, which finds the singer-songwriter backed by the same musicians on the 'Mi Sei Apparaso Come Un Fantasma' live album. Steve Albini produces, and to quote the official press release, "This is the first Songs: Ohia record with more than one song that could be played at a strip joint or monster truck show."

title: Pause
summary: The second Four Tet album from producer Kieran Hebden (who is also in the band Fridge), 'Pause' is a dense, eclectic collection of a variety of electronic and live instrumentation and found sounds.

title: I See You
summary: The third full-length release for the British indie pop trio was co-produced by Rodaidh McDonald and Jamie xx.

title: Ordinary Corrupt Human Love
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the San Francisco black metal band was produced by Jack Shirley

title: Laulu Laakson Kukista
summary: This is the latest album for the Finnish rock band.

title: Helplessness Blues
summary: The Seattle indie-folk outfit return with the harmonious follow-up to their debut.

title: Mezmerize
summary: Rick Rubin co-produced this first of two planned 2005 releases for SOAD (with 'Hypnotize' coming in the fall).

title: Purple
summary: The metal band returns from a tour bus accident in 2012 with a new lineup. Nick Jost and Sebastian Thomson take over for Allen Blickle and Matt Maggioni on the fourth studio release produced by David Fridmann.

title: Beauty And The Beat
summary: This self-produced second album for the Boston-based rapper includes guest appearances from Mr. Lif, Percee P, Dagah and Insight.

title: Aromanticism
summary: The debut full-length release for the Los Angeles-based artist features contributions from Animals as Leaders' Tosin Abasi, Miguel Atwood-Ferguson, Son Lux's Ian Chang, Ludwig Görannson, Joshua Willing Halpern, Hundred Waters' Nicole Miglis, Rob Moose, Cam Obi, Majical Cloudz's Matt Otto, KING's Paris Strother, and Thundercat.

title: Twin Cinema
summary: This is the third album of sunny indie-pop tunes for the acclaimed union of Neko Case, Dan Bejar (also of Destroyer) and A.C. Newman.

title: Benji
summary: The sixth full-length release for Mark Kozelek as Sun Kil Moon includes contributions from Owen Ashworth, Will Oldham, Sonic Youth's Steve Shelley, and Jen Wood.

title: For Hero: For Fool
summary: The anticon crew that includes Doseone--and, fortunately, the nearly-killed Dax Pierson--makes the jump to a more major label (EMI/Astralwerks) for the first time.

title: Juno
summary: The debut full-length for the Los Angeles-based pop artist was co-produced by Jared Soloman.

title: Bird Songs of a Killjoy
summary: The second full-length release for the Los Angeles-based folk singer-songwriter was produced by Gus Seyffert.

title: Interplanetary Class Classics
summary: The Village People's Randy Jones, Yoko Ono, Slow Club's Rebecca Taylor are some of the guests featured on the debut full-length release for the band first mentioned in Eccentronic Research Council's 2015 concept release that includes Fat White Family's Lias Saoudi and Saul Adamczewski as well as Eccentronic Research Council's Adrian Flanagan and Dean Honer.

title: Seasons of My Soul
summary: The debut release for British singer-songwriter was produced by  Steve Brown.

title: New Moon
summary: The twin-CD set 'New Moon' compiles two dozen rare tracks recorded by the late singer-songwriter from 1994-1997.

title: The Drift
summary: The legendary singer-songwriter and one-time teen idol re-emerges with his first album in 11 years. Anyone expecting conventional rock or pop should look elsewhere, however, as it is even more challenging than previous release 'Tilt.'

title: Pray for Haiti
summary: The latest full-length release for the rapper features guest appearances from  Melanie Charles, Keisha Plum, Tha God Fahim, and Westside Gunn.

title: Working Class Woman
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Canadian electronic producer features influences from Italo Disco and proto-industrial music.

title: Over and Even
summary: The third full-length release for the Kentucky singer-songwriter features guest appearance from Rachel Grimes and Will Oldham.

title: The  Budos Band III
summary: The third full-length album for the Staten Island group was recorded live during a 48 hour period.

title: Streetcore
summary: The former Clash leader was nearing completion of this fourth and final solo album when he died of a heart attack in 2002. It includes covers of Bob Marley's "Redemption Song" (recorded without his backing band the Mescaleros) and Bobby Charles' "Before I Grow Too Old," as well as eight Strummer originals veering from reggae to rock.

title: Happy Songs For Happy People
summary: Don't let the title fool you; the Glaswegian instrumental post-rockers are just as dour as ever on this fourth studio LP.

title: Source Tags & Codes
artist: ...And You Will Know Us by the Trail of Dead
summary: Following the critical success of their 1999 effort, 'Madonna,' the lengthily-named Austin, Texas indie band signed with Interscope and recorded this, their major-label debut.

title: Greatest Hits: The Evidence
summary: This 16-track best-of collection includes most of the original gangster's hits, including "I'm Your Pusher," "O.G.," and "Colors," as well as the previously unreleased "Money, Power, Women." However, the disc omits his work with Body Count.

title: Atrocity Exhibition
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Detroit rapper was produced by Paul White and features guest appearances from Ab-Soul, B-Real, Kelela, Kendrick Lamar, Petite Noir, and Earl Sweatshirt.

title: Semper Femina
summary: The sixth full-length release for the British folk singer-songwriter was produced by Blake Mills.

title: Hannah
summary: The second release for the Los Angeles-based singer-songwriter was recorded with her brother Tommy in their Texas hometown.

title: Transangelic Exodus
summary: The seventh full-length release for the singer-songwriter was produced by Tim Sandusky.

title: My Favorite Picture of You
summary: The latest release for the Texas singer-songwriter includes songs co-written with Shawn Camp, Rodney Crowell, Lyle Lovett, and Chris Stapleton.

title: Smother
summary: The British quartet releases its follow-up to its 2010 Mercury Prize-nominated album Two Dancers, produced by Richard Formby.

title: Have One On Me
summary: The three-disc follow-up to 2006's "Ys" was a mystery as advance copies were not sent until a few weeks before the release date to circumvent any leaks of the songs.

title: Seeking New Gods
summary: The seventh full-length solo release for the Super Furry Animals frontman  was inspired by Mount Paektu, an active volcano on the border of North Korea and China.

title: Good News
summary: The debut full-length release for the rapper features guest appearance from 2Chainz, Beyoncé, Big Sean, City Girls, Da Baby, Lil Durk, Popcaan, SZA,, and Young Thug.

title: Acoustic
summary: The latest full-length release for the Mali artist features acoustic versions of songs from her 2017 album, Mogoya.

title: Things Have Changed
summary: The soul singer's reinterpretations of Bob Dylan songs was produced by Steve Jordan and feature guest appearances from Keith Richards and Trombone Shorty.

title: Ba Power
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Malian afro-rock band that features the ngoni was produced by Chris Eckman.

title: De Vermis Mysteriis
summary: The concept album for the heavy metal band led by Matt Pike was produced by Kurt Ballou of Converge.

title: Oceans Apart
summary: This is the third album in three years for the newly-reunited Australian duo of Grant McLennan and Robert Forster.

title: Veckatimest
summary: The third album for the Brooklyn-based indie-rock band.

title: I'm All Ears
summary: The second full-length release for the British duo of Jenny Hollingworth and Rosa Walton features production from Faris Badwan, SOPHIE, and David Wrench.

title: Quarantine The Past
summary: With the band reunited and touring in 2010, here comes a 23-tracks greatest-hits compilation chosen by the band members.

title: Pink City
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Canadian singer-songwriter features contributions from Owen Pallett and Kath Bloom.

title: Devotion
summary: The singer who began her career as a guest on SBTRKT and Joker's singles releases her debut full-length album.

title: Bitte Orca
summary: The latest album for the Brooklyn-based indie band is its first on the Domino Records label.

title: Amadjar
summary: The ninth full-length release for the Malian Tuareg band features guest appearances from Rodolphe Burger, Jeiche Ould Chighaly, Warren Ellis, Cass McCombs, Michah Nelson, Stephen O'Malley, and Noura Mint Seymali.

title: Bubblegum
summary: The former Screaming Trees member and Queens Of The Stone Age collaborator returns with his sixth solo album, credited to the Mark Lanegan Band. Guests include Ween, PJ Harvey, Josh Homme, Nick Oliveri and Izzy Stradlin and Duff McKagan.

title: The Real New Fall L.P. (Formerly Country On The Click)
summary: Yes, as you may have surmised, this is the real new Fall full-length (just one in a very, very long line of releases from the amazingly prolific Mark E. Smith and company). Originally titled 'Country On The Click,' this album was leaked in early stages on the Internet, but has since been remixed and resequenced.

title: Tenacious D
summary: What started as a series of HBO shorts has turned into a full-fledged band, featuring actor Jack Black ("High Fidelity") and Kyle Gass. Dave Grohl (Foo Fighters) and Steve McDonald (Redd Kross) are among the guest musicians on this, the D's debut album, produced by the Dust Brothers.

title: Walking Proof
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Nashville singer-songwriter was produced by ex-Cage the Elephant guitarist Lincoln Parish.

title: American Kid
summary: Co-produced with Craig Ross, the mostly acoustic release for the singer-songwriter was inspired by her father, who passed away in 2009.

title: No Dream
summary: The surprise full-length release for the New York punk artist was produced by Jack Shirley.

title: Life Metal
summary: The Seattle drone metal specialists return with the first of two planned 2019 follow-ups to 2015's Kannon. This four-song set was produced by Steve Albini.

title: The Soft Bulletin
summary: The Dave Fridmann-produced 'Soft Bulletin' is considered by many fans and critics to be the band's finest album, and found its way onto quite a few Best of 1999 lists.

title: Journal For Plague Lovers
summary: The latest album for the Welsh rock band was produced by Steve Albini and features lyrics from Richey James Edwards, who went missing in 1995.

title: In Cauda Venenum
summary: The 13th full-length release for the Swedish progressive death metal group comes in both an English and Swedish versions.

title: King Push - Darkest Before Dawn: The Prelude
summary: The second full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from Ab-Liva, A$AP Rocky, Kehlani, Jill Scott, Beanie Sigel, The-Dream, and Kanye West.

title: The Weather Station
summary: The fourth full-length release for Canadian singer-songwriter Tamara Lindeman was self-produced.

title: Muchacho
summary: The sixth release for Matthew Houck as Phosphorescent was written in Brooklyn and Mexico after his 18-month tour for 2010's Here's To Taking It Easy.

title: I Am Not Afraid Of You And I Will Beat Your Ass
summary: After two relatively subdued albums, Ira, Georgia and James return with a much more varied effort that at times recalls pretty much every stage of their history. Roger Moutenot again produces.

title: Clara
summary: The latest full-length release for the Canadian electronic/ambient project of Scott Morgan was inspired by a three-minute composition from a 22-piece hungarian string orchestra.

title: Wrongdoers
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the metalcore band led by Chris Day and Cory Brandan is its first with three new members: John Finnegan, Jeff Hickey, and Clayton Holyoak (replacing Jake Schultz, Scottie H. Henry, and Chris Raines/Matt Marquez).

title: Chemistry Of Common Life
summary: The second full-length album for the Canadian hard-rock band.

title: Goodness
summary: The third full-length release for the Massachusetts indie rock band was produced by Seth Manchester.

title: Crimes
summary: The fourth album for the abrasive, Seattle-based punk-rockers was produced by John Goodmanson (Blonde Redhead).

title: The Airing Of Grievances
summary: The debut full-length album from the New Jersey punk-rock sextet.

title: Patience
summary: The third full-length release for the Philadelphia-based punk rock band led by Marisa Dabice was produced by Will Yip.

title: Blinking Lights And Other Revelations
summary: Mark Everett's diverse and epic sixth Eels album spans two CDs. It probably would never be classified as a happy album, but it does include appearances from Tom Waits, R.E.M.'s Peter Buck, and The Lovin' Spoonful's John Sebastian.

title: Vertikal
summary: The sixth full-length release from the Swedish metal band was inspired by Fritz Lang's film, Metropolis.

title: Old Ideas
summary: The first new album from the Canadian singer-songwriter in eight years includes production work by Patrick Leonard, Ed Sanders, Dino Soldo, and Anjani Thomas.

title: Left Of The Dial: Dispatches From The '80s Underground
summary: This 82-song, 4-disc box set compiles various indie and alternative tracks from the 1980s across multiple genres, and includes music from both the decade's "biggest" names (The Smiths, R.E.M., Depeche Mode, Violent Femmes, etc.) as well as lesser-known artists such as The Raincoats, Green On Red, and The Lyres.

title: Run To Ruin
summary: Recorded by Steve Albini, 'Run To Ruin' is the New York singer-songwriter's third LP. The Dirty Three's Jim White chips in on drums.

title: The Meadowlands
summary: The indie rockers took four years to record this third album.

title: Celebration Day [Live]
summary: The 2007 concert at London's O2 in honor of Atlantic Records founder Ahmet Ertegun featured the remaining original members of the British blues rock band along with Jason Bonham, son of the late John Bonham, on drums, as they performed together for the first time in over 30 years is finally released five years later.

title: Boys And Girls In America
summary: The Brooklyn-based rockers move to emo label Vagrant for this John Agnello-produced release.

title: Elaenia
summary: The debut full-length release for electronic producer Sam Shepherd features a wide variety of influences including Brazilian classical, jazz, and soul music.

title: Hell-On
summary: The latest full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Eric Bachmann, Joey Burns, Beth Ditto, Doug Gillard, Kelly Hogan, Mark Lanegan, k.d. Lang, AC Newman, and Laura Veirs, was self-produced with co-production on six tracks with Bjorn Yttling of Peter Bjorn & John.

title: Pure Comedy
summary: The third full-length release for the singer-songwriter Josh Tillman as father John Misty was produced with Jonathan Wilson.

title: Two Hands
summary: The second release in 2019 for the Brooklyn folk-influenced rock band led by Adrianne Lenker was recorded live.

title: Big Inner
summary: The music of the 1970s influences the debut release for the Richmond, Virginia-based singer-songwriter.

title: Ys
summary: Steve Albini, Jim O'Rourke and Van Dyke Parks lend a hand on this five-song full-length from the folk singer-songwriter.

title: Coral Island
summary: The 24-track release from the British indie rock band features Ian and James Skelly's grandfather Ian Murray as narrator.

title: Ode
summary: The first studio release with the new jazz trio line-up of Mehldau, bassist Larry Grenadier, and drummer Jeff Ballard is an album of tributes to both real and fictional people.

title: Home Video
summary: The third full-length release for the indie singer-songwriter features contributions from Julien Baker and Phoebe Bridgers.

title: The Moon and Stars: Prescriptions for Dreamers
summary: The latest full-length release for the Memphis singer-songwriter features a guest appearance from Carla Thomas and was produced with Jack Splash.

title: Kish Kash
summary: The third album for the house duo of Simon Ratcliffe and Felix Buxton features contributions from Dizzee Rascal, Me'Shell NdegeOcello, JC Chasez and Siouxsie Sioux.

title: Interstate Gospel
summary: The third full-length release for the country trio of Miranda Lambert, Ashley Monroe and Angaleena Presley was produced by Frank Liddell.

title: Gave in Rest
summary: The second release in 2018 for the Canadian artist was inspired by her European tour and features contributions from Thierry Amar, Terri Hron, Lisa McGee, and Jessica Moss.

title: Revolution
summary: This is the third album for the country singer who was a finalist on Nashville Star.

title: Enter The Vaselines
summary: The two-disc set for the Scottish indie-rock band includes the reissues of two EPs, an LP, several demos, and live tracks recorded in the late 1980s.

title: The Impossible Kid
summary: The seventh full-length solo studio release for the indie rap artist was self-produced.

title: Landfall
summary: Hurricane Sandy is the subject of the debut collaboration album from Laurie Anderson and the Kronos Quartet.

title: Tomorrow's Harvest
summary: This is the first full-length release in eight years for the Scottish electronic duo of Marcus Eoin and Mike Sandison.

title: Architect
summary: This is the debut release for the Scottish composer features influences from classical and pop music.

title: Strange Mercy
summary: St. Vincent, otherwise known as Annie Clark, releases her third album, produced by John Congleton.

title: Winter Wheat
summary: The second solo release for the ex-Weakerthans frontman includes contributions from his wife, Christine Fellows, as well as his former bandmates Greg Smith and Jason Tait.

title: Loom
summary: The second full-length release for the experimental artist was influenced by her mother's cancer diagnosis and eventual passing in 2018.

title: Ecstatic Arrow
summary: The third full-length release for the British duo of Alice Richards and Samuel Pillay was recorded in Switzerland.

title: Crazy Ex-Girlfriend
summary: This sophomore effort finds the former "Nashville Star" contestant becoming a bona-fide star (albeit from Texas rather than Tennessee). It combines eight Lambert originals with three covers.

title: Astroworld
summary: The third solo release for the rapper features guest appearances and contributions from such artist as 21 Savage, James Blake, Drake, John Mayer, Frank Ocean, Pharrell, Quavo, Swae Lee, Tame Imapala, Sevn Thomas, Thundercat, and The Weeknd.

title: Montero
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from Miley Cyrus, Doja Cat, Jack Harlow, Elton John, and Megan Thee Stallion.

title: New Bermuda
summary: The third full-length studio release for the California black metal band was produced by Jack Shirley.

title: I Don't Live Here Anymore
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Philadelphia rock band led by Adam Granduciel is its first in four years.

title: async
summary: The first solo release for the Grammy-winning Japanese synth pop composer in eight years features David Sylvian on one track.

title: Bonxie
summary: The third full length release for the British folk-pop band was produced by Gil Norton.

title: The  Harrow and the Harvest
summary: Eight years after her last release, the country-folk singer releases new material.

title: One Beat
summary: The acclaimed indie-rock trio from Olympia, Wash. return with their sixth album.

title: High Violet
summary: The band and Peter Katis produced the Brooklyn-based rock quintet's fifth full-length album.

title: Miss Universe
summary: The debut full-length release for the London-based singer-songwriter features co-production from Will Archer, Oli Barton-Wood, Jazzi Bobbi, Luke Bower, John Congleton, M.T. Hadley, and the Invisible's Dave Okumu.

title: This Right Here Is Buck 65
summary: This right here is the American debut for the Canadian country-rapper (born Richard Terfry), who has actually been recording north of the border since the mid-1990s. Apparently he's worth $1.15 more than 50 Cent, although we're not sure if that's in Canadian dollars or not.

title: Bloom
summary: The second full-length release for the Australian pop singer-songwriter features guest appearances from Ariana Grande and Gordi.

title: The Singles
summary: Two new songs are included on this collection of some of Goldfrapp's biggest singles.

title: Beyoncé
summary: The fifth full-length record for the R&B pop singer was a surprise iTunes release, with a short film accompanying each track.

title: Cole's Corner
summary: This is the fourth solo album for the sometime Pulp guitarist.

title: Still Over It
summary: The second full-length release for the Atlanta R&B artist features guest appearances from Cardi B, Ciara, JT, Ari Lennox, Lil Durk, Omarion, and Pharrell Williams.

title: And Then Life Was Beautiful
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British artist features guest appearances from Adekunle Gold, Lucky Daye, Lianne La Havas, and serpentwithfeet.

title: Clearing the Path to Ascend
summary: This is the seventh studio release for the Oregon doom metal trio of Mike Scheidt, Aaron Rieseburg, and Travis Foster .

title: Emeritus
summary: The ninth album for the Texas-born rapper features guest appearances from Bilal, Bun B, Lil Wayne, J. Prince, Papa Rue, Slim Thug, and Z-Ro.

title: evermore
summary: The second surprise release from the singer-songwriter in 2020 features contributions from Jack Antonoff, Aaron Dessner, Haim, Marcus Mumford, The National, Justin Vernon, and William Bowery (aka Joe Alwyn).

title: Lookaftering
summary: Coming a full 35 years after her debut ('Just Another Diamond Day'), the British folk singer's second LP finds her backed by fans/followers such as Devendra Banhart and Joanna Newsom.

title: R.A.P. Music
summary: The sixth album for Atlanta rapper Killer Mike was produced by El-P and includes guest appearances from Bun B, T.I., Scar, Emily Panic, and Trouble.

title: On the Line
summary: The fourth full-length release for the singer-songwriter/actress features contributions from Ryan Adams, Beck, Jim Keltner, Ringo Starr, Benmont Tench, and Don Was.

title: Pageant
summary: The second full-length release for the pop-punk duo of Liv Bruce and Ben Hopkinsfeatures horns and contributions from Kiley Lotz of Petal, Alex and Noah from Diet Cig, as well as Ben's mother.

title: This Is Our Science
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Minneapolis-based hip-hop artist was produced by John Congleton and features Tegan Quin as a guest vocalist.

title: Levon Vincent
summary: The Berlin-based electronic artist released his debut full-length release for free online the day before its official date.

title: Before Today
summary: Los Angeles-based Ariel Pink releases his first album on the 4AD label.

title: Amo
summary: The sixth full-length release for the British rock/metalcore band was produced by the band's own Oli Sykes and Jordan Fish.

title: Wind's Poem
summary: The fourth full-length album for the Washington state-based artist Phil Elverum.

title: Singing Bones
summary: The husband and wife duo of Brett and Rennie Sparks return with their sixth CD of dark, country-tinged folk-rock.

title: Fever To Tell
summary: This is the highly-anticipated debut LP for the New York art-punk trio, who have developed a fanbase and generated a great deal of publicity (not to mention a major-label deal) through a series of EPs and live performances.

title: The Ugly Organ
summary: A bit of a concept album (set as a play about sex and relationships), 'The Ugly Organ' is the Nebraska band's fourth LP, following 2000's acclaimed 'Domestica.'

title: The Last Broadcast
summary: The Manchester, England band reunites with producer Steve Osborne for their sophomore album, following 2000's 'Lost Souls,' which launched them into stardom in both the U.S. and U.K. "There Goes the Fear" is the lead single.

title: Ocean Roar
summary: The second release in 2012 from Phil Elverum as Mount Eerie is part of a two-album concept begun on Clear Moon.

title: Crushing
summary: The second full-length release for the Australian singer-songwriter was produced by Burke Reid.

title: The Path of the Clouds
summary: The latest full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter was inspired from watching Unsolved Mysteries episodes during the pandemic lockdown and features contributions from Jesse Chandler, Simon Raymonde, Emma Ruth Rundle, and Amber Webber.

title: Kaputt
summary: Canadian pop craftsman Daniel Bejar's ninth album combines the glam of David Bowie and the rock and roll of T. Rex into a retro dance soundtrack for disco fans.

title: Yonder Is The Clock
summary: The second album on the Team Love label for the three brothers from upstate New York.

title: Any Human Friend
summary: The third full-length release for the London-based singer-songwriter was produced by Hackman and David Wrench.

title: Beautiful Thugger Girls
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the rapper features guiest appearances from Future, Gunna, Jacquees, Lil Durk, Millie Go Lightly, and Snoop Dogg.

title: Geogaddi
summary: The Scottish duo finally return with a full-length follow-up to their acclaimed 1998 debut, 'Music Has A Right To Children.'

title: Mental Illness
summary: The singer-songwriter takes on her reputation for acoustic, depressing and dark songs with her ninth full-length studio release produced by Paul Bryan.

title: Hearts Of Oak
summary: Ted Leo, formerly of Chisel, returns with his fourth album of punk-influenced singer-songwriter indie-folk rock.

title: Yellow
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the British jazz composer/multi-instrumentalist/producer.

title: Treasure of Love
summary: The first full-length studio release in 12 years for the Texas trio that includes Joe Ely, Jimmie Dale Gilmore, and Butch Hancock was produced by Lloyd Maines.

title: The Age of Immunology
summary: This is the second full-length release for the London-based experimental psychedelic pop project led by Cathy Lucas.

title: A Hero's Death
summary: The second full-length release for the Dublin post-punk band was recorded in Los Angeles by producer Dan Carey.

title: It Won't Be Like This All the Time
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Scottish indie rock quintet was produced by band's guitarist, Andy MacFarlane.

title: Post Self
summary: This is the second full-length release since the industrial/post-punk duo of Justin Broadrick and G.C. Green reunited after disbanding in 2002.

title: Little Oblivions
summary: The third full-length release for the singer-songwriter was recorded in Memphis by Calvin Lauber and mixed by Craig Silvey.

title: Fantasy Empire
summary: The sixth full-length release for the Rhode Island noise rock band is its first album recorded in a proper studio.

title: Tomorrow Is My Turn
summary: The debut solo release for the Carolina Chocolate Drops co-founder was produced by T Bone Burnett.

title: Bow Down To The Exit Sign
summary: Former British club DJ David Holmes has been building a name for himself as a composer of soundtracks both real (Steven Soderbergh's "Out of Sight") and imaginary (the previous Holmes albums 'Let's Get Killed' and 'This Film's Crap, Let's Slash The Seats). 'Bow Down' continues that tradition by forming the soundtrack to an as-yet-unproduced screenplay, although it is clearly more song-oriented than its predecessors. Jon Spencer, Bobby Gillespie (Primal Scream), and Martina Topley-Bird (best known for her work on Tricky's albums) are among the guest vocalists.

title: Voices
summary: The latest project for the composer features readings of the  UN Declaration read by Kiki Layne (plus 70+ other languages/voices) and the 1949 recording of the preamble to the declaration by Eleanor Roosevelt.

title: And Nothing Hurt
summary: The eighth full-length release is the first in six years for Jason Pierce may be his last as Spiritualized.

title: As Days Get Dark
summary: This is the first new full-length release in over 15 years from the Scottish indie rock duo of Aidan Moffat and Malcolm Middleton.

title: From Dreams to Dust
summary: The latest full-length release for the folk rock band was recorded at a one-room church and was mixed by Mike Mogis.

title: Warm
summary: The second full-length solo release for the Wilco frontman was self-produced and recorded.

title: A Pocket of Wind Resistance
summary: The Scottish singer-songwriter adapted her and Pippa Murphy's Wind Resistance stage show into an album.

title: Indestructible Machine
summary: The Columbus, Ohio, singer releases her debut album of country punk rock music.

title: Meshes of Voice
summary: The collaboration between Jenny Hval and Susanna Wallumrød was inspired by Maya Deren's 1943 surrealist film, Meshes of the Afternoon and was originally written for Ladyfest in 2009.

title: Cool Dry Place
summary: The debut full-length release for the Nashville-based singer-songwriter from Texas was produced by Alberto Sewald and Logan Chung.

title: Singing Saw
summary: The third full-length solo release for the former Woods bass player was produced by Sam Cohen.

title: Light Up Gold
summary: This is the debut full-length release on What's Your Rupture? for the Brooklyn-based rock quartet from Texas.

title: 1991 [EP]
summary: The debut four-track EP for the New York rapper includes dance elements.

title: Electric Dirt
summary: Larry Campbell produces the follow-up to Levon Helm's Grammy-winning album, Dirt Farmer.

title: Course in Fable
summary: The latest release for the New York-based singer-songwriter was produced by Tortoise's John McEntire and features contributions from Bill MacKay, Nancy Ives, Douglas Jenkins, Ryan Jewell, and Andrew Scott Young.

title: Serena-Maneesh
summary: This debut album from the Norwegian shoegaze six-piece marks the inaugural release by the new record label from UK website Playlouder. Sufjan Stevens guests.

title: Flower Boy
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from ASAP Rocky, Anna of the North, Estelle, Steve Lacy, Lil Wayne, Frank Ocean, Rex Orange County, Jaden Smith, and Kali Uchis.

title: Before the Dawn [Live]
summary: The second live release for the British singer-songwriter is a three-disc album featuring songs from her her month-long residency at London's Hammersmith Apollo.

title: The Art of Losing
summary: The second full-length release for the Welsh singer-songwriter  Catherine Anne Davies features a guest appearances from James Dean Bradfield.

title: My Echo
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter was produced by her ex-husband Tucker Martine and features contributions from Karl Blau, Bill Frisell, Jim James, and Matt Ward.

title: The Great Pretenders
summary: The second release for the Californian trio of Michael Shuman, Zach Dawes and Tyler Parkford features guest appearances from Brian Wilson and Alex Turner.

title: A World Lit Only by Fire
summary: This is the first release in 13 years from the British industrial metal band led by Justin Broadrick.

title: The Way I'm Livin'
summary: The seventh studio release for the award-winning country singer was produced by her husband, Frank Liddell.

title: Love's Crushing Diamond
summary: The debut full-length release for solo project for Brooklyn-based  Jordan Lee was recorded while the singer-songwriter toured across the US.

title: Emily's D+Evolution
summary: The fifth full-length solo release for the multiple Grammy-winning artist is a concept album built around her muse named Emily (which is also her middle name) and was produced with Tony Visconti.

title: Medulla
summary: What the Icelandic singer's fifth album lacks in instrumentation (although there is a bit, provided by members of Matmos, Mum, and other collaborators), it makes up for with voices--lots and lots of voices. Think everything from beatboxing (including contributions from The Roots' Rahzel), choirs and Inuit throat-singing to, well, Mike Patton.

title: Blue Cathedral
summary: The psychedelic indie-rockers from Santa Cruz, Calif. make their Sub Pop debut with this third disc. Guitarist Ben Chasny has been added to the lineup, supplementing the original quartet led by vocalist/guitarist Ethan Miller.

title: Old Ramon
summary: Stuck in label limbo since 1997, 'Old Ramon' finally sees the light of day, thanks to Sub Pop records. It is the first official RHP release since 1996's 'Songs For A Blue Guitar,' although frontman Mark Kozelek released the solo album 'What's Next to the Moon' and appeared in the film "Almost Famous" in the interim.

title: Mwng
summary: The Furries return with an entire album of Welsh-language songs.

title: Play
summary: Although techno artist Moby had been on the scene for almost a decade and had released five albums, his fame had chiefly been limited to his club hit "Go" back in 1991. 'Play' changed all that, however, garnering a sea of critical and popular acclaim for the artist. A mix of styles (including deviations into blues and gospel), 'Play' also has the unique distinction of having all 18 of its tracks licensed for use in film, television and advertising.

title: Anicca
summary: The third full-length studio release for producer Mtendere Mandowa as Teebs features contributions from Ringgo Ancheta (aka MNDSGN), Daydream Masi, Michael Lundy, Panda Bear, Pink Siifu, Jimetta Rose, Thomas Stankiewicz, Sudan Archives, and Anna Wise.

title: Apollo Kids
summary: The Wu-Tang member branches out with his own brand of street flow on his solo album of soul-heavy funk sounds and old-school hip-hop.

title: Cancer4Cure
summary: The third solo album for producer El-P features guest appearances by  Danny Brown, Interpol’s Paul Banks, Islands' Nick Diamonds, and Killer Mike.

title: Fever Dreams
summary: The latest full-length release for the Irish folk band led by Conor O’Brien was mixed by David Wrench.

title: Rare, Forever
summary: This is the second full-length studio release for the British DJ and experimental electronic producer.

title: Forgotten Days
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Arkansas doom metal band was recorded in Texas and was produced by Randall Dunn.

title: Mama, You Can Bet!
summary: The third full-length release for Georgia Anne Muldrow under the name Jyoti features a guest appearance from Lakeica Benjamin.

title: Eton Alive
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the British duo of Jason Williamson and Andrew Fearn is the first album on their own label.

title: Mazy Fly
summary: This is the second full-length release for California-based Tia Cabral.

title: The Curious Hand
summary: The second full-length release for the Irish singer-songwriter was produced with Leo Abrahams.

title: It
summary: The final solo release from the Suicide frontman before his death in July 2016 was recorded over six years with his wife, Liz Lamere.

title: Lovers
summary: The instrumental jazz double-album from the Wilco guitarist features an ensemble of 23 musicians conducted by Michael Leonhart and was produced by David Breskin.

title: Divided & United: Songs of the Civil War
summary: Randall Poster produced the two-disc set that includes artists such as Loretta Lynn, Vince Gill, Joe Henry, Del McCoury, Carolina Chocolate Drops, Old Crow Medicine Show, Dolly Parton, Pokey Lafarge, Shovels & Rope, Chris Thile, and Lee Ann Womack interpreting Civil War songs.

title: Sister Faith
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Kentucky noise-rock trio was produced by J. Robbins.

title: This Is Happening
summary: The third album for the dance-rock band is reportedly James Murphy's last as LCD Soundsystem.

title: Snares Like a Haircut
summary: The fourth full-length release for the duo of Randy Randall and Dean Allen Spunt is its first on the Drag City label.

title: Donuts
summary: Acclaimed hip-hop producer James Yancey released this instrumental disc shortly before his death at the age of 32.

title: No Holiday
summary: This is the first new release in five years from the Los Angeles punk rock band led by Kim Shattuck (who passed away on 2 Oct 2019).

title: The Hex
summary: The posthumous release for the singer-songwriter/producer was recorded over several years before it was completed a month before his death in July.

title: Black Metal 2
summary: This is the sequel to the British artist's 2014 solo album, Black Metal.

title: A Celebration of Endings
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the the Scottish alternative rock trio was produced by Rich Costey.

title: Giants of All Sizes
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the British rock band features contributions from Chilli Chilton, Jesca Hoop and The Plumedores.

title: The Imperial
summary: The second full-length release for the Portland, Oregon-based country soul band that includes members of Richmond Fontaine was produced by John Morgan Askew.

title: Etch And Etch Deep
summary: This is the second full-length release for the British trio of Louise Croft, Gemma and Sophie Bakerwood.

title: No!
summary: This enhanced-CD experience is TMBG's first official album geared toward the younger set, with 17 children's songs with titles such as "Where Do They Make Balloons?" and "I Am Not a Grocery Bag." (Not that the titles themselves make this any different than a grownup TMBG album, mind you.)

title: Treats
summary: The electro-rock Brooklyn-based duo releases its debut album with Mom + Pop and M.I.A.'s N.E.E.T. Recordings.

title: Blue Hearts
summary: The 14th full-length solo studio release for the former Hüsker Dü frontman was recorded at Chicago's Electrical Audio.

title: Constant Bop
summary: The debut full-length solo release for White Denim frontman James Petralli features contributions from his bandmates and ex-Shearwater bassist Kevin Schneider.

title: Kids See Ghosts
summary: The debut surprise studio release for the collaboration between Kanye West and Kid Cudi features contributions from André 3000, Mos Def, Ty Dolla $ign as well as samples from Kurt Cobain's "Burn the Rain" and Louis Prima's "What Would Santa Claus Do?".

title: Our Endless Numbered Days
summary: Miami, Fla. singer-songwriter Sam Beam (who moonlights as a cinematography professor) returns with his second album, recorded with Brian Deck (Modest Mouse, Red Red Meat) at the helm.

title: The Evening Of My Best Day
summary: 'Evening' represents Jones' first album of self-penned material in six years. The roster of guests includes Nels Cline, David Hidalgo, Grant Lee Phillips and Bill Frisell.
The fifth release from the Chicago-based outfit continue their foray into "modern classical" composition using acoustic instruments.

title: Indestructible
summary: The Bay Area punk band returns with its first album in three years.

title: Silver Lake
summary: The unique singer-songwriter's 11th LP was produced by Mark Howard (Lucinda Williams).

title: S.T.R.E.E.T. D.A.D.
summary: Founded in 1996 in San Francisco, this now New York-based instrumental outfit (which shares some members with the band !!!) has previously drawn a bit of acclaim for their vinyl-only releases. This six-track effort represents their first CD release, which showcases their dancier, dubbier, funkier brand of post-rock.

title: Trouble Will Find Me
summary: The sixth studio release for the Brooklyn indie rock quintet features guest appearances from Annie Clark of St. Vincent, Richard Reed Parry of Arcade Fire, Sufjan Stevens, and Sharon Van Ette.

title: Full Circle
summary: The first release in a dozen years for the country artist features guest appearances by Elvis Costello and Willie Nelson and was produced by John Carter Cash and her daughter, Patsy Lynn Russell.

title: Mr. Misunderstood
summary: The fifth full-length album for the country singer was recorded in a month and was a surprise release first to his fan club then to iTunes.

title: The World Has Made Me The Man Of My Dreams
summary: The seventh album for the German-born singer features Pat Metheny, Jason Lindner, and Robert Glasper.

title: Ocean's Twelve OST
summary: The British DJ and composer one again provides the score for Steven Soderbergh's caper flick, as he did for Ocean's Eleven.

title: The Practice of Love
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Norwegian avant-garde artist features guest appearances from Félicia Atkinson, Laura Jean and Vivian Wang.

title: Let Them Eat Chaos
summary: The follow-up to the British artist's Mercury Prize-nominated release was produced by Dan Carey.

title: Stage Four
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Los Angeles-based post-hardcore band led by Jeremy Bolm was influenced by the death of Bolm's mother from cancer and produced by Brad Wood.

title: Ire Works
summary: The New Jersey hardcore rock band's third album is their first without drummer Chris Pennie.

title: Mood Valiant
summary: The third full-length release for the Australian quartet led by Nai Palm features a guest appearance from Arthur Verocai.

title: Dust
summary: The third full-length release for the Berlin-based American electronic artist features vocals from Klein, Lafawndah and Michael Salu as well as contributions from $hit and $hine’s Craig Clouse, Maximillion Dunbar, Julia Holter, and Eli Keszler.

title: Forward Constant Motion
summary: The second full-length release for the British duo of Merida Richards and Sam Pilla Virginia Wing was produced by Misha Hering.

title: Cardinal
summary: The debut full-length release on the Run For Cover Label for the New Jersey indie rock band features two songs from its 2014 compilation, Everything So Far.

title: Sulphur English
summary: The Richmond, Virginia metal band's fourth album was produced by Mikey Allred.

title: No Shape
summary: The fourth full-length release for the indie singer-songwriter was produced by Blake Mills and features a guest appearance from Weyes Blood.

title: Hell On Heels
summary: This is the debut album from the Miranda Lambert-led country trio that includes Angaleena Presley and Ashley Monroe.

title: Lost And Safe
summary: The third release for the acclaimed cut-and-paste outfit features an expanded vocal role for guitarist Nick Zammuto.

title: Excavation
summary: Bobby Krlic's second full-length release as The Haxan Cloak was influenced by electronic music.

title: The Book Of Traps and Lessons
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British spoken-word poet was co-produced by Rick Rubin and Dan Carey.

title: Sugar Mountain: Live At Canterbury House 1968
summary: Released as part of the Archive series of rare recordings of concerts from the early days of his career, this album includes songs recorded from a gig in Ann Arbor, Michigan, on November 9-10, just before the release of his debut solo album.

title: Room for the Moon
summary: The solo project for the Moscow artist features songs in Russian, English, French and Japanese.

title: Mutable Set
summary: The fourth full-length release for the California songwriter/producer features songs co-written with Cass McCombs.

title: Dolphine
summary: The fifth full-length release for the singer-songwriter Erin Birgy features contributions from members of such band as Big Thief, Hand Habits and Iji.

title: MITH
summary: The third full-length release for the Alabama-born sculptor-turned-singer features contributions from Sam Gendel, Laraaji, Nelson Patton, and Richard Swift.

title: Fall Be Kind [EP]
summary: The five-track EP is the second release for the year for the rock trio.

title: ONoffON
summary: This 16-track disc (complete with a brief intermission between 'sets') marks the first studio recording in a whopping 22 years for the Boston-based trio of Roger Miller (guitar, vocals), Clint Conley (bass, vocals) and Peter Prescott (drums, vocals), with production by Bob Weston and Rick Harte and additional instrumentation on two tracks by the band Rachel's.
'2' is the aptly-named second album for the Portland-based indie-pop quartet.

title: Veni Vidi Vicious
summary: One of the first Next Big Things of 2002, Sweden's The Hives follow last year's media darlings The Strokes and The White Stripes in bringing the rock back to alternative rock. The only catch is that the band has been around for over a decade, with this particular album actually dating back to 2000, when it gained a limited U.S. release on a tiny Epitaph imprint. However, the Swedes were able to benefit from the rush to capitalize on the neo-garage/punk-rock movement by scoring a major label deal in early 2002 and a rerelease of this, their second full-length. (They've got The Strokes beat on length, though, managing to release an even shorter album, at just 27 minutes.)

title: Gimme Fiction
summary: Mike McCarthy returns as producer for the Britt Daniel-led band's varied follow-up to their acclaimed 2002 outing 'Kill The Moonlight.' Spoon fans will not be disappointed.

title: Blood Bitch
summary: The latest release for the Norwegian artist was co-produced with Lasse Marhaug and features a blood theme.

title: Feels
summary: Electric where the mellower 'Sung Tongs' was acoustic, 'Feels' is nevertheless another idiosyncratic outing for the freak-folk four-piece.

title: Down to Believing
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter was influenced by her break up with Steve Earle and the autism diagnosis for her son Henry.

title: It Is What It Is
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Los Angeles-based artist features guest appearances from and Steve Arrington, Childish Gambino, Louis Cole, Zack Fox, Steve Lacy, Lil B, and Ty Dolla $ign.

title: Black Cadillac
summary: The singer-songwriter reflects on the recent deaths of her father, mother and stepmother with this 12-song set.

title: Western Stars
summary: The first new solo studio release in five years for the rock artist features contributions from Ron Aniello (who also produced), Jon Brion, Charlie Giordano, David Sancious,  Patti Scialfa, and Soozie Tyrell.

title: Yeezus
summary: Chief Keef, Daft Punk, Frank Ocean, Kid Cudi, King L, Rick Rubin, RZA, and Justin Vernon are some of the producers and artists the rapper worked with on his sixth solo release influenced by such genres as industrial, new wave, and Chicago house music.

title: Bird Songs
summary: The Grammy-award winning saxophonist's latest album is a collection of Charlie "Bird" Parker songs recorded with Lovano's band, the Us Five.

title: Last Man Standing
summary: The latest full-length studio release for the legendary country singer-songwriter features 11 new songs co-written with producer Buddy Cannon.

title: Wildheart
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles R&B singer-songwriter features guest appearances from Lenny Kravitz and Kurupt.

title: Body
summary: The 20th full-length release for the Australian trio of Chris Abrahams, Lloyd Swanton, and Tony Buck consists of a single nearly 57-minute-long piece.

title: RE-ANIMATOR
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the British art pop/rock band was produced by John Congleton.

title: Countless Branches
summary: The latest full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was produced by Joshua Henry.

title: Ephorize
summary: The third full-length release for the Chicago rapper was produced by Def Starz and Turreekk.

title: Ten [Reissue]
summary: The rerelease of the debut album for the grunge band is the part of a planned rerelease of the rest of its albums, leading up to its 20th anniversary in 2011.

title: Ga Ga Ga Ga Ga
summary: The Austin band serves up their latest album hoping fans go ga ga over it.

title: Hope Downs
summary: The debut full-length release for the Australian indie rock quintet was co-produced with Liam Judson and recorded live in a house in the Australian bush.

title: In My Mind
summary: The major label full-length debut release for R&B singer Bryan James Sledge features guest appearances from such artsts as Big K.R.I.T., Buddy, Chance the Rapper, and Kendrick Lamar.

title: Empath
summary: The latest solo release for the Canadian metal artist features contributions from Morgan Ågren, Ryan Dahle, Ché Aimee Dorval, Mike Keneally, Samus Paulicelli, Steve Vai, and Anneke Van Giersbergen.

title: Henryk Górecki: Symphony No. 3 "Symphony of Sorrowful Songs" [Live]
summary: The collaboration between the Portishead singer and the Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra conducted by Krzysztof Penderecki was recorded live in Warsaw on November 29th, 2014.

title: Sometimes the Blues is Just a Passing Bird
summary: The latest EP from Kristian Matsson was recorded while he was on tour.

title: Quiet Signs
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles singer-songwriter is her first recorded in a professional studio.

title: Takk...
summary: Sigur Ros' fourth album is the first to feature songs sung mainly in their native Icelandic, rather than their fabricated Hopelandish.

title: MCII
summary: The second release for the San Francisco-based rock singer features K. Dylan Edrich and Ty Segall as guest musicians.

title: Insula
summary: The debut full-length release for the Edinburgh grime producer features everyday sounds like conversations, police sirens, dial tones as well as influences from Japanese video game music.

title: Inner Song
summary: The second full-length release for the Welsh artist features a guest appearance from John Cale.

title: The Serpent & the Sphere
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Oregon black metal band was produced by Billy Anderson.

title: Nomad
summary: The second solo release for Tuareg guitarist-singer Omara “Bombino” Moctar was produced by The Black Keys' Dan Auerbach.

title: Copia
summary: Portland, Ore. ambient electronica artist Matthew Cooper returns with a fourth album.

title: The Black Album
summary: The hugely successful Brooklyn rapper worked with an A-list of producers (including Just Blaze, Kanye West, Aqua, Eminem, Rick Rubin and The Neptunes) on what he has stated will be the final release of his career. (Sure it will.)

title: Lost in Translation OST
summary: The soundtrack to Sofia Coppola's second feature film includes the first new music in over ten years from My Bloody Valentine's Kevin Shields (who scored much of the film), new music from Air, and older tracks from Squarepusher, Jesus And Mary Chain, and Death In Vegas.

title: Blood Money
summary: Written for a Robert Wilson stage production of Georg Büchner's unfinished 1836 play 'Woyzeck,' 'Blood Money' is one of two Waits releases in May 2002 (the other being 'Alice,' which was similarly created for the stage).

title: The  Worse Things Get, the Harder I Fight, the Harder I Fight, the More I Love You
summary: The sixth full-length release includes guest appearances from  Howe Gelb, Mudhoney's Steve Turner, Visqueen, M. Ward as well as members of Calexico, Los Lobos, My Morning Jacket, the New Pornographers, was produced by Tucker Martine.

title: My Life In The Bush Of Ghosts [2006 Version]
summary: Twenty-five years after its original release, this groundbreaking, sample-driven collaboration between Byrne and Eno has been remastered and enlarged with seven bonus tracks.

title: Introducing Karl Blau
summary: The latest release from the Washington State singer-songwriter was recorded with producer Tucker Martine.

title: Invasion of Privacy
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the New York rap artist features guest appearances from 21 Savage, Chance The Rapper, Kehlani, and SZA.

title: Burn Your Fire for No Witness
summary: The full-length release for the Missouri-born singer-songwriter was produced with John Congleton.

title: Singularity
summary: The fifth full-length solo studio release for the British electronic artist/producer features elements from such styles and influences from acoustic piano, choral music, psychedelic ambient, and techno music.

title: Halo
summary: The seventh full-length release for the singer-songwriter from Argentina features a guest appearance from Deerhoof's John Dieterich.

title: The Sciences
summary: The fourth full-length surprise release for the Northern California stoner metal band is its first new album in nearly two decades.

title: Living for a Song: A Tribute to Hank Cochran
summary: Elvis Costello, Ronnie Dunn, Merle Haggard, Emmylou Harris, Alison Krauss, Kris Kristofferson, Willie Nelson, and Leon Russell are some of the artists on Jamey Johnson's tribute to songwriter Hank Cochran.

title: Eleven Eleven
summary: The singer-songwriter who started his career with The Blasters wrote and recorded his latest solo album while on tour or during breaks from his 2010 tour.

title: ANIMA
summary: The third full-length solo release for the Radiohead artist was produced by Nigel Godrich and a companion 15-minute film directed by Paul Thomas Anderson is to be released on Netflix on the same day.

title: Sparkle Hard
summary: The seventh full-length release for the indie rock band features a guest appearance from Kim Gordon.

title: Imidiwan: Companions
summary: This is the fourth album for the African band.

title: The Crane Wife
summary: 'Crane Wife' marks the literate, Colin Meloy-led band's major label debut.

title: Black to the Future
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Shabaka Hutchings-led jazz quartet features guest appearances from Angel Bat Dawid, D Double E, Joshua Edelin, Lianne La Havas, Moor Mother, Kojey Radical, and Steve Williamson.

title: Extraordinary Machine
summary: The singer-songwriter's third album finally sees the light of day after originally being shelved by her record label in 2003 and then leaked onto the Internet. This official 'Machine' is a newly-recorded version (with producer Mike Elizondo taking over for the original's Jon Brion), so if you've heard the leaked tracks, you haven't heard this. Let the comparisons begin!

title: All Nerve
summary: The first new studio release from alternative rock in 10 years features the same line-up (Kelley and Kim Deal, Josephine Wiggs, and Jim Macpherson) that was on 1993's Last Splash and includes contributions from Courtney Barnett and Steve Albini.

title: Lamentations
summary: The latest full-length release for the ambient composer features tape loops from his personal archives - some date as far back as 1979.

title: Yesterday's Gone
summary: The debut full-length release for the British rapper features guest appearances from Kwes, Tom Misch, Mum and Rebel Kleff.

title: A.H.A.T.H.H.A.F.T.C.T.T.C.O.T.E.
summary: The Dallas rock trio continues what it terms as "stonegaze" music on its debut on the Kemado label.

title: Hey What
summary: The 13th full-length release for the Minnesota indie rock duo (bassist Steve Garrington left the band in 2020) of Alan Sparhawk and Mimi Parker was produced by BJ Burton.

title: Rips
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Washington DC trio formed by Wild Flag's Mary Timony, Laura Harris, and Betsy Wright.

title: Listening to Pictures (Pentimento Volume I)
summary: This is the first new release in nine years for the ambient jazz trumpeter.

title: Thanks for the Dance
summary: The posthumous release features music from the singer-songwriter's final session was produced by his son, Adam Cohen and features contributions from such artists as Beck, Leslie Feist, Daniel Lanois, Javier Mas, Richard Reed Perry, and Jennifer Warnes.

title: Premonitions
summary: The debut full-length release for the Los Angeles singer-songwriter was produced with Justin Raisen and Yves Rothman.

title: Carry Fire
summary: The 11th solo release for the Led Zeppelin lead singer is backed by his band the Sensational Space Shifters and features a guest appearance from Chrissie Hynde.

title: The Pretty Toney Album
summary: The former Wu-Tang member's fourth solo album (and first since ditching the "Killah" portion of his name) features contributions from Missy Elliott, Jadakiss and RZA.

title: Yoshimi Battles The Pink Robots
summary: The Oklahoma band finally returns with a follow-up to perhaps their strongest effort to date, 1999's 'The Soft Bulletin.' Here, the Lips venture even more into electronic territory, working once again with producer Dave Fridmann (Mercury Rev). Yoshimi of Japanese band The Boredoms guests on vocals on one track and lends her name to part of the album's title (the "Yoshimi" part, not the "Pink Robots" part).

title: The Beginning Stages Of...
summary: It's a bit hard NOT to get noticed when your band consists of a couple dozen people dressed in white robes, but having one of the most memorable debut albums in recent years (think Mercury Rev + Spiritualized + Up With People) certainly doesn't hurt. This 10-song debut (which was originally intended as a demo) did in fact land the Austin, Texas band led by former Tripping Daisy member Tim DeLaughter a major label deal.

title: Negro Swan
summary: The fourth full-length release for Dev Hynes as Blood Orange was self-produced and features guest appearances from A$AP Rocky, Ian Isiah, Steve Lacy, Janet Mock, Anne Muldrow, Project Pat, Puff Daddy, and Tei Shi.

title: Ten
summary: The jazz pianist with his backing band the Bandwagon releases a showcase of Moran's work, including a film score, a ballet piece, and songs by such artists as Leonard Bernstein, Thelonious Monk, Andrew Hill, and Jaki Byard.

title: For Free
summary: The latest full-length solo release for the singer-songwriter features a guest appearance from Sarah Jarosz.

title: Cuz I Love You

title: Love
summary: If the concept of "The Beatles, remixed" saddens you, know that original Beatles producer George Martin was at the helm for this project, which serves as the soundtrack to the Vegas-based Cirque du Soleil show of the same name. The 26 mashed-up tracks here were augmented with additional instrumentation and vocals performed by The Beatles themselves, culled from hours of original demo and master tapes, with pieces of 130 songs ultimately represented in some form.

title: Until the Quiet Comes
summary: Erykah Badu, Laura Darlington, Niki Randa, Thundercat, and Thom Yorke guest on the fourth release for the California electronic producer.

title: While I'm Livin'
summary: The first full-length album of new material in 17 years from the country legend was produced by Brandi Carlile and Shooter Jennings.

title: Stranger Things, Vol. 1 [Original Television Series Soundtrack]
summary: The first volume of the soundtrack to the Netflix show from Kyle Dixon & Michael Stein feature 36 tracks.

title: Amygdala
summary: The first solo releases in nine years from electronic producer Stefan Kozalla features guest appearances from Caribou, Apparat, Hildegard Knef, Matthew Dear, Ada, Milosh, and Dirk von Lotzow.

title: Foil Deer
summary: The second full-length major studio release for the Massachusetts indie rock band led by Sadie Dupuis was produced with Nicolas Vernhes.

title: Open Your Heart
summary: The third album from the Brooklyn quartet includes influences from country, psych, and rock music.

title: Laurel Hell
summary: The sixth full-length release for New York City indie artist Mitski was produced by Patrick Hyland.

title: Attack On Memory
summary: The second album for Cleveland's Cloud Nothings was produced by Steve Albini.

title: Like Red On A Rose
summary: The country singer's second 2006 album is another change-of-pace: a disc full of love songs produced by Alison Krauss.

title: Southern Air
summary: The eighth full-length release from the rock band led by Ryan Key and produced with Neal Avron features guest appearances from  Alex Gaskarth of All Time Low, Tay Jardine of We Are The In Crowd, and Cassadee Pope of Hey Monday.

title: Skeleton
summary: The third album for the Los Angeles-area punk-rock band.

title: Nonagon Infinity
summary: The eighth full-length release for the Australian psychedelic rock group was created to flow seamlessly to each following track and be able to be played in a infinite loop.

title: case/lang/veirs
summary: The debut full-length release for the collaboration between Neko Case, k.d. lang and Laura Veirs was produced by Tucker Martine.

title: Saturn
summary: The second full-length release for the British R&B artist features guest appearances from Kwabs and SiR.

title: Still Brazy

title: Gargoyle
summary: The latest release for the alternative rock artist features guest appearances from Josh Homme, Greg Dulli and Duke Garwood.

title: Wildflower

title: Deserted
summary: The first full-length studio release in eight years for the British punk collective was recorded near the Joshua Tree desert.

title: The Prodigal Son
summary: The first new full-length solo release in six years for the guitarist was produced with his son, Joachim Cooder.

title: EX EYE
summary: This is the debut four-track release for black metal/post-metal project that includes Colin Stetson, Liturgy's Greg Fox, Shahzad Ismaily, and Toby Summerfield.

title: Ill Manors
summary: The third release for the British musician is a companion piece to the film he wrote and directed, also named Ill Manors.

title: Hot Sauce Committee, Pt. 2
summary: The Brooklyn-based hip-hop legends return with their eighth studio album.

title: Ø (Disambiguation)
summary: The Christian rockers return with their fifth album of metalcore, the first release without founding member Aaron Gillespie.

title: Faking The Books
summary: This is the third LP for the German electro-pop outfit led by vocalist Valerie Trebeljahr and guitarist Markus Acher (also of The Notwist).

title: The Remote Part
summary: The third album for the Scottish rockers is already a big hit with UK music fans, helped by the success of lead single "You Held the World in Your Arms."

title: White Men Are Black Men Too
summary: The follow-up for the Edinburgh trio's Mercury-winning debut release was recording while on tour.

title: An Evening with Silk Sonic
summary: The full-length collaboration between Anderson .Paak and Bruno Mars was inspired by 1970s funk, soul and R&B music.

title: Visions of Us on the Land
summary: The 12th release for the Seattle indie singer-songwriter is the final album in his trilogy of albums that began with 2012's Maraqopa and was produced by Richard Swift.

title: Black Encyclopedia of the Air

title: Between My Head and the Sky
summary: The first album credited to the Yoko Ono Plastic Ono Band since 1975 features Keigo "Cornelius" Oyamada, Yuka Honda (of Cibo Matto), and her son/producer Sean Lennon.

title: Unflesh
summary: The second full-length release for Elizabeth Bernholz as Gazelle Twin includes production from Benge.

title: Loner
summary: The third full-length release for the singer-songwriter features influences from electronic, folk, pop, surf and punk music and was co-produced with Paul Butler.

title: No Answer: Lower Floors
summary: The latest release for the Michigan noise rock band includes contributions from former members Aaron Dilloway, Mike Connelly, and new guitarist James Baljo.

title: Sour
summary: The debut full-length release for the pop singer-songwriter features production from Dan Nigro, Alexander 23, and Jam City.

title: Skying
summary: The third album for the British rock quintet was produced and recorded by the band.

title: As the Love Continues
summary: The 10th full-length studio release for the Scottish post-rock band was produced by Dave Fridmann and features contributions from Atticus Ross and Colin Stetson.

title: The  Defenestration of St. Martin
summary: The former lead singer of the Britpop band Gene returns with his debut solo album.

title: Apocalypse
summary: Bassist Stephen Bruner collaborated with Flying Lotus on his second release infused by jazz, soul, and electronic music elements as Thundercat.

title: Lisbon
summary: The longtime New York indie band returns with another album of garage-rock and experimental instrumentation with its album, Lisbon.

title: The  Ghosts of Highway 20
summary: The 12th full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter was inspired by the highway that runs through Florida and Texas.

title: The Source
