summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Indiana dream-pop band led by Drew Auscherman.

title: Abandoned City
summary: The song titles for the experimental German musician's second solo release was inspired by photos of vacant cities and was recorded in 10 days in his home studio.

title: Will Happiness Find Me?
summary: This is the third full-length release from the Estonian-born electronic producer.

title: Give You the Ghost
summary: The debut album for the band that includes members of Gayngs was written in month and produced with Jim Eno of Spoon.

title: Warm Heart Of Africa
summary: The debut album for the African artist features guest appearances by M.I.A. and Vampire Weekend's Ezra Koenig.

title: So When You Gonna...
summary: The second full-length release for the London-based trio was produced and mixed by Marta Salogni.

title: Wise Up Ghost and Other Songs
summary: Originally begun as an album of reworked Costello songs, the debut collaboration between Elvis Costello and the Roots is instead a largely original release produced by Steven Mandel.

title: What It Means to Be Left-Handed
summary: The New York City band led by Adam Pierce releases its seventh album.

title: Are You Thinking What I'm Thinking?
summary: This debut for the all-girl L.A.-based trio (who are daughters of music industry bigwigs) was produced by former Prince backing musician Wendy Melvoin.

title: No More Songs About Sleep And Fire
summary: The veteran Illinois-based college-radio favorites offer up more new wave (or is that post new wave or new new wave?) tunes on their eighth studio LP.

title: Chain Gang Of Love
summary: Denmark's Raveonettes--now including two new members in addition to founders Sune Rose Wagner, Sharin Foo and their drum machine--make their major-label debut with this 13-track effort produced by Richard Gottehrer (Blondie). As on their debut EP, all songs are restricted to a single key (here, b-flat major) and must be shorter than 3 minutes.

title: Summer Sun
summary: The days of hard-rocking Yo La Tengo appear to be over (at least on record), as the Hoboken, NJ trio continues along the atmospheric, lower-volume path begun on 'And Then Nothing Turned Itself Inside-Out.' Included among the 13 Roger Moutenot-produced tracks is a cover of Big Star's "Take Care" and the James McNew-sung "Tiny Birds."

title: Have You Fed the Fish?
summary: After wowing music critics and winning Britain's Mercury Music Prize for his 2000 debut album, 'The Hour of Bewilderbeast,' Damon Gough (who is the one and only member of Badly Drawn Boy) took a bit of time off, recording only the soundtrack for 'About A Boy' in the interim. He now returns with a proper follow-up, preceded by single "You Were Right."

title: Creatures
summary: This is the fifth LP for the Athens, GA-based indie-pop band (part of the Elephant 6 collective) fronted by Andrew Rieger and Laura Carter.

title: Genesis
summary: Busta's fourth solo album includes 20 new tracks produced by the likes of Dr. Dre, the Neptunes, and Pete Rock. Guest vocalists include P. Diddy, Mary J. Blige, and the Flipmode Squad.

title: Delirium Tremens
summary: The third set of English translated Serge Gainsbourg songs from the Bad Seeds member features contributions from Xanthe Waite and Katy Beale.

title: Local Honey
summary: The third full-length solo release for The Gaslight Anthem frontman was produced by Peter Katis.

title: El Dorado
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the guitarist from South Carolina was produced by the Black Keys' Dan Auerbach.

title: Gathered
summary: The latest solo release from the Giant Sand artist features guest appearances from Pieta Brown, his daughter Talula Gelb, Anna Karina, Kira Skov and M. Ward.

title: Record
summary: The fifth full-length solo release for the Everything But The Girl singer features guest appearances from Bailey Rae and Shura.

title: The Soft Bounce
summary: The debut full-length release for Erol Alkan and Richard Norris as Beyond the Wizard's Sleeve features guest appearances from Euros Childs, Blaine Harrison of The Mystery Jets, Holly Miranda, Hannah Peel, and Jane Weaver.

title: Dying
summary: The debut full-length release for the British rock quartet was produced by Dominic Mitchison.

title: Unicorn
summary: The debut album for the British trio was produced by David Kosten.

title: IV
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Canadian jazz group features guest appearances from Future Islands' Samuel T. Herring, Mick Jenkins, Kaytranada, Colin Stetson, and Charlotte Day Wilson.

title: Cosmic Wink
summary: The third full-length release for the Los Angeles-based singer-songwriter was inspired by her recent move to California from Texas.

title: Frozen Letter
summary: The fourth full-length release for the North Carolina garage rock band led by Dan McGee features a guest appearance from Superchunk's Mac McCaughan.

title: A  Different Kind of Fix
summary: The third album for the British rock band was produced by Ben Allen, along with contributions from Jim Abbiss and Jack Steadman.

title: Wheelhouse
summary: The country singer self-produced his ninth studio release that features guest appearances from Dierks Bentley, Charlie Daniels, Hunter Hayes, Eric Idle, Mat Kearney, LL Cool J, and Roger Miller.

title: Forgiveness Rock Record
summary: With John McEntire as producer, Kevin Drew, Brendan Canning, Charles Spearin, Andrew Whiteman, Sam Goldberg, and Justin Peroff worked together to write the group's fourth studio album (outside of the two Broken Social Scene Presents...albums). Other BSS members do appear as guests on this release, including Leslie Feist, Amy Millan and Evan Cranley of Stars, Emily Haines and Jimmy Shaw of Metric, Jason Collett, and Ohad Benchetrit of Do Make Say Think and Years.

title: Fair Ain't Fair
summary: The Brooklyn, New York-based artist explores the idea of an apocalypse on his latest album.

title: Castlemania
summary: This is the first of two releases in 2011 for the San Francisco indie rock band led by John Dwyer.

title: Where The Wild Things Are [OST]
summary: The Yeah Yeah Yeahs' Karen O and several of her musician friends compose the soundtrack to Spike Jonze's adaptation of the children's book, Where The Wild Things Are.

title: Saltwater
summary: Martin Crane expands his Brazos music project with the addition of drummer Ian Chang and bassist Spencer Zahn on his second full-length release.

title: Some Racing, Some Stopping
summary: The sophomore full-length album for the indie rock trio from Champaign, Illinois.

title: In The Reins [EP]
summary: This mini-album finds seven new originals written and sung by Sam Beam (Iron & Wine) with Calexico's Joey Burns and John Convertino performing as his backing band.

title: Bigger Than Life
summary: The third full-length release for the Chris Stewart music project was self-recorded and produced.

title: Morning/Evening
summary: The two-track, 40-minutes album for Kieran Hebden as Four Tet was created using Ableton Live software.

title: Death After Life
summary: This is the debut full-length techno release for Chicago-based producer Ryan McRyhew.

title: Young Modern
summary: The fifth album from the Australian band includes Luke Steele, Julian Hamilton, and Paul Mac as guests.

title: You Can't Imagine How Much Fun We're Having
summary: The underground hip-hop duo of Slug and Ant return with a new two-disc set.

title: Street Punk
summary: Produced by Facundo Bermudez, Seth Bogart shares lead vocals with Shannon Shaw on the garage punk band's second full-length release.

title: They Threw Us in a Trench and Stuck a Monument On Top
summary: This debut LP from the experimental punk outfit from Brooklyn known for their strong live sets features lengthy song titles and an even lengthier closing track (clocking in at over half an hour).

title: Flat White Moon
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the British rock band led by brothers David Brewis and Peter Brewis was inspired in part by music from The Beatles, Free, Fleetwood Mac, and Led Zeppelin.

title: Tonic Immobility
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Mike Patton-led band that includes  Duane Denison, John Stanier, and Trevor Dunn was co-produced with Paul Allen.

title: Abysmal Thoughts
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Brooklyn indie pop band-turned-solo-project by Jonny Pierce who wrote and produced the album.

title: Bestival Live 2011
summary: The recording of The Cure's appearance at Britain's Bestival in September 2011 is the band's first live album since 1993.

title: 151A
summary: This is the debut solo full-length album for violinist/producer K. Ishibashi.

title: Celestite
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the black metal duo is a five-track companion album to 2011's Celestial Lineage.

title: First Flower
summary: The second full-length release for the Austin-based singer-songwriter was produced with Erik Wofford.

title: Silver/Lead
summary: The 40th anniversary for British post-punk band brings its 15th studio release that was partly recorded in Wales.

title: Jaakko Eino Kalevi
summary: The full-length debut for the Berlin-based electronic artist features guest appearances from Suad Khalifa and Sonja Immonen.

title: Taking Back Sunday
summary: The rock band from Long Island returns with a new album produced by Queens of the Stoneage's Eric Valentine and features the original lineup from its 2002 debut.

title: The Big Roar
summary: This is the debut full-length album on Atlantic for the Welsh trio and continues to be a cacophony of rock riffs and pop sensibility.

title: Pilot Talk
summary: Ski Beatz produced most of the New Orleans-born rapper's first solo album with Def Jam.

title: Waxing Gibbous
summary: This is the fifth studio album for the ex-Arab Strap band member.

title: Intruder
summary: The 18th full-length solo release for the British electronic artist is said to be about climate change from the Earth's point of view.

title: In the End
summary: The final release for Dolores O'Riordan (who passed away in January 2018) and the Irish rock band was produced by Stephen Street.

title: Felder
summary: The latest solo release for the Mouse on Mars artist is the fourth album in St. Werner's experimental Fiepblatter series.

title: Fantastic Planet
summary: This is the latest release for the solo project of Sarah Lipstate.

title: Legacy
summary: This is the debut full-length release from one of the pioneers of footwork.

title: Duppy Writer
summary: British producer Wrongtom remixes a collection of Roots Manuva's tracks.

title: Natural
summary: Check out the latest album from the British punk-rock band formed in 1977.

title: Shitty Hits
summary: The debut full-length release for the Brooklyn pop singer-songwriter was self-produced like her 2015 EP, Bleaksploitation.

title: Growing Pains
summary: The eighth album for the R&B singer was produced with help from The-Dream, Ne-Yo, Stargate, Dre & Vidal, and Timbaland.

title: Total Loss
summary: Tom Krell's second release as How to Dress Well shows more R&B influences.

title: Songs and Stories [Live]
summary: The country singer-songwriter releases a live acoustic album recorded at Nashville's Belcourt Theatre in 2009.

title: We Have You Surrounded
summary: The Dirtbombs fourth full-length album includes covers of songs by Alan Moore, Dead Moon, and Sparks.

title: Gliss Riffer
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Baltimore-based electronic artist was self-produced.

title: Typhoons
summary: The third full-length release for the British rock duo was self-produced except for two tracks with production from Paul Epworth.

title: Fudge Sandwich
summary: The covers album from the garage rock artist features songs by The Dils, Amon Düül II, Funkadelic, Gong, Grateful Dead, John Lennon, Rudimentary Peni, Sparks, Spencer Davis Group, War, and Neil Young.

title: Strychnine Dandelions
summary: The debut album featuring Reigning Sound's Greg Cartwright and The Ettes' Coco Hames includes appearances by Dan Auerbach, Patrick Keeler, and fellow band members Jem Cohen, Poni Silver, and Dave Amels.

title: A Brighter Beat
summary: This is the first solo release for the Scottish artist since the breakup of his band Arab Strap.

title: We All Raise Our Voices to the Air: Live Songs 04.11.08
summary: The two-disc live album collects 20 live songs from the band's tour for its 2011 album, The King Is Dead.

title: 22 Dreams
summary: The ninth album for Paul Weller features Blur's Graham Coxon, Little Barrie, Oasis' Noel Gallagher and Gem Archer, Ocean Colour Scene's Steve Cradock, and Stone Roses' Aziz Ibrahim.

title: SUGAREGG
summary: The third full-length release for Alicia Bognanno's rock project was produced by John Congleton.

title: The Bob's Burgers Music Album [Original Television Soundtrack]
summary: The soundtrack to the Fox animated comedy features songs from the first 107 episodes as well as five exclusive cover songs performed by  Lapsley, The National, St. Vincent, and Stephin Merritt of Magnetic Fields.

title: Ambulance
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Swedish indie rock band was live recorded over a few days.

title: Serpents Unleashed
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Ohio trash metal band was produced by Kurt Ballou.

title: Through the Window
summary: This is the experimental techno three-track release from Cold Cave member Dominick Fernow.

title: Olympic Girls
summary: The third full-length release for the New Zealand folk band was produced by Tom Healy.

title: Goodnight Oslo
summary: The second album Robyn Hitchcock has recorded with The Venus 3 (Peter Buck, Scott McCaughey, & Bill Rieflin) features a track used in the film Rachel Getting Married.

title: Little Amber Bottles
summary: The Detroit-based group and backing band on Loretta Lynn's "Van Lear Rose" release their sophomore album.

title: The Route To The Harmonium
summary: The latest full-length solo release for the Scottish singer-songwriter was recorded in his Scottish home and was produced with David Wrench.

title: Notes of Blue
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the alt-country band led by Jay Farrar was inspired by blues music.

title: LP3
summary: The third full-length release for the Philadelphia rock band was produced by Jonathan Low.

title: The Family Myth
summary: Chris Zane (Les Savy Fav) produced this third album for the Toronto duo-turned-foursome.

title: Half-Light
summary: The debut full-length release for the ex-Vampire Weekend member features guest appearances from Angel Deradoorian and Kelly Zutrau.

title: In a Dream
summary: With the end of LCD Soundsystem, Nancy Whang becomes a full-time member of Juan Maclean's synth-pop project for the duo's third full-length studio release.

title: International
summary: Hannes Norrvide's project expands into a trio with the addition of   Loke Rahbek and Malthe Fisher (who also produces the album) for its fourth full-length release.

title: Ancient & Modern
summary: The British country-punk rock band releases its latest album on Sin Record Label, which the band ran from 1985 to 1988.

title: Dents And Shells
summary: The sixth album for the indie-folk singer-songwriter was recorded in Texas and Arizona with a cast of up to eight backing musicians.

title: Brainwashed
summary: The late Beatle's final studio album was produced by Jeff Lynne with Harrison's son, Dhani.

title: Scarecrow
summary: Working again with longtime producer Allen Reynolds, Brooks' first country-pop album in four years includes duets with George Jones and Trisha Yearwood. If Brooks' claims are to be believed, this will also be his farewell album.

title: Once We Were Trees
summary: Los Angeles-based alt-country outfit Beachwood Sparks return with a second album for Sub Pop. The disc includes a cover of Sade's "By Your Side."

title: Drawn From Life
summary: The first album in four years (since 1997's 'The Drop') for Brian Eno finds the legendary musician/producer paired for the first time with German DJ/percussionist J. Peter Schwalm. Longtime Eno friend Laurie Anderson provides vocals on one song, although most of the thirteen tracks are atmospheric, soundtrack-like instrumentals (some with strings). Believe it or not, Eno will be performing live in support of the album, with at least one scheduled date (at the Fuji Rock Festival on 29 July 2001).

title: Let's Get Out Of This Country
summary: The six-piece Glaswegian indie-pop band really did leave the country, recording this third full-length with producer Jari Haapalainen (The Concretes) in Sweden.

title: Making a Door Less Open
summary: The first release in four years for the band led by Will Toledo was recorded over two sessions and is said to "contain elements of EDM, hip hop, futurism, doo-wop, soul, and of course rock and roll."

title: Wake Up!
summary: Backed by The Roots, John Legend delivers his fourth studio album of soul-conscious classics and original material.

title: The Blue Hour
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the British alternative rock band was produced by Alan Moulder.

title: I Never Learn
summary: The third full-length release for the Swedish singer-songwriter was produced with Björn Yttling and Greg Kurstin.

title: The Big Doe Rehab
summary: The seventh album for the member of the Wu-Tang Clan.

title: Object 47
summary: The first album for the punk band without Bruce Gilbert, who left in 2004.

title: The Don of Diamond Dreams
summary: The fifth full-length studio release for the duo of Ishmael Butler and Tende ‘Baba’ Maraire feature guest appearances from Darius, Carlos Overall, Purple Tape Nate, and Stas THEE Boss.

title: Pain
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Australian indie rock band is its first on the Sub Pop label.

title: Food
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the New York R&B singer was produced by Dave Sitek with guest appearances from CSS and Priscilla Ahn.

title: Room(s)
summary: Electronic producer Travis Stewart's latest album under the Machinedrum moniker is his first on the Planet Mu label.

title: Hyperspace
summary: The 14th full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter features contributions from Paul Epworth, Sky Ferreira, Terrell Hines, Greg Kurstin, Chris Martin, and Pharrell Williams.

title: Colour The Small One
summary: Australian singer-songwriter Sia Furler (also known for her work with Zero 7) received a boost when a track from her second solo album was featured during the conclusion of HBO's "Six Feet Under," prompting a very belated U.S. release of the album in 2006.

title: Redemption
summary: The conclusion of the ex-Danity Kane member's Heart trilogy features a guest appearance from PJ Morton.

title: Undercard
summary: Previously known as The Extra Glenns, the duo that comprises John Darnielle of The Mountain Goats and Franklin Bruno of Nothing Painted Blue, releases its first album under the new name.

title: The  Truth About Love
summary: Pink's sixth studio album features Eminem, Fun.'s Nate Ruess, and Lily Rose Cooper. It is her first album recorded for RCA Records.

title: Brood X
summary: The first new release in 17 years for the New York blues-punk band that includes Cristina Martinez and Jon Spencer.

title: Women As Lovers
summary: The first record for the San Francisco-based band since Devin Hoff joined as their bass player.

title: Everything Will Be Alright in the End
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the alternative rock quartet led by Rivers Cuomo was produced by Ric Ocasek.

title: Ritual in Repeat
summary: The third full-length release for the Denver husband-and-wife indie pop duo features production from Patrick Carney of The Black Keys, Jim Eno of Spoon, and Richard Swift.

title: Everything Not Saved Will Be Lost, Pt. 2
summary: The second part to the British indie rock band's earlier this year released Everything Not Saved Will Be Lost Pt. 1 was produced by frontman Yannis Philippakis with assistance from engineer Brett Shaw.

title: The Clearing
summary: The third album recorded at Justin Vernon's studio with Brian Joseph for the North Carolina trio is said to be bigger, bolder, and broader than previous releases.

title: Palberta5000
summary: The fifth full-length release for the New York-based trio of Ani Ivry-Block, Lily Konigsberg and Nina Ryser was recorded over four days with producer Matt Labozza.

title: How Do You Love?
summary: The second full-length release for the Los Angeles-based band is the first with new drummer and bassist Brooke Dickson and Drew Thomsen.

title: Highway Hypnosis
summary: The third release for Eva Moolchan as Sneaks was produced by Carlos Hernandez and Tony Seltzer (as well as Jacknife Lee on "Hong Kong to Amsterdam").

title: Resolve
summary: The latest solo release for the British artist who is also a member of Hidden Orchestra was self-produced.

title: Antisocialites
summary: The second full-length release for the Toronto-based indie-pop band led by Molly Rankin was produced by Alec O'Hanley and John Congleton.

title: Golden Eagle
summary: The debut full-length release for the Irish-born country artist was produced by Paul Gregory of Lanterns On The Lake.

title: Apache
summary: The latest solo release for the multiple Grammy award-winner was produced by Eric Krasno.

title: I Forget Where We Were
summary: The follow-up to the British singer-songwriter's Mercury Prize-nominated debut was produced by Chris Bond.

title: Unravelling
summary: The third full-length studio release for the Scottish indie rock band was produced by Paul Savage.

title: El Pintor
summary: Self-produced, the first release in four years for the New York rock band is also its first without bassist Carlos Dengler and features contributions from Secret Machines' Brandon Curtis, Jellyfish's Roger Joseph Manning, Jr., and Bon Iver's Rob Moose.

title: Impressions
summary: The second full-length release for the Los Angeles pop trio comes five years after their 2009 debut, Expressions.

title: The Reckoning
summary: The second full-length release for the British producer/singer-songwriter was produced by Ryan Adams.

title: Wild Crush
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British band sees the addition of Kristian Robinson and the return of Duke Garwood.

title: Motion: Connected Works
summary: The fourth full-length solo studio release for Mountains' Koen Holtkamp includes a disc of music that were first released on vinyl.

title: Invasion of Love
summary: The debut solo project for Cherry Ghost frontman Simon Aldred was produced by Ash Workman.

title: Pearl Mystic
summary: The debut full-length release for the British indie rock quintet includes influences from psychedelic and krautrock.

title: Pleasure Pressure Point
summary: Ex-Beta Band-er Steve Mason's latest group releases its debut full-length.

title: Jinx
summary: The second full-length release for the Brooklyn-based post-punk trio was produced by Monte Vallier.

title: Dream Wife
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the London based indie-pop trio of Rakel Mjöll, Alice Go, and Bella Podpadec.

title: Rose Mountain
summary: The sixth full-length release for the New Jersey rock trio was produced by Matt Bayles.

title: Nothing
summary: With the death of Daddi Gee, who worked under the name the Spaceape, dubstep producer Steve Goodman goes solo with this release, which does feature Spaceape’s vocals on one track.

title: What Went Down
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British indie rock band was recorded in France with producer James Ford.

title: Don't Tell the Driver
summary: The fourth solo release for the Dirty Three guitarist features guest appearances from  Peggy Frew, Caroline Kennedy-McCracken, Oliver Mann, Kishore Ryan, Ian Wadley, and Jeff Wegener.

title: Bodied
summary: The sixth full-length release for British electronic producer Alan Myson is said to have a "much greater focus into the sound design and palette."

title: Wooden Aquarium
summary: The third full-length release for the British rock band was recorded live with producer Jonathan Schenke.

title: Honey Locust Honky Tonk
summary: The 17-track album from the prolific singer-songwriter is his 19th solo release.

title: More Light
summary: The tenth studio release for the Scottish rock band was produced by David Holmes and features guest appearances by Robert Plant, My Bloody Valentine's Kevin Shields, and Mark Stewart.

title: Frantic
summary: Fresh off the Roxy Music reunion tour, Bryan Ferry resumes his solo career with this 13-track effort, a mix of Ferry originals and covers (including two Dylan tracks). Ferry has actually been working on this album for parts of the last eight (!) years, and it includes contributions from former Roxy Music partner/nemesis Brian Eno, the Eurythmics' Dave Stewart, and Radiohead's Johnny Greenwood.

title: Go Tell Fire To The Mountain
summary: The British rock band self-produced its debut full-length album, which was recorded in an unused church.

title: Human The Death Dance
summary: The underground rapper/poet returns with his second album for Epitaph, joined by guests Buck 65, Jolie Holland and Mark Isham.

title: Canta Lechuza
summary: Roberto Carlos Lange's second solo electronic album was written while he was staying at an isolated cabin in Connecticut.

title: White Crosses

title: Guns Don't Kill People...Lazers Do
summary: Switch and Diplo team up to release their first album as Major Lazer.

title: Happiness In Magazines
summary: Stephen Street produces the former Blur guitarist's fifth solo disc.

title: Brighter Wounds
summary: The fifth full-length release for Ryan Lott's solo-project-turned-trio that now includes Rafiq Bhatia and Ian Chang is its first on the City Slang label.

title: Water on Mars
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Philadelphia indie rock trio led by Mike Polizze is its first recorded in a professional studio.

title: The Chaos

title: Saint Bartlett
summary: The latest album for the singer-songwriter was produced by Richard Swift and recorded in just under week.

title: The '59 Sound
summary: The sophomore album for the New Jersey punk-rock band was produced by Ted Hutt.

title: Marlon Williams
summary: The solo full-length debut for the New Zealand singer-songwriter was co-produced with Ben Edwards.

title: Serpentine Prison
summary: The debut full-length solo release for The National's frontman was recorded over 14 days with producer Booker T. Jones.

title: Tomboy
summary: Noah Lennox, Animal Collective's founding member, releases his fourth solo album.

title: I'll Follow You
summary: The fourth album but the first with Merge Records for the Brooklyn-based band.

title: Say Yes to Love
summary: The noise punk band led by Meredith Graves releases a full-length follow-up to its 2013's four-track EP, I Have Lost All Desire For Feeling.

title: Sun and Shade
summary: Singer-guitarist Jeremy Earl and his band release their sixth full-length of sunny West Coast pop and folk rock.

title: The Volunteers
summary: Onelinedrawing is the alter ego for Sacramento, Calif.-based singer/guitarist Jonah Matranga, formerly of the emo band Far.

title: Margerine Eclipse
summary: 'Margerine Eclipse' marks the London-based band's first LP since the death of long-time member Mary Hansen, as well as the once-prolific group's longest-ever gap between albums (2 1/2 years).

title: Punk Rock
summary: 'Punk Rock' is just that, combining new recordings of some of the band's edgier late-70s output with live performances culled from their 25th anniversary tour in 2002.

title: In Reverie
summary: Less punk, more pop is the motto for the fourth album by the New Jersey emo band led by singer-songwriter Chris Conley.

title: AOI: Bionix
summary: The second installment in the "Art Official Intelligence" series (following 2000's 'Mosaic Thump') features the hit single "Baby Phat" and guest appearances from Slick Rick and Cypress Hill's B Real.

title: Last Place
summary: The first release in over a decade for the California indie rock band was produced by frontman Jason Lytle.

title: Why Love Now
summary: The fifth full-length release for the noise rock band was produced by Arthur Rizk and Lydia Lunch.

title: Asleep on the Floodplain
summary: Ben Chasny's psych-folk project releases its seventh album in five years, producing a more playful, atmospheric sound with Ben's trademark twangy, country-folk feel.

title: Postcards From a Young Man
summary: The Welsh rock band goes with a poppier sound on its Dave Eringa-produced 10th studio album.

title: Angels Of Destruction
summary: The Philadelphia/Brooklyn-based band returns with its latest studio album following a Christmas album in 2005.

title: Weirdon
summary: The seventh full-length release from the Philadelphia psych-punk trio includes influences from pop and indie rock music.

title: Shelter
summary: The is the debut full-length release from the London-based house/techno producer.

title: Ashore
summary: The British folk singer's latest album is a concept album about the relationships we have with the sea.

title: Payola
summary: The punk band led by Conor Oberst returns from a 13-year hiatus for its second full-length release that was co-produced by Mike Mogis.

title: The Eraser
summary: Nigel Godrich produced this 9-song solo debut for the Radiohead frontman, which mainly sounds like--shockingly--a Radiohead album, albeit with much less guitar.

title: The Visitor
summary: The third full-length solo release for the South American dance producer/artist includes contributions from Philipp Gorbachev, Ana Helder, Daniel Maloso, Alejandro Paz, Juliana Gattas, A'rea Negrot, Liset Alea and Jorge Gonz lez.

title: I Know What Love Isn't
summary: The Swedish singer-songwriter's first album in five years was influenced by a break-up.

title: Free TC
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the Los Angeles hip hop/R&B artist features guest appearances from such artists as Babyface, Brandy, E-40, Fetty Wap, Future, Kendrick Lamar, Rae Sremmurd, Trey Songz, Kanye West, Wiz Khalifa, and YG.

title: Rave Tapes
summary: The eighth full-length release for the Scottish post-rock band was produced with Paul Savage.

title: With The Lights Out
summary: This three-disc box set contains more than 50 previously unreleased recordings by the legendary Seattle band, including demos, live tracks, and alternate versions. Also included is an extensive bonus DVD filled with live performances.

title: Trouble in Paradise
summary: The second full-length release for the British synthpop artist Elly Jackson (Ben Langmaid left the band during the recording of the album) was co-produced with Ian Sherwin.

title: Something
summary: Alan Moulder and Dan Carey produces the first album in four years from New York's Chairlift.

title: Ashes & Fire
summary: The North Carolina-born singer's 13th album was produced by Glyn Johns, and it is his first since he left the band in part to Meniere's disease in 2009.

title: Renegade Breakdown
summary: The Canadian dance artist returns with L'Oeil Nu (Pierre Guerineau and Asaël R. Robitaille) with a pop and rock-inspired album.

title: Masts of Manhatta
summary: Tracy Bonhamâ€™s career trajectory seems to run in reverse; with each record, she gets riskier, coming a long, long way from the bottled-up furious angst of her â€˜90s alt-rock staple â€œMother Mother.â€ Masts of Manhatta, her fourth album and first since 2005â€™s Blink the Brightest, ups the ante from that haunting record by accentuating its elliptical turns, its songs dodging conventional routes in favor of left turns. Bonham is assisted greatly by Beck guitarist Smokey Hormel and his trio, who lend her songs earthiness and art, giving this heft and welcome unpredictability. To an extent, Bonham lays out her albumâ€™s thesis on â€œWe Moved Our City to the Country,â€ a knowing satire of hipsters fleeing the urban jungle for faux authenticity, where she feels the pull of the two extremes as evidenced by how her sawing violin contrasts with the cabaret shuffle of Hormelâ€™s group. Masts of Manhatta walks this line throughout, sometimes getting quite a bit livelier, sometimes indulging in decidedly moody textures, always twisting just slightly from the expected, making for a record thatâ€™s quite intriguing upon the first listen and better on repeats, where the songs begin to dig in and all the textures gain resonance. ~ Stephen Thomas Erlewine

summary: The two talented singer-songwriters and accomplished pianists pair up to release a duet album of original songs, featuring production by T-Bone Burnett.

title: Darling Arithmetic
summary: The third full-length release for the Conor O'Brien solo project was self-recorded and produced at home.

title: Passerby
summary: The second full-length release for the duo of Zoë Randell and Steve Hassett was co-produced with the National's Aaron Dessner.

title: LP
summary: Themes of religion are prominent in Chris d'Eon's latest solo album.

title: Putting The Days To Bed
summary: The John Roderick-led Seattle indie rockers return with a third album.

title: Suspended Animation
summary: The theme of Mike Patton's fourth Fantomas album (which is similar in sound to their first disc) is a calendar, which each track named after a different day of April 2005.

title: Local Valley
summary: The Swedish singer-songwriter sings in English, Spanish and Swedish on his fourth full-length studio release.

title: Kiss Of Death
summary: The New York rapper's second solo disc (after stints in the Ruff Ryders and the Lox) features production from Kanye West, the Neptunes and Swizz Beatz, with appearances from Nate Dogg, Snoop Dogg and Anthony Hamilton.

title: Ready For Love
summary: John Hammond follows his successful album of Tom Waits covers, Wicked Grin, with his first-ever original material. Well, ok, so he only wrote one song on this new album, but it is his first. Complimenting that track are selections written by the likes of Tom Waits, George Jones, Jagger/Richards and David Hidalgo (who also appears on the album).

title: Universal Truths And Cycles
summary: The Ohio band fronted by Robert Pollard offers up a 19-track set that is not just a return to former home Matador Records but a full return to classic, self-produced GBV form, after working with outside producers on the previous two albums.

title: The Golden Dove
summary: The second solo release for former Helium singer/guitarist Mary Timony was produced by Sparklehorse's Mark Linkous.

title: When I Was Cruel
summary: Costello's first album of original material in six years is a return to his new wave/punk/rock roots, with several members of The Attractions (Steve Nieve, Pete Thomas) in tow.

title: Everybody Got Their Something
summary: This is the debut American release for the Tokyo-born (but internationally-raised) singer-songwriter, who is the daughter of producer Don Costa and the goddaughter of Frank Sinatra. Costa has been performing since the age of five and has already scored hits in Europe and Australia.

title: SelmaSongs: Music from the Motion Picture Dancer in the Dark
summary: The soundtrack to Lars Von Trier's "Dancer In The Dark" consists of seven tracks from Bjork, who also starred in the film. Includes "I've Seen It All," a duet with Radiohead's Thom Yorke.

title: Quiet and Peace
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the Boston alternative rock band was produced by Dave Minehan.

title: Glynnaestra
summary: The experimental collaboration between Daniel O'Sullivan and Alexander Tucker explore avant pop on their second release.

title: Strangelet
summary: REM's Peter Buck and Bill Rieflin guest on the Los Angeles troubadour's latest disc of originals.

title: OH (Ohio)
summary: The latest album for the band from Nashville was produced by Mark Nevers and Roger Moutenot.

title: Thrice Woven
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the Washington state black metal band features guest appearances from Anna Von Hausswolff and Neurosis' Steve Von Till.

title: At War With The Mystics
summary: Dave Fridmann returns as producer for the ever-weird, Wayne Coyne-led band's first release in four years.
The British singer’s sophomore album is full of soul and pop rhythms, comparable to Amy Winehouse and Duffy.

title: Wild Peace
summary: The debut release for the indie rock duo of Thom Hill and Linda Jarvis.

title: Str8 Killa [EP]
summary: This eight-track EP follows on the heels of his 2009 independent mixtapes, The Miseducation of Freddie Gibbs and midwestganstaboxframecadillacmuzik.

title: 11 Short Stories Of Pain & Glory
summary: The ninth full-length release for the Celtic punk rock band was recorded in Texas and produced by Ted Hutt.

title: Troubadour
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Connecticut trio is said to be somewhat autobiographical.

title: Compass
summary: The fifth album for the British singer was produced by Beck and features a guest appearance by Chris Taylor of the band Grizzly Bear.

title: Dead Man's Bones
summary: Actors Ryan Gosling and Zach Shields team up to release their debut album as Dead Man's Bones.

title: Volume One
summary: Actress Zooey Deschanel teams up with M Ward on this debut album.

title: Everyone I Ever Met
summary: This is the debut full-length album for the British indie five-piece band.

title: Lantern
summary: This is the fourth album for the improvisational, instrumental, genre-defying four-piece, which shares a guitarist (Bryce Dessner) with The National.

title: An Album by Korallreven
summary: This is the first album from the Swedish duo of Marcus Joons and Daniel Tjader (formerly of The Radio Dept.).

title: Blue Chips 7000
summary: The second full-length studio release for the rapper is the third for his Blue Chips trilogy and features guest appearances from Big Body Bes, Jah Tiger, Meyhem Lauren and Rick Ross.

title: Oracular Spectacular
summary: David Fridmann produced the debut full-length album for the New York-based band.

title: Son of Rogues Gallery: Pirate Ballads, Sea Songs & Chanteys
summary: Johnny Depp and Hal Willner's second collection of pirate/sea songs includes vocals from such artists as Dr. John, Marianne Faithfull, Iggy Pop, Courtney Love, Keith Richards, Patti Smith, Michael Stipe, and Tom Waits.

title: Blondes
summary: The debut album for the Brooklyn electronic duo of Zach Steinman and Sam Haar includes three previously released tracks.

title: The Story of Sonny Boy Slim
summary: The second full-length release for the Austin guitarist was self-produced.

title: Amok

After the success of the tour, the band decided to work on an album and recorded the debut in three days.

title: Ur Fun

title: hej!
summary: The full-length debut studio release for the London-based producer features a guest appearance from Chairlift's Caroline Polachek.

title: The Return
summary: The debut full-length release for the British jazz artist features a guest appearance from Mansur Brown and influences from drum 'n' bass, hip hop and R&B.

title: Hang
summary: The fifth full-length release for the indie rock duo of Sam France and Jonathan Rado features a full symphony orchestra conducted by Trey Pollard and contributions from Matthew E. White, The Flaming Lips' Steve Drozd and The Lemon Twigs.

title: A Cure for Loneliness
summary: The eighth solo release for J. Geils Band lead singer features four songs co-written with Grammy/Academy Award-winning songwriter Will Jennings.

title: Aa
summary: The debut full-length release for the Philadelphia electronic producer features guest appearances from such artists as Future, Leikeli47, M.I.A., Novelist, Pusha T, Rustie, and Tirzah.

title: Before A Million Universes
summary: This is the second full-length release for the New York post-punk quartet.

title: Wald
summary: The seventh full-length release from Berlin-based producer Stefan Betke was inspired by his walks in the Alps forest.

title: Parker Millsap
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Oklahoma singer-songwriter.

title: Unity Band
summary: The latest album for Pat Metheny features an ensemble that includes Antonio Sanchez, Ben Williams, and Chris Potter.

title: The High Country
summary: The alt-country band's latest album tells of a dark and violent love affair set in an unnamed Oregon logging town.

title: Gentle Spirit

It includes Andy Cabic and Otto Hauser of Vetiver; Chris Robinson and Adam McDougall of the Black Crowes; and Brian Geltner, Barry Goldberg, Josh Grange, Gerald Johnson, Gary Louris, and Gary Mallaber as guest musicians.

title: Screws Get Loose

title: Isla

title: Intoxication
summary: The dance-hall artist returns with his latest album, including one song with Akon.

title: ...And They Have Escaped the Weight of Darkness
summary: The second full-length album for Icelander Olafur Arnalds continues to meld classical music with pop and rock music.

title: Babes Never Die
summary: The second full-length release for the Scottish indie-pop duo of Cat Myers (taking over for Shona McVicar, who left shortly after their debut release) and Stina Tweeddale was produced by James Dring.

title: True Romance
summary: The debut studio release for the British pop singer includes some tracks from her two previous mixtapes "Heartbreaks and Earthquakes" and "Super Ultra."

title: Jumping the Shark
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the Seekae co-founder was produced with Fanny B.

title: Russian Roulette

title: Algiers
summary: The latest full-length release for the Arizona alternative rock band led by Joey Burns and John Convertino was recorded in New Orleans with producer Craig Schumacher.

title: Young Machetes
summary: The band's fifth album was produced by Guy Piccioto and John Goodmanson.

title: My Way
summary: The latest release for the country singer-songwriter is a tribute to Frank Sinatra featuring songs made famous by the the man called the Chairman of the Board and a guest appearance by Norah Jones.

title: Backwater
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Australian electronic-pop duo of Chloe Kaul and Simon Lam.

title: Cellar Door
summary: Even with more than 20 years in the industry, British DJ/producers Conrad McDonnell and Dan Tyler have not released a full-length album of their own until now.

title: Woke On A Whaleheart
summary: The singer-songwriter behind Smog [and its more parenthetical offshoot, (Smog)] returns with his first release under his given name.

title: Blood Pressures
summary: Ending a multi-year hiatus, The Kills return with another album of minimalist garage punk.

title: Doko Mien
summary: The third full-length release for the Nigerian Afro-electronic band led by London-born Eno Williams was produced by Max Grunhard.

title: Move in Spectrums
summary: The first release in four years for the Brooklyn synth-pop trio was produced by the Violens' Jorge Elbrecht.

title: Two Matchsticks
summary: This is the second album for the band led by American Analog Set's Andrew Kenny and includes Sean Haskins, Matt Pond and Leslie Sisson. Death Cab For Cutie's Ben Gibbard features as a guest.

title: Escape 2 Mars
summary: The rapper who was a member of Blackalicious releases his second solo album.

title: The Neon
summary: The latest full-length release from the British synth-pop duo was self-produced and recorded in Atlanta.

title: Do It Again
summary: The five-track mini-LP from the collaboration between Royksopp and Robyn includes two tracks from Röyksopp’s upcoming album.

title: In Stormy Nights
summary: The first release in three years for the Japanese psych-rockers contains just six tracks, including one that clocks in at nearly half an hour.

title: Elsie
summary: The debut side project for Gaslight Anthem lead singer Brian Fallon also features his guitar tech, Ian Perkins.

title: Slime & Reason
summary: The fourth album for the rapper includes Metronomy as a guest artist.

title: Reunion Tour
summary: The Canadian band's fourth studio album, again produced by Ian Blurton.

title: Principe del Norte
summary: The fourth solo release from the Norwegian artist/producer is a two-disc (or four LP) album of instrumentals influenced by 90's ambient music.

title: Lost Time
summary: The debut release for Liturgy's Greg Fox and Oneida's Kid Millions was recorded in two separate sessions.

title: Everyday Robots
summary: The solo debut release for the Blur frontman features guest appearances from Brian Eno, Bat For Lashes' Natasha Khan, and The Leytonstone City Mission Choir.

title: Lustre
summary: Ryan Hadlock helped produce the fifth studio album for British singer-songwriter, Ed Harcourt. The UK edition includes a seven-track bonus disc.

title: Heaven Is Whenever
summary: The first album for the band without Franz Nicolay, who left the band in January 2010, was produced by Dean Baltulonis.

title: What Do You Think About the Car?
summary: The debut full-length release for the British alternative pop singer-songwriter was produced by James Ford of Simian Mobile Disco.

title: In Mind
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Brooklyn-based New Jersey indie rock band is its first with new guitarist, Julian Lynch (Matt Mondanile left to concentrate on Ducktails).

title: Seek Warmer Climes
summary: This is the debut full-length release from the Danish post-punk band led by Adrian Toubro.

title: ilp.
summary: The debut full-length release for the British producer/singer  includes elements of R&B, pop and electronic music.

title: Unearth
summary: The second album for duo of Andrew Phillips and Marcus O'Dair was inspired by places in United Kingdom and features a guest appearance by Robert Wyatt.

title: Forever Today
summary: The 27-member Swedish band's third album was recorded live during two recording sessions.

title: Ten New Songs
summary: Leonard Cohen's first album of new material since 1992's 'The Future' contains, oddly enough, ten new songs. Sharon Robinson co-wrote each of the tracks, as well as providing instrumentation and backing vocals.

title: Ceremonials
summary: The darker second album for the indie band was produced by Paul Epworth.

title: Before I Die
summary: The debut full-length release for the Los Angeles-based South Korean electronic artist was self-produced.

title: The Way It Is
summary: Kanye West is among the producers on this major-label debut for the 21-year-old Oakland, Calif. native.

title: Be the Void
summary: Dr. Dog officially adds Dimitri Manos to the band for its live tracked seventh album coproduced with Nathan Sabatino.

title: Transit Transit
summary: With influences ranging from Sonic Youth to My Bloody Valentine, this Los Angeles trio's second album mixes melodic dream pop, electronica, and rock.

title: Leaving Meaning.

title: The Sea of Memories
summary: The Swedish pop duo of Henrik Martensson and his friend Johan Angergard of Labrador Records, as well as such bands as Club 8, Acid House Kings, and the Legends, releases its debut album.

title: Talkie Walkie
summary: Nigel Godrich (Radiohead) produced this third studio LP for the French duo, who handle all the vocal duties themselves for the first time.

title: My Morning Jacket
summary: This is the first new studio release in six years for the rock band led by Jim James (who also produced the album).

title: Woke Myself Up
summary: Although still a solo album, 'Woke Myself Up' finds the singer-songwriter backed by her former bandmates in the Canadian group Eric's Trip for the first time in a decade.

title: Egoli
summary: The fourth full-length release for the collective that includes Damon Albarn, Gruff Rhys, and Moonchild Sanelly was recorded in a week with guest appearances from such artist as Ghetts, Mahotella Queens, Mr. Jukes, Phuzekhemisi, Radio 123, and Nick Zinner.

title: Evil Spirits
summary: The first release in a decade for the British punk rock band was recorded live over nine days by producer Tony Visconti.

title: The Possum in the Driveway
summary: The fifth full-length solo release produced by Scott Amore comes after a series of setbacks including a studio fire, a car crash, and a bout of the measles for the singer-songwriter.

title: At Least for Now
summary: This is the full-length debut release for the British singer-songwriter first discovered in Paris, France.

title: Mariachi El Bronx (III)
summary: This is the third full-length release from the Mexican Mariachi music side project formed by the Los Angeles punk band The Bronx.

title: Knoxville
summary: The recording is the live improv performance of Christian Fennesz, David Daniell, and the Necks' Tony Buck at the Knoxille, Tennessee, Big Ears Festival in February 2009.

title: Them Crooked Vultures
summary: The debut album for the supergroup composed of the Foo Fighters' Dave Grohl, Queens Of The Stone Age's Josh Homme, and Led Zeppelin's John Paul Jones.

title: H.N.I.C. Pt. 2
summary: The rapper, also part of Mobb Deep, returns with a continuation to his debut solo album, "H.N.I.C.," after last year's "Return of the Mac."

title: Boo!
summary: The first album in more than 15 years features guest appearances by Booker T. Jones, Kris Kristofferson, Wayne Kramer, Marcus Miller, and a song originally cowritten with Bob Dylan.

title: Berberian Sound Studio
summary: The soundtrack to Berberian Sound Studio, Peter Strickland's homage to Italian horror films, is the final album for Trish Keenan, who passed away in January 2011.

title: Belief System
summary: The 23-track release from British electronic producer Paul Woolford was recorded over a period of three years.

title: Super
summary: The 13th studio release for the British synth-pop duo was produced by Stuart Price.

title: Invisible Girl
summary: This is the third full-length album for the Canadian rock duo.

title: Rose City
summary: After taking a year off, Kevin and Anita Robinson wrote and recorded this album in a month.

title: Hummingbird, Go!
summary: The Swedish singer previously based in New Orleans releases her latest solo album.

title: To Be Still
summary: The California-born, Portland, Oregon-based singer-songwriter releases her follow-up to her debut album, "The Pirate’s Gospel."

title: Hera Ma Nono
summary: This is the sophomore album for the Kenyan and American group.

title: Mala in Cuba
summary: In 2011, DJ Gilles Peterson asked British dubstep producer Mala to come to Cuba to help on his "Havana Cultura: The Search Continues" album. Mala integrated the sounds he heard on his first official solo full-length debut release.

title: Daisy
summary: This is the fourth full-length album for the Long Island, New York, rock band.

title: Return Of The Mac
summary: This solo release (somewhere between a mixtape and a true album) for the Mobb Deep rapper was produced by the Alchemist.

title: Joyful Rebellion
summary: This is the second full-length for the adventurous Canadian rapper, who mixes jazz, reggae and rock with hip-hop. He produced the album himself, and even plays guitar and piano on several tracks.

title: The Traveling Kind
summary: The second full-length release from Emmylou Harris and Rodney Crowell features six co-written songs and was produced by Joe Henry.

title: Pale Communion
summary: The 11th full-length release for the Swedish progressive rock/metal band was produced by bandleader Mikael Åkerfeldt and mixed by Porcupine Tree's Steven Wilson.

title: Another World [EP]
summary: The New York City band releases its latest EP ahead of its full-length album, "The Crying Light."

title: So You Wannabe an Outlaw
summary: The 17th full-length studio release for the singer-songwriter was produced by Richard Bennett and features guest appearances from  Johnny Bush, Miranda Lambert and Willie Nelson.

title: Departing
summary: The Canadian indie rock trio return with their second release of lovelorn, nostalgic, anthem-heavy pop songs.

title: The Pet Parade
summary: The ninth full-length release for Eric D. Johnson's indie folk project was produced and engineered with Josh Kaufman.

title: Girl with Basket of Fruit
summary: the 11th full-length release for the Los Angeles-based experimental band led by Jamie Stewart and was co-produced by Angela Seo and Deerhoof's Greg Saunier.

title: Million Dollars To Kill Me
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Southern California pop-punk band was produced by Kurt Ballou.

title: Hammer of the Witches
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the British extreme metal band led by Dani Filth features a line-up with two guitarists: Marek "Ashok" Šmerda and Richard Shaw.

title: We Come from the Same Place
summary: This is the third full-length release for the indie pop band.

title: No One's First, And You're Next
summary: Modest Mouse releases an album with tracks from the "We Were Dead Before the Ship Even Sank" and "Good News for People Who Love Bad News" recording sessions.

title: Many Moons
summary: The debut full-length solo release for the Real Estate frontman was produced by Woods' Jarvis Taveniere.

title: Believe You Me
summary: This is the debut full-length release from the collaboration between Julianna Barwick and Helado Negro (aka Roberto Lange).

title: Black Cascade
summary: The third album for the Washington-based metal band was produced by Randall Dunn.

title: Stranger Than Fiction
summary: After a number of mixtapes, the rapper from Louisiana releases his debut full-length studio release that includes guest appearances from Juicy J and Wiz Khalifa.

title: Total Dust
summary: Leon Taheny produced the debut solo album for Holy Fuck's Brian Borcherdt as Dusted.

title: Vertigo Days
summary: The first new full-length studio release in seven years for the German band features guest appearances Angel Bat Dawid, Ben LaMar Gay, Juana Molina, and Zayaendo.

title: Love in the 4th Dimension
summary: The debut full-length release for the British indie rock band led by Jules Jackson was co-produced with Catherine Marks.

title: Skin
summary: The second full-length release for Australian electronic producer Harley Streten features guest appearances from AlunaGeorge, Beck, Kai, Allan Kingdom, Kučka, Little Dragon, Tove Lo, Vic Mensa, MNDR, Raekwon, and Vince Staples.

title: Family
summary: British folk rock artist Teddy Thompson collaborates with his father Richard, his mother Linda, his sister Kami, his half-brother Jack Thompson, and nephew Zak Hobbs on this debut release produced by Teddy.

title: Till Midnight
summary: The fourth studio release for the singer-songwriter was produced by Christopher Thorn and features guest appearances from Ben Nichols of Lucero, Dave Hause of The Loved Ones, Jenny O., Chad Price, and John Snodgrass of Drag The River.

title: The Big Other
summary: The full-length debut for the British indie rock band includes a song dedicated to World War II scientist Alan Turing.

title: I Was a Cat from a Book
summary: Dave Wrench helped produced the album with the British singer-songwriter that includes contributions from members of The Cinematic Orchestra, Lamb, and Sparrow & The Workshop.

title: MMXII
summary: An apocalyptic future is the central theme for the 15th album from the British post-punk rock band.

title: I Love You. It's a Fever Dream
summary: The first release in four years for Kristian Matsson as The Tallest Man On Earth was recorded in his Brooklyn apartment.

title: The Desired Effect
summary: The second full-length solo release for The Killers lead singer was produced with Ariel Rechtshaid.

title: Hive Mind
summary: Mi Ami's Daniel Martin-McCormicks releases a five-track album of house music under the name Ital for Planet Mu.

title: Cigarettes After Sex
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Brooklyn ambient pop band led by Greg Gonzalez.

title: IV
summary: The first studio release in more than five years [not including the Year Zero soundtrack] for the Vancouver rock band was produced by Randall Dunn.

The third full-length studio release for the British singer-songwriter features songs co-written with such artists as Brian Burton, Samuel Dixon, Paul Epworth, Tobias Jesso Jr., Greg Kurstin, Bruno Mars, Max Martin, Karl Johan Schuster, and Ryan Tedder.

title: Centipede Hz
summary: The ninth studio album sees the return of founding member Deakin and co-producer Ben Allen.

title: Smile
summary: The Japanese experimental group's latest album features guest musicians Michio Kurihara of Ghost and Stephen O'Malley of Sunn O))).

title: The  Bronx (IV)
summary: The fourth self-titled release for the Los Angeles punk band is its first since 2008. They previously released two albums under the name Mariachi El Bronx in 2009 and 2011.

title: Honey Moon
summary: The latest album for the duo is a series of love songs to celebrate their 20 years of marriage.

title: The Rhumb Line
summary: This is the debut full-length album for the upstate New York indie rock band.

title: The  Inevitable End
summary: The final release for the Norwegian electronic duo of Svein Berge and Torbjørn Brundtland as Röyksopp features guest appearances from Ryan James of Man Without Country, Jamie McDermott of The Irrepressibles, Robyn, and Susanne Sundfør.

title: Humbug
summary: The third album for the British band was co-produced by Josh Homme and James Ford.

title: Tales of a Grass Widow
summary: The fifth full-length release for the sister duo of Bianca and Sierra Casady was produced with Valgeir Sigurðsson.

title: Winds Take No Shape
summary: The Bay Area indie-pop band returns with a second LP.

title: Today Is The Day [EP]
summary: More "rocking" than recent LP 'Summer Sun,' this six-track EP includes four new songs plus alternate versions of "Cherry Chapstick" and the title cut.

title: Chicken & Beer
summary: Perhaps the most successful Dirty South rapper, Ludacris returns with his third Def Jam release.

title: So Much Staying Alive & Lovelessness
summary: Mixing post-rock and emo with punk edigness and experimentalism, Chicago's Joan of Arc features members of the Owls and Cap'n Jazz, including Owls vocalist Tim Kinsella. On this fourth album, they are also joined by members of Califone, Isotope 217, and Ugly Casanova, among others.

title: Equilibrium
summary: The latest installment in Thirsty Ear's Blue Series (which mixes cutting-edge jazz with elements of electronica and hip-hop), 'Equilibrium' showcases the talents of avant-garde pianist Matthew Shipp.

title: Held
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the Manchester electronic producer.

title: Night & Day
summary: Andre Williams and the Canadian alt-country rock band the Sadies worked together in 2008, however due to Williams' legal and personal problems the project was shelved until they reunited recently to finish the album.

title: True Loves
summary: This is the Brooklyn indie rockers first full-length album on Dovecote.

title: The Lamb
summary: The second full-length release for the Chicago-based singer-songwriter was written after a series of events including "a home invasion, deaths of loved ones and general violence."

title: New Spirit
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Australian electro-rock trio (previously known as Pivot) was recorded in London and Sydney.

title: Arms Around a Vision
summary: The third full-length release for the Northern Irish post-punk band was self-produced and mixed by Dan Rejmer.

title: Going Back Home
summary: After former Mr. Feelgood guitarist Wilko Johnson learned he had terminal pancreatic cancer, he went on tour and soon heard from Who singer Roger Daltrey about recording an album together. The collaboration was recorded in a week and was produced by Dave Eringa.

title: Despite Our Differences
summary: Mitchell Froom produced the latest for the duo of Amy Ray and Emily Saliers.

title: Combat Sports
summary: The fourth full-length release for the indie rock band was produced by Ross Orton.

title: Who Are You
summary: This is the debut full-length studio release for producer Eddie Ruscha, who previously released music under the name Secret Circuit.

title: Royal Headache
summary: The self-titled release for the garage punk band from Australia was produced by Mikey Young of Eddy Current Suppression Ring.

title: Just A Little Lovin'
summary: Shelby Lynne's 10th album has her covering some of Dusty Springfield's biggest hits.

title: Jackleg Devotional to the Heart
summary: The second release for the Texas folk band was co-produced by band member Jason Reimer and producer Stuart Sikes.

title: XXXX
artist: You Say Party! We Say Die!
summary: Released in their native country last fall, the third album for the Canadian rockers finds the quintet adds new variations to their sound.

title: Translated From Love
summary: Five years since her last release (Christmas album withstanding), country singer Kelly Willis returns with a new album.

title: Lux
summary: Brian Eno's debut solo release on Warp (two previous releases were collaborations with other artists) was originally composed for a sound art exhibit in Italy.

title: Unbreakable
summary: The first studio release in seven years for the R&B/pop singer features guest appearances from Missy Elliott and J. Cole.

title: We Must Become the Pitiless Censors of Ourselves
summary: This is the latest album for the experimental composer from Minnesota.

title: Pyramid
summary: The four-track album from the Norwegian ensemble was self-produced and created over two weeks in Sweden.

title: Gene
summary: The first full-length release for the Late Of The Pier frontman as LA Priest since 2015's Inji was co-produced with Erol Alkan.

title: Blue With Lou
summary: The first new studio release in eight years for the E Street Band member features six songs co-written with Lou Reed.

title: Embers
summary: The second full-length release for the British electronic producer Ross Tones includes natural field recordings from around the small English village he held the recording sessions at.

title: Promise Everything
summary: The British rock band return from its three-plus year hiatus to release its third full-length album produced by Sam Pura.

title: Moon Tides
summary: The full-length debut for Vetiver's Daniel Hindman and Sarah Versprille was produced by Richard Swift of The Shins.

title: Memory
summary: The second full-length album for the electronic duo of Anateus Roy and Bryant Rutledge includes influences from such music genres as techno, footwork, and drum 'n' bass.

title: There's Always Another Girl
summary: The singer-songwriter's 11th studio album's focus is funding There's Always Another Girl (previously known as Speeches Delivered to Animals and Plants), in conjunction with the Pledge Music website, and she's also donating a percentage of the money put up by the fans to a pair of animal shelters.

title: A Woman, A Man, Walked By
summary: PJ Harvey and her producer John Parish team up again with a new album produced by Flood.

title: 200 Million Thousand

title: Electric Slave
summary: The third release from the Austin soul and blues-rock band includes production from Stuart Sikes and John Congleton on three tracks.

title: Rot Gut, Domestic
artist: Margot & the Nuclear So and So's
summary: Jon Congleton produced the fourth album for the indie pop group led by Richard Edwards.

title: Kudos
summary: This is the full-length debut album for the New Zealand indie rock quartet.

title: The Autumn Defense
summary: This is the third album for the side project of Wilco members Pat Sansone and John Stirratt.

title: The Minus 5 [The Gun Album]
summary: Scott McCaughey's seventh Minus 5 album includes contributions from members of Wilco, R.E.M., The Decemberists, Ministry, The Posies and more.

title: Waiting on a Song

title: Life Death Love and Freedom
summary: John Mellencamp latest album was produced by T Bone Burnett who also developed a new audio format promised to help the album sold sound like master tapes.

title: The New Abnormal

title: Golem

title: Wait For Love
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Baltimore post-hardcore band was produced by by Will Yip.

title: Bashed Out

title: The Physical World
summary: The second full-length studio release for the Canadian duo of Sebastien Grainger and Jesse F. Keeler was produced by Dave Sardy.

title: Hour of the Dawn

title: Wreck
summary: The seventh release for the New York noise rock band was produced by Andrew Schneider.

title: Human Hearts
summary: The indie rock band from Milwaukee, Wisconsin, releases its fourth full-length album.

title: The Inevitable Past Is the Future Forgotten
summary: The San Diego indie rock band returns with its first studio full-length album in more than 13 years.

title: The Eminem Show
summary: Working once again with producer Dr. Dre, Marshall Mathers returns with his third album.

title: Thrashing thru the Passion
summary: The first full-length studio release for the Brooklyn-based rock band in five years was produced by Josh Kaufman.

title: Reflection

title: Mourn
summary: The debut full-length release for the Spanish band formed by four teenagers was recorded in two days.

title: The Scene Between
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British bedroom project-turned-band sees Ian Parton taking the reins as a solo project once again: writing, producing and performing all the songs with guest vocalists.

title: OK Human

title: async: Remodels
