summary: The jazz standards release from Tony Bennett and Lady Gaga followed their collaboration on a track off Bennett's 2011 album, Duets II.

title: Yell Fire!
summary: Pink and Sly & Robbie guest on the latest Spearhead offering, which was produced by Michael Franti with Mario Caldato Jr. (Beastie Boys) and mixes reggae, hip-hop and R&B.

title: Working Girl
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British electro-pop artist features production from Com Truise, Patrick Lukens, Ariel Rechtshaid, Jas Shaw of Simian Mobile Disco, and MNDR's Pete Wade.

title: Preparations
summary: The fourth album for the artist also known as Savath & Savalas.

title: WYWH
summary: After three years, the Stockholm-based band is back with its fourth album of pure dance pop.

title: Mt. St. Helens Vietnam Band
summary: The Seattle-based band's debut album was produced with Scott Colburn.

title: Perfect Symmetry
summary: The third album for the British rock group was produced with Jon Brion and Stuart Price.

title: Weezer (Red Album)
summary: The sixth studio album for the Los Angeles band was produced by Rick Rubin and Jacknife Lee.

title: The Spirit Of Apollo
summary: Squeak E. Clean and DJ Zegon team up with a variety of guests on their first album together.

title: In a Warzone
summary: The third full-length release for the punk trio of Rancid's Tim Armstrong, blink-182's Travis Barker, and "Skinhead Rob" Aston, is its first in eight years.

title: More Than Just a Dream
summary: Produced by Tony Hoffer, the Los Angeles six-piece mixes electronic music elements to its 1960s soul on its second full-length release.

title: Fire Away
summary: The Grammy-winning Los Angeles-based group releases its latest album produced by Tony Berg.

title: Sunny Side Up
summary: The second album for the singer was produced by Ethan Johns.

title: In A Space Outta Sound
summary: George Evelyn's latest dubby, trip-hoppy, downtempo NoW disc was co-produced by Robin Taylor-Firth.

title: The Big Bang
summary: Missy Elliott, will.i.am, Nas, and Stevie Wonder are among the guests on the veteran rapper's first effort in four years.

title: Some People Have Real Problems
summary: The third album for the Australian singer known for her work with Zero 7.

title: The Third Gleam
summary: The latest full-length release for the folk rock trio is the third installment of their ongoing Gleam series.

title: Run The Road Volume 2
summary: This is the second in a series of compilations showcasing the UK grime scene. Included here are artists such as Kano and Plan B.

title: Encore
summary: The fourth full studio album for the multi-platinum superstar features appearances from Obie Trice, 50 Cent, Nate Dogg and D-12.

title: Complete Strangers
summary: The sixth full-length release for the indie folk band led by Andy Cabic was produced by Thom Monahan.

title: Sam's Town
summary: Flood and Alan Moulder handled production for the popular Las Vegas band's second album.

title: Life Coach
summary: Trans Am's Phil Manley releases his first solo album.

title: Swoon
summary: The second album for the Los Angeles indie-rock band was produced by Dave Cooley.

title: All At Once
summary: The avant-garde Los Angeles band's third album is their first without co-founder Jeff Rosenberg.

title: DVA
summary: The second full-length release for the British electronic singer Ema Jolly includes a cover of Chris Isaak's "Wicked Game."

title: Wooden Arms
summary: The Montreal band releases its follow-up to 2007's "Close to Paradise."

title: Fandango
summary: The fifth release for the New Zealand psychedelic indie rock band is 80 minutes long.

title: Things Go Better With RJ And Al
summary: The duo of RJD2 and Blueprint return with a second collaboration.

title: Rize of the Fenix
summary: The third album for Jack Black and Kyle Gass as Tenacious D features Dave Grohl on drums.

title: Pacific Daydream
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the alternative rock band led by Rivers Cuomo features production from Jonny Coffer, Toby Gad, J.R. Rotem, and Butch Walker.

title: Copper Gone
summary: The first studio release for the indie rapper in four years features production from Alias, Buck 65, Cecil Otter, and Reanimator.

title: Give the Drummer Some
summary: The Blink-182 drummer releases his debut solo album, featuring collaborations with RZA, Lupe Fiasco, Lil Wayne and others.

title: The Crawling Distance
summary: The first of six planned albums from Ex-Guided By Voices singer Robert Pollard (and his other side projects) for 2009.

title: Life Processes
summary: The sophomore release for the band from Leeds was produced by Matt Bayles.

title: Fluorescence
summary: This is the fourth full-length studio album for the indie quartet.

title: Talk That Talk
summary: The Barbados-born singer's sixth studio album features guest appearances by Calvin Harris and Jay-Z.

title: Greendale
summary: Credited to Neil Young & Crazy Horse (expect electric rather than acoustic), this latest offering by the 57-year-old rocker is a 10-song concept album about the lives of the fictitious Green family.

title: The Blueprint 2: The Gift & the Curse
summary: A sequel to his critically-acclaimed 2001 album 'The Blueprint,' Jay-Z's new two-disc set is all over the map in the course of 110 minutes and 25 tracks. The roster of producers and guests includes (but is by no means limited to): The Neptunes, Lenny Kravitz, Big Boi, Dr. Dre, Timbaland, Heavy D, Rakim, Beyonce Knowles, Faith Evans,  Notorious B.I.G. and Scarface.

title: Big TV
summary: The changing dynamics of the relationship between a small town couple when they move to the big city is the concept behind the third full-length release for the British rock band led by Harry McVeigh.

title: We Started Nothing
summary: The single "Shut Up and Let Me Go" from the debut album for the British duo was used in an Apple commercial.

title: Lost Highway
summary: Nashville producer Dann Huff helmed Bon Jovi's first album-length stab at country-rock. LeAnn Rimes and Big & Rich guest.

title: Caveman
summary: The second release for the New York indie band was produced by Nick Stumpf.

title: Distortland
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the alternative rock band was recorded in Courtney Taylor's basement on cassette before being mixed by Jim Lowe.

title: All Around Us
summary: The second full-length release for the Seattle artist was recorded in Iceland with producer Alex Somers.

title: Reality Check
summary: The debut album for the French indie-pop trio based in London, England.

title: True Romance
summary: The end of the British artist's four-year relationship was an influence on her fourth full-length release.

title: Forever So
summary: The debut full-length album for the Australian folk quartet was produced by Noah Georgeson.

title: Careless World: Rise of the Last King
summary: The second album for the Compton, California, rapper features guest appearances by Busta Rhymes, Nicki Minaj, Nas, Robin Thicke, and Wale.

title: Poor Moon
summary: This is the debut full-length release from the side project of Fleet Foxes members Christian Wargo and Casey Wescott.

title: Traps
summary: The third album for the indie pop band from Milwaukee (who previously were called Jail) was recorded in the basement of lead singer Vinnie Kircher.

title: Portrait of an Ugly Man
summary: The third full-length release for the Minnesota emo band was produced by lead singer, Erik Paulson.

title: Sinematic
summary: The first solo release from The Band guitarist since 2011's How To Become Clairvoyant was inspired in part by his work on the score for Martin Scorsese's The Irishman and features contributions from such artists as Doyle Bramhall II, Citizen Cope, Glen Hansard, DJ Howie B, Van Morrison, and Derek Trucks.

title: Kubrick
summary: The second release for the British electronic duo is an instrumental album inspired by Stanley Kubrick's films.

title: Rodeo
summary: The debut full-length studio release for Houston hip-hop artist features guest appearances from  2 Chainz, Justin Bieber, Chief Keef, Juicy J, Swae Lee, Quavo, Toro y Moi, The Weeknd, Kanye West, and Young Thug.

title: Vicissitude
summary: The third full-length release from indie electronic artist James Chapman was self-recorded.

title: Gordian
summary: This is the second full-length release for the Berlin-based Romanian techno producer.

title: In Animal Tongue
summary: This is the third album for the Carla Bozulich-led project under the name Evangelista.

title: The  Appeal: Georgia's Most Wanted
summary: The third studio release for the rapper features guest appearances by Bun B, Swizz Beatz, Ray J, Nicki Minaj, Pharrell, Wyclef Jean, and Estelle.

title: No Guts. No Glory.
summary: The Australian rock band formed by brothers, Joel and Ryan O'Keeffe releases its second full-length studio album.

title: Everything's The Rush
summary: The third album for the British four-piece group is their first on the Fiction label.

title: Music Is My Savior
summary: This debut for New York rapper Shawn Mims--which includes his hit single "This Is Why I'm Hot"--was produced by Miami's Blackout Movement.

title: The Emancipation Of Mimi
summary: The singer wrote many of the songs appearing on 'Mimi,' and even produced one cut, with the remainder of the production duties falling to Jermaine Dupri, the Neptunes and Kanye West. Also appearing are Nelly, Twista and Snoop Dogg.

title: The Richest Man in Babylon
summary: The Washington D.C.-based production duo of Rob Garza and Eric Hilton are back with their third proper LP, following 2000's 'The Mirror Conspiracy.' Like its predessor, 'Babylon' is a multicultural mix of down-tempo instrumentals and vocal tracks, with Pam Bricker, Lou Lou, Notch, Emiliana Torrini, Sleepy Wonder and Shinehead providing the voices.

title: Til The Casket Drops
summary: Pharrell Williams returns to produce (and also guest on) the rap duo's third album.

title: My December
summary: The singer's third disc was produced by David Kahne and features an unlikely contribution on bass from Mike Watt (The Minutemen).

title: AmeriKKKant
summary: The 14th full-length studio release for the industrial metal band led by Al Jourgensen is its first without guitarist Mike Scaccia, who passed away in 2012.

title: Where the Messengers Meet
summary: The Seattle indie rock quartet returns with its sophomore disc less than two years after debuting its self-titled album.

title: Last Light
summary: The seventh album for the indie rock band.

title: Blood Red Shoes
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British duo was self-produced and recorded in Berlin.

title: Blue Film
summary: The debut full-length release for the Los Angeles artist Matthew Hemerlein was written and recorded while traveling between his parents house in Maryland, Nashville, Asia, and Europe.

title: Battle Studies
summary: The singer-songwriter's latest album was co-produced with Steve Jordan.

title: Lift Your Spirit
summary: The third full-length solo release for the retro-soul singer features production from DJ Khalil, Theron Feemster, Rock Mafia, and Pharrell Williams.

title: Introducing Joss Stone
summary: Despite the title, this is the third album for the young British soul singer. Raphael Saadiq produces, with Lauryn Hill and Common guesting.

title: Yours to Discover
summary: The pop-influenced second solo release for the Death from Above 1979 drummer/singer is his first in five years.

title: Rituals
summary: This is the full-length debut for the rock band formed by former M83 member Nicolas Fromageau.

title: Ye
summary: The seven-track release from the rapper was streamed live from Wyoming and featured guest appearances from 070 Shake, DeJ Loaf, Jeremih, Kid Cudi, John Legend, Nicki Minaj, PARTYNEXTDOOR, Ty Dolla $ign, Valee and Charlie Wilson.

title: Endless Wire
summary: The legendary band's first studio album since 1982 includes a full version of their mini-opera "Wire & Glass," which was recently released (appropriately enough) as a mini-album.

title: Simulation Theory
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the British rock band was produced by Rich Costey, Mike Elizondo, Shellback, and Timbaland. The deluxe and super deluxe editions feature alternate versions of several of the album's tracks.

title: CCCLX
summary: The debut full-length release for the Montreal electronic producer features guest appearances from Syv De Blare, Denzel Curry, CJ Flemings, J.K. The Reaper, King Mez, Le1f, Mike Dean, Nell, Sophie, and Speng.

title: Motorizer
summary: The British heavy metal band releases its latest album, produced with Cameron Webb.

title: Thumbtacks and Glue
summary: The sixth full-length release from the Canadian folk-pop band led by Mark Andrew Hamilton was produced by Arran Fisher.

title: Love Is a Four Letter Word
summary: The fourth album from the singer-songwriter was produced by Joe Chiccarelli.

title: Songs of Experience
summary: The 14th full-length studio release for the Irish rock band was delayed after recent political changes in the world caused the band to change it from being a planned companion album to the more personal Songs of Innocence to a more political one.

title: Hitting The Ground
summary: The Violent Femmes' leader emerges with his very first solo release some 20 years after that band's formation. Here, Gano is joined by a star-studded cast that includes John Cale, They Might Be Giants, Mary Lou Lord, Lou Reed, Linda Perry, PJ Harvey and Frank Black.

title: C'mon C'mon
summary: Sheryl Crow's fourth album features guest appearances from Emmylou Harris, Don Henley, Lenny Kravitz, Liz Phair and Stevie Nicks.

title: Sound of a Woman
summary: The debut full-length release for Canadian artist features guest appearances from Mick Jenkins and Joey Bada$$.

title: The Dangermen Sessions, Vol. 1
summary: The veteran "nutty" ska band's first album since their 1999 reunion disc 'Wonderful' is a collection of 13 covers, including their takes on classics "Lola" and "Israelites."

title: Golden
summary: The 14th full-length studio release for the Australian pop artist features influences from country music, with three tracks recorded in Nashville and a guest appearance from Jack Savoretti.

title: There's A Fire
summary: John Leckie produced this second major-label release for the now five-member New York band led by Steve Schiltz.

title: Honey
summary: The third full-length release for the British pop singer  features guest appearances from such artists as Craig David, Floating Points, Four Tet, Geeneus, Kaytranada, Major Lazer, and Novelist.

title: Some Loud Thunder
summary: Dave Fridmann produced the acclaimed indie band's second LP, which again is self-released in the U.S.

title: Straight No Chaser
summary: The second album for the British singer was produced with Kanye West, who also appears as a guest artist.

title: Do The Bambi
summary: This is the first Kill Rock Stars release for the Berlin-based pop duo of Francoise Cactus and Brezel Goring.

title: Scatter the Rats
summary: The first studio release in 20 years for the Los Angeles grunge/punk band was produced by Norm Block and Nick Launay.

title: Chroma
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was produced by Dan Carey.

title: Purpose
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Canadian pop singer features guest appearances from Big Sean, Diplo, Halsey, Travis Scott, and Skrillex.

title: Gardens & Villa
summary: The debut album for the Santa Barbara-based indie pop band was produced by Richard Swift.

title: Teenage Emotions
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the Atlanta rapper features guest appearances from Diplo, Evander Griiim, Grace, Migos, Stefflon Don, and YG.

title: Heavy Blanket
summary: J Mascis formed the band in high school with Pete Cougar and Johnny Pancake, however due to unfortunate circumstances they did not record together until reunited in 2011.

title: Erotic Reruns
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Brooklyn experimental rock band the was self-recorded and produced.

title: Wicked Nature
summary: The sixth full-length release for the Australian alternative rock band led by Craig Nicholls was funded through PledgeMusic and co-produced with Paul McKercher.

title: Scream
summary: Ozzy's is a scream heard around the world. The former Black Sabbath frontman returns with his 10th studio album of menacing heavy metal.

title: The Colossus
summary: The fourth full-length album for the producer-DJ better known to the general public as the creator of the "Mad Men" theme (an edited version of his instrumental track "A Beautiful Mine.").

title: Emoh
summary: Although the former Folk Implosion and Sebadoh member has recorded solo discs before under the name Sentridoh, 'Emoh' marks his first release under his own name. It includes six home-recorded tracks as well as eight new studio cuts recorded with producers Mark Nevers, Josh Schwartz and Wally Gagel.

title: All The Way
summary: The Brooklyn duo releases its first album under the Social Registry label.

title: Waiting For The Sirens' Call
summary: The veteran Manchester band's latest disc was produced by Tore Johansson and John Leckie, and sees touring guitarist Phil Cunningham becoming an official full-time band member, replacing departed keyboardist Gillian Gilbert.

title: Back To Light
summary: Tim Simenon returned after nearly 15 years to his Bomb The Bass name in 2008 and for his second album, works with Gui Boratto and features vocals from Depeche Mode's Martin Gore.

title: Made In China
summary: The rocker's latest solo record is the first for her new label, Ye Olde Records.

title: Mistake, Mistake, Mistake, Mistake
summary: Electronica artist and producer Jimmy Tamborello (who is 1/2 of the Postal Service, 1/3 of Figurine, and 1/1 of Dntel) returns with a solo album of minimal techno under yet another name, with Erlend Oye, John Tejada and Jenny Lewis minimally guesting.

title: Babel
summary: The second release for the folk band was produced by Markus Dravs.

title: American Central Dust
summary: Jay Farrar returns to Son Volt to release the band's sixth album.

title: Widow's Weeds
summary: The fifth full-length release for the Los Angeles alternative rock band was produced by Butch Vig.

title: truANT
summary: This sophomore disc for the Southern California alt-metal outfit was produced by Robert and Dean DeLeo of the Stone Temple Pilots.

title: Three-Four
summary: This disc compiles tracks from three previously-released EPs by the indie rock trio, who originally got their start composing music for NPR's "This American Life." Also included are three brand-new tracks.

title: Tropical Storm
summary: Jamaican dancehall artist Beenie Man returns with a bid for crossover stardom, utilizing hip-hop producers such as The Neptunes, and even dueting with Janet Jackson on one track.

title: Golden State
summary: This is the fourth long-player for Gavin Rossdale and Bush, and was produced by Dave Sardie (Slayer, Marilyn Manson).

title: The  Speed of Things
summary: The second full-length release for the Detroit electronic pop duo was produced with Ben West.

title: Girl Talk
summary: Produced by Tom Biller, the third full-length release for the British singer moves toward an indie rock direction.

title: Lonely Avenue
summary: Singer-songwriter Ben Folds and English novelist Nick Hornby collaborate to create an album featuring the piano compositions and musical arrangements of Folds and the words of Hornby.

title: Grace Potter & the Nocturnals
summary: Mark Batson produced the third album for the Vermont-based rock group. It is the first with new members, Catherine Popper and Benny Yurco.

title: Last of Our Kind
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British rock band led by Justin Hawkins was produced by guitarist Dan Hawkins.

title: California
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the pop-punk band was produced by John Feldmann and is the first with Alkaline Trio's Matt Skiba, who replaced Tom DeLonge.

title: Sam Sparro
summary: This is the debut album for the son of gospel singer Chris Falson.

title: Picture Show
summary: The second studio album for the rock band from Utah was produced by Justin Meldal-Johnsen.

title: Identified
summary: The star of "High School Musical" releases her latest album, produced in part by JR Rotem, Dr. Luke, Tim James, and Antonina Armato.

title: Black Acetate
summary: A bit more rock-oriented than its predecessor, 'Acetate' is nevertheless another experimental effort from the now-63-year-old Cale.

title: Detour
summary: The pop singer-songwriter covers country songs for her 11th full-length studio release with guest appearances from Vince Gill, Emmylou Harris, Jewel, Alison Krauss, and Willie Nelson.

title: It's About Time
summary: The first Chic album in over 25 years features guest appearances from Cosha, Craig David, Danny L Harle, Lady Gaga, LunchMoney Lewis, Vic Mensa, Mura Masa, NAO, Philippe Saisse, Emeli Sandé, Hailee Steinfeld, and Stefflon Don.

title: Drift
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Brooklyn post-punk band was recorded with Travis Harrison.

title: Revolutions
summary: The roster of guests for the turntablists' fourth LP includes Cypress Hill, dead prez, Ghostface Killah, Black Thought (The Roots), Slug (Atmosphere) and Blue Man Group.

title: Printz
summary: This U.S. debut disc for the genre-mashing Australian brother-sister duo of Chris and Vila Colonna (who appended the "81" to their name to avoid conflicts with a similarly-named children's music band) combines tracks from their EP "White Printz" and their UK single "Red Printz."
Album number five finds the singer-songwriter seemingly entering an early mid-life crisis, as she dives headfirst into commercial teen-dance-pop territory.

title: Red Letter Days
summary: The fourth album from Jakob Dylan & Co. includes lead single "When You're on Top" and a bonus cover of Elvis Costello's "(What's So Funny 'bout) Peace, Love & Understanding." Long-time guitarist Michael Ward has left the group, leaving room for Pearl Jam's Mike McCready to provide some of the lead guitar on the album.

title: We Are A & C
summary: The third U.S. release for the eclectic Amsterdam-based duo (following 2001's import-only release 'Sound Shopping') contains 14 equally eclectic tunes, including highlights "Dirty Robot" and "5th Dimension."

title: We Are Young Money
summary: The collaboration project from Lil Wayne features Drake, Guycci Mane, Lloyd, Tyga, Shanell, Birdman, Shawt Dawg, Nicki Minaj, T-Streets,  Lil' Chuckee, Lil' Twist, Jae Millz, Gudda Gudda, and Mack Maine.

title: Wasteland, Baby!
summary: Te second full-length release for the Irish singer-songwriter features a guest appearance from Mavis Staples.

title: Everybody's Dying To Meet You
summary: The second full-length release for the British indie pop trio was produced by Brian O'Shaughnessy.

title: Dark Black Makeup
summary: The debut full-length release for the punk trio of brothers from Missouri was produced by Ross Orton.

title: Galapagos
summary: This is the second release for the British rock band led by Simon Critten.

title: Kiss
summary: The second studio album from the Canadian vocalist features Justin Bieber and Owl City.

title: Forget Tomorrow
summary: You wouldn't know it from their album covers, or their music, but this indie-rock four-piece hails from Athens, Georgia, not Tokyo. 'Tomorrow' is their third full-length and first in five years (four, if you include their collaboration with Bedhead).

title: Yesterday Was Forever
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was funded from a Kickstarter campaign.

title: Purple Noon
summary: The fourth full-length release for Atlanta-based chillwave producer Ernest Greene was mixed by Ben H. Allen.

title: Rewolf
summary: The fourth full-length album for the New York City-based band features reworkings of some of its previously released songs.

title: Didn't It Rain
summary: Joe Henry returns as producer for the second jazz/blues release for actor-singer Hugh Laurie.

title: Hands All Over
summary: In 2008, Maroon 5 released a remix album with the help of several different DJs and producers. The group then spent most of the following two years working with a different producer -- famous rock/country-pop architect Robert John "Mutt" Lange -- on Hands All Over, which marked the band's third studio offering of rhythmic, soulful pop songs.

title: Chuck
summary: The Canadian punk-pop outfit returns with a fourth LP, produced by Greig Nori. The disc is named after a UN worker (Chuck Pelletier) who helped the band escape violence in the Congo while they were there shooting a film.

title: Amerikaz Nightmare
summary: The duo of Prodigy and Havoc are assisted by guests such as 50 Cent, Nate Dogg, R. Kelly, Jadakiss and Nelly on this disc co-produced by The Alchemist.

title: Vehicles & Animals
summary: This debut disc for the South London, England quartet (originally released in the UK in 2003) was produced by Victor Van Vugt (Beth Orton) and gained a Mercury Music Prize nomination.

title: Let It Rain
summary: On her sixth studio album, the singer-songwriter works with producer John Parish (PJ Harvey) for the first time.

title: The Age Of Miracles
summary: The latest album for the Grammy-winning singer-songwriter features Vince Gill and Alison Krauss as guest singers.

title: Funny Looking Angels
summary: The Editors lead singer Tom Smith and former Razorlight drummer Andy Burrows team up to release an album of classic and original Christmas songs.

title: Here We Go Again: Celebrating the Genius of Ray Charles
summary: Willie Nelson and Wynton Marsalis return to work together on this Ray Charles tribute with Norah Jones recorded in February 2009 at the Rose Theater.

title: The Bright Lights Of America
summary: The ninth album for the quartet from Pittsburg, Pa., was produced by Tony Visconti.

title: Breathing Statues
summary: The second full-length release for the Brooklyn trio-turned duo of Isaac Emmanuel and Melati Malaywas was recorded while on tour.

title: Beat The Devil's Tattoo
summary: With new drummer Leah Shapiro (who replaced Nick Jago), the rock band from San Francisco works to mix its rock side with the country/acoustic sound it revealed in 2005's Howl.

title: As U Were
summary: The latest album for the Bay area hip-hop artist features guest appearances by Lateet, Sam Sparro, Joyo Velarde, Trackademicks, Clyde Carson, The Gift, and Francis and the Lights.

title: Julian Plenti Is... Skyscraper
summary: Interpol's Paul Banks releases his debut solo album under the name Julian Plenti.

title: Version
summary: The second artist album from the acclaimed DJ and producer (Amy Winehouse, Lily Allen) is filled with covers, as Ronson takes on works by artists as diverse as Radiohead, The Smiths, Britney Spears, Coldplay and Ryan Adams. Both Winehouse and Allen guest, along with Robbie Williams, Phantom Planet and Kasabian.
This is the fourth LP for the underground rap trio of Evidence, Rakaa and DJ Babu.

title: Through the Night
summary: Ren Harvieu is the latest British singer to release a debut album influenced by the sounds of the 1960s.

title: LP
summary: Vampire Weekend's Rostam Batmanglij and Ra Ra Riot's Wes Miles team up to release their first album together.

title: Wildflower
summary: This is the singer's first album in three years.

title: Only By The Night
summary: The fourth album for the rock band from Tennessee was produced by Angelo Petraglia and Jacquire King.

title: All Delighted People EP
summary: Before the October 12th release of Sufjan Steven's full length album The Age of Adz, the artist released this eight-track EP as a digital download.

title: Songs for Our Mothers
summary: Drugs, murder, and abusive relationships are some of the dark subjects of the second full-length release from the British band.

title: The Devil You Know
summary: The members of Black Sabbath (without Ozzy Osboune) return as Heaven & Hell to release its first album under the name.

title: I'm with You
summary: The California rock band releases their 10th album produced by Rick Rubin and the first since 2006 and with new guitarist Josh Klinghoffer, who replaced John Frusciante.

title: Stranger
summary: The third full-length studio release for the Swedish rapper was recorded in Miami and was produced by Yung Gud, Yung Sherman and White Armour.

title: Say Yes!: A Tribute to Elliott Smith
summary: The latest tribute release to the singer-songwriter features covers of his songs by such artists as Julien Baker, Lou Barlow, Tanya Donelly, William Fitzsimmons, Swervedriver's Adam Franklin, Juliana Hatfield, Jesu/Sun Kil Moon, J. Mascis, Amanda Palmer, Wild Sun, Waxahatchee, and Yuck.

title: Glow & Behold
summary: The British indie rock band returns as a trio for its second studio release after lead singer Daniel Blumberg left the band to pursue his own music.

title: VII
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Portland, Oregon-based experimental folk band is its first on the Vagrant label.

title: The Curse Of Blondie
summary: 'Curse' marks the eighth studio album for Deborah Harry & co., and their first since their 1999 comeback effort 'No Exit.'

title: The Fire Theft
summary: Former Sunny Day Real Estate members Jeremy Enigk, William Goldsmith and Nate Mendel make their debut as The Fire Theft with this 13-track disc, co-produced by Brad Wood.

title: Learning From Falling
summary: Who is Lamya? Born in Africa, educated in England, and later residing in the U.S., she is a classically-trained opera singer who embarked on a pop career, first serving as lead vocalist for Soul II Soul and later as a backup singer for Duran Duran and David Bowie. For this solo debut, she wrote, produced, and composed each of the 12 tracks.

title: Satan's Circus
summary: The duo's fourth album departs from previous outings, taking an all-instrumental (and guitar-free) approach rather than relying on guest vocalists. Think Kraftwerk and you won't be too far off.

title: Yes, It's True
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the indie choral pop band Tim DeLaughter was co-produced with Eric Drew Feldman and Tim Palmer.

title: Fly Yellow Moon
summary: The debut album for the Guillemots singer-songwriter was produced by Adam Noble .

title: Sun, Sun, Sun
summary: Rilo Kiley's Blake Sennett returns with a sophomore set for his side project, The Elected. Contributors include members of Eisley and Bright Eyes, as well as Rilo Kiley bandmate Jenny Lewis.

title: Double Up
summary: Apparently no longer trapped in the closet, the crooner enlists Young Jeezy, Snoop Dogg, Ludacris and T.I. to help enliven this upbeat successor to 2005's 'TP.3 Reloaded.'

title: The Glass Passenger
summary: The sophomore album for the rock band started by Something Corporate's Andrew McMahon.

title: Global Warming
summary: Christina Aguilera, Chris Brown, Enrique Iglesias, Jennifer Lopez, The Wanted, and Usher are some of the guests on the seventh studio album for the Miami rapper.

title: Recovery
summary: Eminem continues his forward momentum with confrontational, angst-ridden rap that digs deep into the psyche on his new album.

title: Stand Up
summary: 'Stand Up' is the band's first studio album in three years and finds them working for the first time with producer Mark Baston (50 Cent, Beyonce).

title: Keep the Village Alive
summary: The ninth full-length studio release for the Welsh alternative rock band led by Kelly Jones was produced with Jim Lowe.

title: There Is a Way

title: Kratitude

title: Ripples

title: Killer Sounds

title: Listening Tree

title: Welcome
summary: This is the debut album for the Spokane, Washington, artist discovered by Peanut Butter Wolf.

title: I Am...Sasha Fierce
summary: The third solo album for the ex-Destiny's Child singer features songs attributed to her alter ego Sasha Fierce.

title: Rock N Roll Jesus

Surprisingly (for a FSOL album), there's guitar, vocals, strings, and harmonica, and trippy song titles such as "The Mello Hippo Disco Show."

title: Law and Order
summary: The solo debut release for the Foxygen member includes contributions from Tim Presley of White Fence.

title: Armed Love

title: Untitled
summary: The latest solo album for the R&B singer features Keri Hilson, Rock City, Tyrese, Robin Thicke, and The-Dream as guest singers.

title: Eclipse

title: Trials & Truths
summary: The second full-length release for the Oklahoma indie rock band led by Cameron Neal was produced by Thom Monahan.

title: Honkey Kong

title: In the Lonely Hour
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the British neo-R&B singer-songwriter.

title: Happiness Ltd.
summary: The Canadian band's third studio album.

title: How Does It Feel

title: Freedom of Speech

title: The Dream

title: Paralytic Stalks

title: Tomorrow's World

title: In Your Dreams

title: R.O.O.T.S

title: The Best Little Secrets Are Kept

title: Free Somehow

title: Go With Me
summary: The debut album for the Seattle indie rock trio was recorded at their home.

title: The Good Feeling Music of Dent May & His Magnificent Ukulele

title: Panic Movement

title: Beg For Mercy

White produced this debut LP, which was mixed by Mercury Rev's Dave Fridmann. And why the album title? According to the band's website, "We all love rabbits."

title: The Listener

title: Slicker Than Your Average
summary: The 21-year old DJ turned-international R&B superstar from England returns with his second LP.

title: Oh Land
summary: This is the Danish singer-songwriter's second full-length album.

title: The Sun And The Moon
summary: Brendan O'Brien produced this second album for the New York band.

title: I Am the West

title: Blame It on Baby

title: 1000 Palms
summary: The third full-length release for the indie rock band was self-recorded and produced.

title: The Other Side of Zero
summary: The Brooklyn rock trio worked on its album for only one month with producer Tony Berg.

title: Free Your Mind And Win A Pony
summary: The debut album for the duo from Baltimore and Sweden.

title: Hey People!
summary: This is the debut album for the four-piece garage-rock band fronted by Kpt.Michi.Gan's Michael Beckett.

title: Draw The Line
summary: The latest album for the British singer-songwriter was produced by the artist himself.

title: Do Things
summary: The ukulele is absent from the second album for the singer-songwriter from Mississippi.

title: I Am Not a Dog on a Chain
summary: The 13th full-length solo release for The Smiths frontman was produced by Joe Chicarelli.

title: XI Versions of Black Noise
summary: The remix album of the electronic artist's 2009 album features production by such artists as Animal Collective, Four Tet, and Moritz Von Oswald.

title: Love + Fear

title: Two
summary: This is the second album from the French electronic artists.

title: Alphabutt
summary: One half of The Moldy Peaches returns with her latest album of funny children's tunes.

title: Thankful

This hit debut album is a direct result of the singer's victory on the first installment of Fox TV's "American Idol" talent competition in 2002. Judging from the album's credits, just about every musician and producer in the industry seemingly worked on the disc, although Clarkson did manage to co-write four out of the dozen songs.

title: Do You Know Squarepusher

Included among the seven new tracks here (totaling just 35 minutes) is an unexpected cover of Joy Division's "Love Will Tear Us Apart."

title: The Great Depression
summary: The fourth album for east coast rapper sees Black Key and DMX himself taking over the production reins from Swizz Beatz on all but two tracks.

title: Wake Up And Smell The Coffee
summary: Yes, apparently they ARE still around. This is the Irish group's sixth album since 1993, and their first with original producer Stephen Street in some time.

title: Someday World
summary: The collaborative release from Brian Eno and Karl Hyde was produced by Eno and Fred Gibson.

title: Fall to Grace
summary: The second studio release for the British singer was produced by Nellee Hooper and Jake Gosling.

title: Turning the Mind
summary: James Chapman releases his follow up to his Mercury Music Prize-nominated album, "We Can Create."

title: Blood
summary: The band's thrid album, "Tonight" is dub remixed by producer Dan Carey.

title: Cyr
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the alternative rock band was produced by the band's frontman, Billy Corgan.

title: Robotique Majestique

title: A New Testament
summary: The second full-length solo release for the former Girls frontman was recorded with producer Doug Boehm.

title: Encyclopedia

title: High Expectations
summary: The debut full-length studio release for the daughter of Neneh Cherry  includes production from MNEK, Steve Mac, and Fraser T Smith.

title: Duck
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the British indie rock band was produced with Ben H. Allen and Andrew Wells.

title: Death Race for Love
summary: The second full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from Clever, Brent Faiyaz and Young Thug.

title: Staying at Tamara's
summary: The second full-length release for the British singer-songwriter features a guest appearance from First Aid Kit.

title: Desire
summary: This is the fourth full-length release for the British synth-pop duo of Theo Hutchcraft and Adam Anderson.

title: Little Victories
summary: This is the second full-length release for the Irish rock quartet was produced by Charlie Russell and Bradley Spence.

title: Chapter & Verse
summary: The seventh full-length release for the Welsh post-hardcore band was produced by Lewis Johns.

title: Shady XV
summary: The Detroit rapper returns with an album of new songs from artists on the Shady label including Bad Meets Evil, D12, Obie Trice, Slaughterhouse, and YelaWolf.

title: No Romeo
summary: The debut full-length release for British pop singer Lauren Henson was produced by John Beck.

summary: Dylan Ross of Cursive joins the Los Angeles electronic group formed by Danny and Tiffany Preston on their second full-length release.

title: Den
summary: The 11th album for the German experimental electronic band is only seven tracks long.

title: New Relics
summary: The eight-track album follows the Scottish trio's third album, Have Some Faith In Magic, released earlier this year.

title: Orangefarben
summary: The second full-length album for Julie Ann Baenziger as Sea of Bees was written after a breakup.

title: Emperor's Nightingale
summary: The British duo's seventh album continues its move toward electronic and rock music.

title: The R.E.D. Album
summary: The long delayed 21-track album for the Los Angeles rapper features guest turns from Dr. Dre, Kendrick Lamar, Snoop Dogg, Lil Wayne, Sly, Drake, Rick Ross, Beanie Sigel, Young Jeezy, Big Boi, E-40, Lloyd, Mario, Wale. Chris Brown, Nelly Furtado, and Tyler, the Creator.

title: Moonfire
summary: The debut full-length release for the indie band from Australia was recorded in Nashville with producer Joe Chiccarelli.

title: Heaven and Earth
summary: The last album for the British singer-songwriter who passed away in 2009 includes one song written by Phil Collins.

title: The Goldberg Sisters
summary: The latest project for actor Adam Goldberg is the first under this name. He previously released an album under the LANDy name.

title: The  Impossible Song & Other Songs

title: Burn Your Town
summary: This is the debut album for the English rock quartet who share the same last name.

title: The Optimist
summary: The British band self-produced its follow-up to its  2007 debut "Fantastic Playroom."

title: Flowers
summary: The latest album for the Chicago band led by Tim Kinsella.

title: On Your Sleeve
summary: The fourth album for the singer is a release of cover songs produced by Diane Gentile.

title: Nine Lives
summary: His first album in five years, Steve Winwood's ninth studio effort features nine songs, including one with guitar work by Eric Clapton.

title: Audio Day Dream
summary: The American Idol runner-up releases his debut album.

title: Amputechture

title: The Preacher's Son
summary: Wyclef's fourth solo disc finds Patti LaBelle, Missy Elliott, Buju Banton, Redman, Carlos Santana (among others) making contributions.

title: Get The Picture
summary: The fourth album for the Bay Area band finds them once again in light, summertime pop mode.

title: Quicken The Heart
summary: The third album for the English indie rock quintet.

title: Boys and Diamonds
summary: The husband-and-wife duo releases its debut full-length album of African and Middle Eastern-influenced music.

title: 22-20s
summary: Brendan Lynch produced this debut for the English blues-rock band, who are named after a Skip James song.

title: We Can Do Anything
summary: This is the first full-length studio release in 16 years for the band led by Gordon Gano and Brian Ritchie with Dresden Dolls' Brian Viglione taking over on drums from Victor de Lorenzo.

title: I Had the Blues But I Shook Them Loose
summary: The debut album for the British rock quartet was produced by Jim Abbiss.

title: Surgery
summary: The L.A. psych-rock band's third disc was produced by Tom Rothrock (Beck).

title: PlectrumElectrum
summary: One of two Prince albums released on the same day, it features the all-female trio 3rdEyeGirl.

title: Ghost Stories
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the alternative rock band led by Chris Martin was influenced in part by Martin's relationship with Gwyneth Paltrow.

title: Don't You
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the New York trio of Kelly Zutrau, Joe Valle, and Marty Sulkow.

title: Soft Control
summary: The full-length debut release for the British pop artist features contributions from Babydaddy, Amanda Ghost, Robin Hannibal, Emile Haynie, Dev Hynes, John Legend, and Johnny Rockstar.

title: Unapologetic
summary: The seventh studio release for the pop singer features Chris Brown, Eminem, Future, and David Guetta as guests with No I.D., Nicky Romero, StarGate, and The-Dream contributing to production.

title: Walk It Off
summary: The sophomore album for the indie rock quartet from Minnesota was produced by Dave Fridmann.

title: Black Panties
summary: The R&B singer's 12th full-length studio release features guest appearances from 2 Chainz, Ludacris, Kelly Rowland, and Young Jezzy.

title: How to Get To Heaven From Scotland
summary: This is the debut album for the rock quartet led by Aidan Moffat.

title: Human Conditions
summary: This is the second solo outing for the former Verve frontman.

title: Music for Courage and Confidence
summary: This covers album from the former American Music Club leader includes versions of songs by everyone from Culture Club ("Do You Really Want To Hurt Me?") to Glen Campbell ("Gentle on My Mind").

title: Under Rug Swept
summary: Morissette's third studio album is the first one the 27-year-old Canadian songwriter has produced herself.

title: In Space
summary: The band's first studio LP in 30 years features the most recent touring lineup of original members Alex Chilton and Jody Stephens with Posies Jon Auer and Ken Stringfellow.

title: Sleep Through The Static
summary: The singer from Hawaii returns with his latest album, which was recorded on solar-powered equipment.

title: The Difference Between Houses And Homes: Lost Songs And Loose Ends 1995-2001
summary: This disc compiles 10 tracks from the Tim Kasher-led band's early 7-inch singles, and adds two previously unreleased cuts.

title: Edward Sharpe & the Magnetic Zeros
summary: The third full-length release from the band led by Alex Ebert was partially recorded at the same time as 2012's Here.

title: A List of the Burning Mountains
summary: The 12th full-length studio release for the Brooklyn rock group consists of two nearly 20-minute long tracks.

title: Global
summary: This greatest hits/mix disc by the German DJ/producer includes two previously unreleased tracks. The accompanying DVD, culled from over 40 hours of footage, is part travelogue and part behind-the-scenes documentary of Van Dyk in action.

title: The  Sound of the Life of the Mind
summary: The fourth studio album for the indie rock band is its first release of new music in 13 years.

title: The Mix-Up
summary: Money Mark guests on this all-instrumental, post-punk-influenced, 12-track set for the veteran hip-hop outfit.

title: Here We Stand
summary: This is the sophomore album for the Scottish indie rock band.

title: Doo-Wops and Hooligans
summary: The Hawaiian-born producer's move to making pop music as a solo artist has proven successful, as his new album is an innovative mix of tribal beats, reggae, and club-worthy jams that show his range as a songwriter.

title: The Seven Autumn Flowers
summary: Robert Wratten (Field Mice) is joined by singers Beth Arzy and Anne Mari on this fifth TBS release.

title: Meteorites
summary: The 12th studio release for the British band led by Ian McCulloch was produced by Youth.

title: Victorious
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Australian hard rock band led by Andrew Stockdale was produced by Brendan O'Brien.

title: The Ascent
summary: The ninth studio release for the British grime artist features guest appearances from such artists as  Far East Movement, French Montana, Ghetts, Kano, Lethal Bizzle, Ms D, Emeli Sandé, Tinchy Stryder, and Tulisa.

title: Break the Spell
summary: Howard Benson returns to produce the third full-length album for the band led by former American Idol contestant, Chris Daughtry.

title: Destroyed
summary: Described by Moby himself as a "soundtrack for empty cities at 2 a.m.," the electronic artist's 10th album was recorded while on tour.

title: Mirror Eye
summary: The second full-length album for the New York experimental rock band.

title: Emotional Technology
summary: This is the fourth album for house music producer Brian Transeau, who has faded from the limelight a bit since his heyday in the mid-to-late 1990s, although has produced hits for the likes of Britney Spears and *NSync. Collaborators here include Rose McGowan, Scott McCloud (Girls Against Boys), and Guru (Gang Starr).

title: Discipline
summary: Janet Jackson's 10th album features Ne-Yo and Missy Elliot.

title: In The Maybe World
summary: Johnny Marr guests on the singer-songwriter's first album in three years and her first disc for the Young God label.

title: Grand Romantic
summary: The debut solo release for the Fun. frontman was produced by Jeff Bhasker and Emile Haynie.

title: NYC
summary: Four Tet's Kieren Hebden and drummer Steve Reid team up for the fourth time on this album about New York City.

title: The Friends [EP]
summary: The Pennsylvania band releases the EP in advance of a full studio album in the fall.

title: Primus & the Chocolate Factory with the Fungi Ensemble
summary: The tribute to the 1971 film Willy Wonka & the Chocolate Factory from the San Francisco Bay Area-based band sees the return of Tim Alexander on drums.

title: Bangerz
summary: Executive produced with Mike Will Made It, the hip-hop-influenced fourth studio release (and her first on the RCA label) for the former Disney star features guest appearances from Big Sean, French Montana, and Britney Spears.

title: LotusFlow3r
summary: After releasing Planet Earth for free in the United Kingdom, the singer-songwriter's three albums (one by new artist Bria Valente) are packaged together as a Target store exclusive in the United States.

title: We'll Live and Die in These Towns
summary: Formally known as The Bridges, the British band returns with a label, a new name, and a new album.

title: Left
summary: Ken Thomas (Sigur Ros) produced this sophomore effort for the anthemic UK rockers.

Can he do it again? Coming a full three years after his surprise megahit 'Play,' this new album from Richard Melville Hall attempts to repeat that disc's success with (surprise) 18 new tracks, including collaborations with Angie Stone, Sinead O'Connor, Azure Ray and MC Lyte.

title: Help Wanted Nights
summary: Originally conceived as a solo project for Cursive's frontman Tim Kasher, the Omaha band now releases its fourth album.

title: Still Got That Hunger
summary: The sixth overall release from the 60s' British psychedelic rock band is its second since reforming in 2011 and was funded via Pledge Music.

title: OX 2010: A Street Odyssey
summary: Cannibal Ox's Vast Aire releases his latest solo album.

title: Blackout
summary: Britney newest release includes tracks written by T-Pain and Pharrell Williams.

title: Dignity
summary: This is the third album for the actress/pop star.

title: Solarized
summary: The fourth solo disc for the former Stone Roses singer includes a collaboration with Noel Gallagher.

title: Yours Truly, Angry Mob
summary: Stephen Street produced the British band's second album, which follows their acclaimed 2005 debut 'Employment.'

title: Polly Scattergood
summary: The debut album for the English singer, who attended the BRIT school (other famous alumni include Amy Winehouse, Leona Lewis, and Adele.)

title: These Systems Are Failing
summary: The 13th full-length studio release for the electronic artist is the first credited under the name Moby & The Void Pacific Choir.

title: We The Best Forever
summary: The LA-based band releases its sophomore full-length of noise-driven, psychedelic rock.

title: Ruins

title: Secrets Are Sinister

title: Sleep Mountain
summary: The second full-length album for the Danish band was produced by Peter Katis.

title: Blood for the Master

title: Clothes Drop
summary: The Black Eyed Peas' will.i.am guests on the dancehall star's sixth studio album.

title: You Can Feel Me
summary: Picture a white man singing R&B. Picture a white man singing R&B while stripping down to his underwear. Picture an average-looking, slightly pudgy white man singing R&B while stripping down to his underwear. That's Har Mar Superstar, and this is his second album.

title: Charango
summary: The English trip-hop outfit's fourth studio album features unlikely guest vocal appearances from rapper Slick Rick and Lambchop's Kurt Wagner.

title: Modulate
summary: Indie rock legend Bob Mould (Hüsker Dü, Sugar) returns with his fifth solo album, and first for his brand new record label (Granary Music). In another first, Mould delves into electronica for the first time as well, abandoning traditional instruments for synths and computers on half of the album.

title: You & I

title: Later...When the TV Turns To Static

title: Futuristically Speaking...Never Be Afraid

title: Brass Knuckles

title: Walking On A Dream
summary: The debut album for the Australian band formed by The Sleepy Jackson's Luke Steele and Pnau's Nick Littlemore.

title: Lissy Trullie
summary: The debut full-length release for the indie rock band was produced by Bernard Butler.

title: Curses
summary: Dave Grohl produced this fourth album for the emo-rockers.

title: Dirty Words
summary: This is the '80s alternative rock-influenced debut disc for the Northampton, England band.

title: Wasted on the Dream
summary: Nashville duo Jake and Jamin Orrall release their eighth album on their own label, Infinity Cat.

title: Surrender
summary: The third full-length release for the British duo was produced by Jonas Quant.

title: Postcards from Paradise

title: Red Carpet Massacre

title: First Kiss
summary: The tenth studio release for the Detroit singer was self-produced.

title: The Orbserver in the Star House
summary: Electronic producers, The Orb teams up with reggae producer Lee "Scratch" Perry on this release.

title: World Wide Rebel Songs

title: Expektoration (Live)

title: My Guilty Pleasure
summary: The second album for the Swedish electronic artist was produced with Johan Agebjorn.

title: Birthmarks
summary: The third full-length studio release for the Canadian rock band led by Luke LaLonde was produced by Roger Leavens.

title: Malice N Wonderland
summary: The latest album for the rapper features such guests as Brandy, The Dream, R. Kelly, Pharrell, and Soulja Boy.

title: The Last DJ
summary: The latest from Tom Petty is a concept album (or diatribe, if you will) about/against the domination of popular music by large, greedy corporations. It was released on October 8, 2002 by a large, greedy corporation.

title: The Carnivorous Lunar Activities Of Lupine Howl
summary: Featuring former members of Spiritualized (who were fired by Jason Pierce before the recording sessions for 'Let It Come Down'), Lupine Howl offers up nine tracks on this debut album, including previously-released singles "Vaporizer" and "125."

title: Return Of Dragon
summary: This is actor-singer Sisqo's sophomore effort, following his 1999 debut 'Unleash The Dragon.' (Sense a pattern here?) Teddy Riley produced the lead single, "Can I Live."

title: A New Tide
summary: The sixth album for the British indie-rock band was produced with Brian Deck.

title: Rainbow Edition

title: Big Mess

title: Distortion

title: Dynamics
summary: This is the second release for the Brooklyn duo of Alex Frankel and Nick Millhiser.

title: The Last Kiss
summary: The rapper's first release in five years features guests such as Mary J. Blige, Nas, Styles P, Ghostface Killah, Raekwon, Ne Yo, Lil Wayne, Young Jeezy, Pharrell, and Faith Evans.

title: My Mind Makes Noises
summary: The debut full-length release for the British indie pop band led by Heather Baron-Gracie was co-produced by The 1975's Matty Healy and George Daniel (as well as Jonathan Gilmore and the band's drummer  Ciara Doran).

title: Timez Are Weird These Days
summary: The Brooklyn-based rapper makes his major-label debut, with producers Dave Sitek and John Hill.

title: ...Ya Know?
summary: Joan Jett and Steven Van Zandt guested on Joey Ramone's second posthumously released solo album that includes demos and unreleased recordings.

title: Human Bell
summary: This is the debut album for the side project of David Heumann, lead singer of Arboretum and Lungfish's bass player Nathan Bell.

title: The Return Of Dr. Octagon
summary: Kool Keith's second Dr. Octagon album follows a full decade after his first, with production this time handled by One Watt Sun.

title: Out Of Nothing
summary: The fourth album for the Britpop band includes a track ("Gravity") co-written by Coldplay's Chris Martin.

title: Howling... It Grows And Grows!!!

title: Stills
summary: The second full-length release from the Denver band formed by Andy Rauworth and Craig Nice was produced by Jacob Portrait.

title: Galore

title: Spine Hits

title: A.M.
summary: This is the debut full-length album for Swervedriver's Adam Franklin and Interpol's Sam Fogarino.

title: Glorious
summary: The debut full-length release for British pop singer-songwriter  Louisa Rose Allen, who won a Grammy for her work on Zedd's Clarity.

title: Tim Robbins and the Rogues Gallery Band
artist: Tim Robbins & the Rogues Gallery Band
summary: The Oscar-winning actor and his backing band release an album of folk rock tunes.

title: Fasciinatiion
summary: The first album released on their new label Blank.wav was written and produced by the band.

title: T.I. Vs T.I.P.

title: Prism
summary: The fourth studio release for the pop singer includes production from Dr. Luke, Greg Kurstin, Max Martin, StarGate, and Greg Wells.

title: Bicycles & Tricycles
summary: Yes, for those of you keeping score at home, Alex Paterson is indeed still recording as The Orb, with 'Bicycles' marking the once trailblazing electronica group's sixth studio release.

title: Hopes And Fears
summary: Yes, you'll see the word "Coldplay" in nearly every review for this debut disc, but the UK trio stand out from the crowd with their unconventional lineup of vocals, drums, and piano.

title: Bounce
summary: Just when you feared the New Jersey hair band would never release another album, they did. Oh joy.

title: Mechanical Wonder
summary: The fifth album from the British rockers is their first U.S. release in five years.

title: The Fabled City
summary: The sophomore solo album for Rage Against the Machine's Tom Morello was produced with Brendan O'Brien.

title: When It Was Now
summary: This is the full-length debut release for the Adelaide, Australian indie pop band.

title: Pacifica
summary: The first release in four years for the Australian electro-pop duo of Julian Hamilton and Kim Moyes.

title: War Stories
summary: The electronic duo's new album includes guests such as Josh Homme (Queens of the Stone Age), Ian Astbury (The Cult), The Duke Spirit, and Autolux.

title: The Art of Love and War
summary: The fourth album for Stone was recorded at Marvin Gaye's original LA studio.

title: Living Things
summary: Personal relationships influenced the lyrics on the fifth album produced with Rick Rubin for the alternative rock band.

title: Glee: The Music, Volume 1
summary: The soundtrack features songs from the first season of the TV show.

title: Entertainment
summary: The New York duo's third album was produced with Jeff Saltzman.

title: Stone Temple Pilots [2018]
summary: The second self-titled release for the alternative rock band is the first to features former The X Factor contestant Jeff Gutt as its lead singer.

title: The Oracle

title: Miley Cyrus & Her Dead Petz
summary: The surprise release from the pop singer was a collaboration with the Flaming Lips' Wayne Coyne.

title: Kings & Queens
summary: The Chicago-based outfit led by Neil Rosario and Mark Henning return with a Prince-esque sophomore set.

title: Thank You
summary: The first new full-length studio release in more than 20 years for the artist known as Queen of Motown was produced with Jack Antonoff.

title: Peaceful, The World Lays Me Down
summary: This is the debut album for the British quartet led by Charlie Fink.

title: Sixes & Sevens
summary: The fifth solo album for the Moldy Peaches member.

title: Corazón

summary: This is the debut full-length studio album for the Canadian electronic artist.

summary: The second album from Nicki Minaj focuses on her male alter ego Roman Zolanski and features guest appearances from 2Chainz, Chris Brown, Beenie Man, Bobby V, Cam'ron, Drake, Lil Wayne, Nas, Rick Ross, and Young Jeezy.

summary: The band return with their first new material in 28 years.

summary: The 11th studio release for the electronic artists features guest appearances from Inyang Bassey, Cold Specks, Wayne Coyne, Skylar Grey, Damien Jurado, and Mark Lanegan.
