title: Fixin' The Charts, Volume One
artist: Everybody Was In The French Resistance...Now
summary: The latest concept album from Art Brut's Eddie Argos and Blood Arm's Dylan Valdes consists of 12 pop responses, such as "Billie's Genes," where a grown-up child responds to Michael Jackson's "Billie Jean."

title: The E.N.D.
summary: The Black Eyed Peas return to release its first studio album in five years.

title: Future This
summary: The second album for the British duo was produced by Paul Epworth.

title: No Hope, No Future
summary: This is the second album for English rock quartet and its first with its new bass player.

title: Welcome To Goon Island
summary: Formerly known as the Xerox Teens until the copy company came calling, the British quintet releases their first full-length.

title: The Soul Sessions, Vol. 2
summary: The British soul singer releases her second set of soul covers produced with Steve Greenberg.

title: Daybreak
summary: The emo rock band from New Jersey releases its seventh studio album, the first without guitarist David Soloway.

title: Dusk And Summer
summary: Chris Carrabba & co.'s long-delayed fourth album was produced chiefly by Don Gilmore, after sessions with Daniel Lanois were largely scrapped. Counting Crows' Adam Duritz guests.

title: Thecontrollersphere
summary: The Georgia quintet releases a five-song EP of indie-folk, recorded during the False Priest album sessions.

title: What Happens Next
summary: The ninth studio release for the British post-punk band (with Andy Gill the only remaining original member) features guest appearances from Gail Ann Dorsey, Alison Mosshart, and Herbert Gronemeyer.

title: Non-Fiction
summary: The sixth full-length release for the R&B artist was produced by Dr. Luke and features guest appearances from Candice, David Guetta, Jeezy, Charisse Mills, Schoolboy Q, and T.I.

title: Calling the World
summary: Produced by John Fields (Andrew W.K., Switchfoot) is Rooney's followup to their self-titled debut.

title: Peace And Love
summary: Hatfield moves toward a more acoustic sound for her self-produced 10th studio release.

title: Splinter
summary: This is the seventh album for these Orange County alt-rockers.

title: Black Letter Days
summary: Recorded direct to two-track, 'Black Letter Days' features a stripped-down sound for the former Pixie and his current band. And if the 18 new tracks here (including not one but two covers of Tom Waits' "The Black Rider") aren't enough for you, there's even more on the companion release, 'Devil's Workshop.'

title: Some Nights
summary: The band's first album on the Fueled By Ramen label was produced by Jeff Bhasker and features Janelle Monae on its single We Are Young.

title: A  Joyful Noise
summary: Brian Higgins produced the fifth album for alternative rock band led by Beth Ditto.

title: Dead Drunk
summary: This is album number three for the side project band for Animal Collective's Dave Portner (aka Avey Tare) and Black Dice's Eric Copeland.

title: Breaking Up
summary: 'Breaking Up' is the English trio's debut album.

title: Gavin DeGraw
summary: The sophomore studio album for the artist best known for the theme song from the TV series "One Tree Hill."

title: Thank You
summary: Executive produced by Ricky Reed, the second full-length major studio release for the pop singer-songwriter feature guest appearances from LunchMoney Lewis and Yo Gotti.

title: Y Not
summary: The latest solo album for the Beatles drummer features Paul McCartney on the track "Walk With You," as well as guest vocals from Joss Stone, Ben Harper, and Richard Marx.

title: When Your Heart Stops Beating
summary: This is the first release for the new project from blink-182's Travis Barker and Mark Hoppus.

title: The Ride
summary: The second full-length release for the Welsh alternative rock band was produced by Dave Sardy.

title: American Standard
summary: The singer-songwriters latest full-length release features some musical and jazz standards from such shows as Breakfast at Tiffany’s, Brigadoon, Guys and Dolls, Oklahoma!, and Show Boat as well as songs made famous by Billie Holiday and Glenn Miller.

title: Music and Words
summary: British visual artist David Shrigley's words were turned into music by Arab Strap co-founder Malcolm Middleton in this collaboration that also features Bridget McCann, Gavin Mitchell, and Scott Vermeire.

title: Storytone
summary: The deluxe two-disc set from the singer-songwriter features one disc with a 92-piece orchestra and choir plus a disc of solo versions of the same songs.

title: Labrinth, Sia & Diplo Present LSD
summary: Delayed from its planned November 2018 release, this 10-song set marks the first collaborative album from the new "supergroup" consisting of British musician Labrinth, singer-songwriter Sia, and proudcer Diplo.

title: Symphonica
summary: A collection of ten covers and seven original songs from the pop singer's 2011-12 orchestral tour.

title: Patience
summary: Patience is indeed a requirement for fans of the former Wham! member, as this is just his fourth solo album of original material and first in eight years.

title: X
summary: X marks the veteran English arena-rock band's tenth album.

title: Music Kills Me
summary: The French electronica duo Rinocerose gained notice for their 1999 debut 'Installation Sonore.' This sophomore effort features 12 new tracks of guitar-infused house.

title: Chops
summary: Gorky's Zygotic Mynci frontman Euros Childs makes his solo debut with this 14-song effort.

title: Decent Work For Decent Pay
summary: The Grammy-nominated (for producing M.I.A.'s "Paper Planes") DJ Wesley "Diplo" Pentz releases his latest remix album, featuring works from a variety of indie-rock bands such as Bloc Party, CSS, and Spank Rock.

title: The Remedy
summary: The second album for the British singer was produced by Flood.

title: Sheezus
summary: The third studio release for the British pop singer was produced by DJ Dahi, Greg Kurstin, and Shellback.

title: Under The Boards
summary: The rock band latest album is the second in a planned triology.

title: Invaders Must Die
summary: The first album for the electronic duo in four years features Dave Grohl and James Rushent as guest musicians.

title: Smoke + Mirrors
summary: The second full-length release fro the Las Vegas rock band was produced with Alex Da Kid.

title: In a World Like This
summary: The eighth studio release for the pop group is its first with Kevin Richardson since he left the group in 2006 and also includes production from Max Martin, Morgan Taylor Reid, and Martin Terefe.

title: The Third Hand
summary: The hip-hop producer attempts a "pop" album for the first time on this third release, utilizing all live instrumentation and even singing on almost all of the tracks.

title: Black Ghosts
summary: The British duo of Theo Keating and Simon Lord releases their first full-length album together.

title: Casino Twilight Dogs
summary: The Australian band's second album was produced by Wayne Connolly (The Vines) and includes their cover of Alphaville's "Forever Young."

title: Year Of The Dog... Again
summary: The rapper's sixth album includes production work from Scott Storch and Swizz Beatz.

title: The Complex
summary: The multimedia collective known as the Blue Man Group, who can be seen and heard in ongoing theatrical productions in several cities, in television commercials for Intel, and even on a previous instrumental album 'Audio,' have released here something akin to a real rock'n'roll album. Their assortment of invented instrumentation is now accompanied by more traditional instruments, and vocals are provided by an array of guests, including Dave Matthews, Spalding Gray and Tracy Bonham. Included also are covers of "White Rabbit" and "I Feel Love."

title: Devil's Workshop
summary: One of two simultaneous releases (Black Letter Days being the other), Devil's Workshop is perhaps the more straightforward of the pair, although like its companion it was recorded direct to 2-track, representing a back-to-basics approach for Black and Co.

title: Reanimation
summary: Not quite the next Linkin Park album, 'Reanimation' is instead a remix of their entire debut album, 'Hybrid Theory' (actually, a remix of the Japanese version, which contained extra tracks). The 19 songs here have been reinvented by an array of alternative and hip hop musicians and producers, including members of Korn, Jurassic 5, Orgy, and Staind, and given cryptic new titles such as "Rnw@y" and "My{Dsmbr." (You'd think with all the money they're making they could at least buy a vowel.)

title: Threes
summary: This is the third album for project that began as a spin-off from At The Drive-In but has since lost founding guitarist Paul Hinojos (who is replaced for this album with Denali's Keeley Davis).

title: Morning Tide
summary: The debut album for the indie pop band from California.

title: Jackie
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the R&B singer features guest appearances from Missy Elliott and Pitbull (as well as Joe Jonas on the Deluxe edition).

title: Satellite Flight: The Journey to Mother Moon
summary: Originally an EP, the 10-track album was a surprise midnight release for the hip hop artist.

title: Paley & Francis
summary: Black Francis and Reid Perry worked together on an album produced by Jon Tiven.

title: Lucky Old Sun
summary: The latest album for the multiple award-winning country singer features guest appearances by Dave Matthews, Mac McAnally and Willie Nelson.

title: St. Jude
summary: The debut album for the British quartet was produced by Stephen Street.

title: Release Therapy
summary: Kanye West, Pharrell Williams and Timbaland are among the producers on the rapper's fifth disc, which also includes appearances by Nelly and R. Kelly.

title: Inherit
summary: This is the third album for the band led by Sonic Youth's Kim Gordon and Pussy Galore's Julie Cafritz.

title: Secondhand Rapture
summary: This is the debut full-length debut for the New York duo of Lizzy Plapinger and producer Max Hershenow.

title: Own the Night
summary: The Nashville country music trio releases their third studio album.

title: We Sing, We Dance, We Steal Things
summary: The third album for the San Diego-based singer-songwriter includes songs that first appeared on three EPs.

title: Red
summary: This is the sophomore album for the British indie pop rock band led by Fyfe Dangerfield.

title: Strangeland
summary: Dan Gtech produced the fourth studio album for the British rock quartet that sees the band returning to emotional, piano-based songs.

title: Space Settings
summary: 'Space Settings' is the debut from the hip-hop side project for Jimmy Tamborello (Postal Service, Dntel), who along with Plug Research artists Allen Avanessian, Daedelus and John Tejada (plus Thomas Fehlmann), provides the musical backdrop for an array of MCs that includes Beans and Rocmon.

title: Glass Floor
summary: This is the full-length debut from the four-piece consisting of Dismemberment Plan bassist Eric Axelson, former Promise Ring members Davey von Bohlen and Dan Didier, and Jawbox founder J. Robbins.

title: Night On Fire
summary: The Louisville, KY retro-electronica outfit, who drew numerous Daft Punk comparisons with their 2002 EP 'Le Funk,' have transitioned into a dance-punk sound with this full-length debut.

title: Merry Christmas II You
summary: The second Christmas album for the pop singer includes four new songs and a rerecording of her 1994 Christmas song "All I Want for Christmas is You."

title: A Better Tomorrow
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the rap group was executive produced by RZA and is its first in seven years.

title: Ices
summary: The third full-length release from the now Northern-California-based singer-songwriter was produced by Benny Sagittarius and Clams Casino.

title: Ancient Mars
summary: This is the second release for the Canadian indie rock duo of Tom Dobrzanski and Zach Gray.

title: There's Me And There's You
summary: This is the second album for the artist under the Matthew Herbert Big Band name.

title: Tangerine Reef
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the experimental pop band is an audiovisual album developed in collaboration with Coral Morphologic and is its first without Panda Bear.

title: Bye Bye 17
summary: Sean Tillmann's fifth full-length release was co-produced with Jim Eno and recorded with a full band.

title: Start and Complete
summary: Alexis Taylor of Hot Chip fame leads this group of innovative, improvisational electro-pop on their second release.

title: Fantasy Ride
summary: The third album for the Atlanta, Georgia singer features guest appearances by Missy Elliot, Justin Timberlake, The-Dream, Ludacris, Chris Brown, and Young Jeezy.

title: Disgraceland
summary: The second full-length release for the Chicago quintet includes production from Dave Sitek, Chris Coady, and Jim Abbiss.

title: Now What
summary: The singer's second solo disc includes six tracks co-written with Linda Perry as well as a cover of Don Henley's "Dirty Laundry."

title: The Adventures Of Ghosthorse And Stillborn
summary: The experimental folk-rock duo of Brooklyn-based sisters Sierra and Bianca Casady return with a third album.

title: Talking To You, Talking To Me
summary: Hailing from Los Angeles by way of Kentucky, Chandra and Leigh Watson--aka the Watson Twins--follow up 2008's "Fire Songs" with "Talking to You, Talking to Me." It features members of Everest and My Morning Jacket's Bo Koster.

title: Razorlight
summary: Chris Thomas (U2, Pulp) produced this brief, self-titled follow up to the Johnny Borrell-led band's 2004 debut 'Up All Night.'

title: Mink Car
summary: The band's first major release since 1996's 'Factory Showroom' features 17 new recordings (including some songs that originally appeared on 1999's self-released 'Long Tall Weekend.').

title: Drops Of Jupiter
summary: This is the major-label debut for the San Francisco adult alternative band.

title: TP.3 Reloaded
summary: A thematic departure from his 2004 double album, TP.3 includes appearances from Snoop Dogg, The Game, Twista and Nivea.

title: The Past Presents The Future
summary: Marc Bianchi's latest album of electronica-infused indie-pop was recorded in "extreme isolation" in California.

title: We Can't Fly
summary: This is the first and final album for the DJ/producing duo of Vita Deluca and Stephen Fasano. Aeroplane became a solo project for Deluca after Fasano's amicable departure in June.

title: Paul McCartney: Ocean's Kingdom
summary: The Beatle was commissioned by the New York City Ballet to compose the score for the romance between a water princess and a land-based prince.

title: Folker
summary: No, it's not a folk album, but Westerberg does handle all of the instruments himself on this latest solo release. (We suppose that it's hard to find replacements for The Replacements.)

title: Grey Oceans
summary: The French-based sister duo releases its first album on Sub Pop records after the previous three were released by Touch and Go Records.

title: Trilla
summary: The Florida rapper's sophomore album includes guest appearances by Jay-Z, R. Kkelly, Nelly, Lil Wayne, and T-Pain.

title: Temper Temper
summary: Don Gilmore returns to produce the fourth studio release from the Welsh metal band.

title: American Soul
summary: The former frontman of Simply Red pays tribute to American 1960s soul music with this 12-track covers release.

title: thefearofmissingout
summary: The second full-length album for the group led by Dhani Harrison features guest appearances from Ben Harper, The Black Knights, Throunn Antonia, Holly Marilyn, and RZA.

title: Darkly, Darkly, Venus Aversa
summary: The UK metal legends return to their roots on their ninth album, which takes a dark mythic tale of demons and doom and turns it into haunting black metal musical configurations.

title: Ritual
summary: Alan Moulder produces the British alternative rock trio's second album.

title: Magna Carta Holy Grail
summary: The rapper's 12th studio album (released five days early to Samsung mobile device owners via an app) features Rick Ross, Justin Timberlake, Beyonce Knowles, and Frank Ocean, with production from Timbaland, Jerome "J-Roc" Harmon, and others.
Yes, this is indeed LL Cool J's tenth album, which includes guest appearances from P. Diddy, Amerie, and Dru Hill, and production from The Neptunes and Trackmasters.

title: Full Moon
summary: This is the third album for the now-23-year-old singer (and former Cinderella). Rodney Jerkins handles most of the production chores on this 17-track disc.

title: V
summary: The fifth album for Pennsylvania alt-rockers features a guest appearance from Tricky. "Forever May Not Be Long Enough," the theme song from this summer's "The Mummy Returns," also appears on the album.

title: Tha Carter IV
summary: The ninth studio album from the rapper features special guests such as Drake, T-Pain, and Rick Ross.

title: It's Me Again
summary: The R&B singer's first album in three years was produced by Missy Elliott.

title: Everything at Once
summary: The eighth full-length studio release for the Scottish rock band features a guest appearance by Josephine Oniyama.

title: The Buffet
summary: The 13th full-length studio release for the R&B artist features guest appearances from his 17-year-old daughter Ariirayé, Jhené Aiko, Jeremih, Juicy J, Lil Wayne, Tinashe, and Ty Dolla $ign.

title: Generation Freakshow
summary: The eighth studio album for the Welsh rock band was produced by Chris Sheldon and lead singer Grant Nicholas.

title: This Kind Of Love
summary: Carly Simon releases her latest album on the Starbuck's new music label, Hear Music.

title: Songs About Girls
summary: The Black Eyed Peas member releases his third solo album, which features Snoop Dogg on one track.

title: Key
summary: Omaha, Nebraska multi-instrumentalist Joe Knapp returns with his second Son, Ambulance full-length, now backed by a full band.

title: Timeless
summary: The legendary Brazilian artist makes a Santana-style comeback for his first album in eight years, teaming with the Black Eyed Peas' will.i.am and a variety of pop, hip-hop and R&B stars, including Erykah Badu, Justin Timberlake, Jill Scott, Black Though, John Legend and more.

title: Revelations
summary: Brendan O'Brien produced this third release for the Chris Cornell-led band.

title: I Can Spin a Rainbow
summary: This is the full-length debut collaboration between Dresden Dolls' Amanda Palmer and The Legendary Pink Dots' Edward Ka-Spel.

title: Lessons In Love
summary: The third album for the R&B artist features a guest appearance by Lil Wayne.

title: City
summary: Martin Gore and members of The Libertines guest on the electro-pop duo's second effort.

title: You Gotta Go There To Come Back
summary: The Welsh band self-produced this fourth studio album.

title: American Life
summary: Madonna's second collaboration with French electronic producer Mirwais includes the lead single title track as well as her recent James Bond theme, "Die Another Day."

title: Dirty Dancing
summary: The London-based electronica duo move toward a darker, dirtier, more electroclash-oriented sound on this third studio album.

title: Song Yet To Be Sung
summary: This is the debut solo release for former Jane's Addiction/Porno For Pyros frontman Perry Farrell. Many of the tracks are more electronic in nature than his previous output with the two bands. Dave Navarro, Jon Brion, and the Mad Professor are among the guest contributors.

title: A Head Full of Dreams
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the British alternative rock band was produced by Rik Simpson and Stargate with guest appearances from Beyoncé, Merry Clayton, Noel Gallagher, Tove Lo, Gwyneth Paltrow, and Annabelle Wallis.

title: Limits of Desire
summary: The second full-length release for the Brooklyn synth-pop band led by Josh Kolenik was self-produced.

title: Back On My B.S.
summary: The first album on the Universal Motown label for the rapper features guest artists such as Lil Wayne, Jadakiss, T. Pain, Pharell, Akon, T.I., Estelle, Mary J Blige, J. Foxx, J. Legend, and Common.

title: Love Hate And Then There's You
summary: The third studio album for the band is its first on the Majordomo label.

title: Fearless Love
summary: The multiple-award winning singer-songwriter works with producer John Shanks on her latest album, which also features vocals from Joss Stone and Natasha Bedingfield.

title: Killing Time
summary: The first full-length album for the punk pop rock band that includes members from the indie pop band Magic Bullets.

title: Stars Dance
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Disney actress/singer is her first as a solo artist and includes contributions from The Cataracs, Desmond Child, Ester Dean, Mike Del Rio, Dreamlab, David Jost, The Monsters and the Strangerz, Rock Mafia, and Stargate.

title: 55 Cadillac
summary: The fourth album for the California-born artist features solo piano pieces.

title: Low in High School
summary: The 11th full-length solo release for the British indie rock singer-songwriter was produced by Joe Chiccarelli.

title: All Wet
summary: The sixth full-length release from French filmmaker/electronic producer Quentin Dupieux features guest appearances from Boys Noize, Charli XCX, Mocky, Peaches, Phra, Siriusmo, Skrillex, and Tetanos.

title: Out Of The Vein
summary: The third album for the radio-friendly San Francisco-based alt-rockers is almost a concept album about breaking up with Charlize Theron, which--lest you think the band was getting wacky all of a sudden--band leader Stephan Jenkins actually did do recently.

title: Deathsentences of the Polished & Structurally Weak
summary: Part book, part CD, this latest effort from the Bay Area collective was inspired by a trip to an auto junkyard. The jokes, satire, and subversion found in previous releases is absent this time around, instead replaced by a collection of letters and writings found in the auto wrecks presented in a 64-page full-color book, and, on the CD, a lyric- and melody- free noise assault that, as the band suggests, is the sound of their studio being destroyed in a car crash.

title: Happy People
summary: This is the second full-length release for the British indie rock band led by Harry Koisser.

title: Tides End
summary: Produced by Mark Verbos, the second full-length release for Shaun Kilfoyle became a solo project after Amalie Bruun left to join Ex Cops.

title: Majenta
summary: Sexual themes continue to dominate the third release for the Detroit producer/photographer/electronic artist.

title: Rolling Papers
summary: The debut from the Pittsburgh rapper features the biggest-selling hip-hop single of 2010, Black and Yellow--a track that became the unofficial anthem for the Steelers in Super Bowl XLV.

title: Bigger Love
summary: The seventh full-length studio release for the R&B singer-songwriter features guest appearances from Jhené Aiko, Camper, Gary Clark Jr., Koffee, and Rapsody

title: Father Of Asahd
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the rapper features guest appearances from 070 Shake, 21 Savage, J Balvin, Beyoncé, Justin Bieber, Big Sean, Buju Banton, Chance the Rapper, Chris Brown, Cardi B, Future, Gunna, Jay-Z, Jeremih, Jeezy, John Legend, Lil Wayne, Lil Baby, Mavado, Meek Mill, Nas, Nipsey Hussle, Post Malone, Quavo, Rick Ross, Travis Scott, Sizzla, and SZA.

title: In Plain Sight
summary: The third full-length release for the indie rock project from Stina Tweeddale was produced by John Congleton.

title: Simple Minds Acoustic
summary: The first acoustic album for the Scottish rock band features a guest appearances from KT Tunstall.

title: Heavy Entertainment Show
summary: The 11th full-length studio release for the British pop singer features songs written with such artists as Brandon Flowers, Serge Gainsbourg, Jewel, The Killers' Dave Keuning, Ed Sheeran, and Rufus Wainwright.

title: Powerballin'
summary: Janet Jackson, Nate Dogg and R. Kelly guest on the St. Louis rapper's second album.

title: Land Air Sea
summary: Originally self-released in March 2003, 'Land Air Sea' returns in 2004 in a resequenced and remixed version (on Epitaph) for this side project from members of Weezer and Rocket From The Crypt.

title: Trinity (Past, Present and Future)
summary: The Detroit hip-hop trio returns with a sophomore LP, following a well-received 2000 debut album. Founding member Jay Dee is no longer with the group (and has been replaced by rapper Elzhi), although he guest produces three tracks.

title: This Way
summary: The singer-songwriter's third album contains 12 new studio tracks and two bonus live tracks.

title: Malpractice
summary: Redman's long-delayed fifth album was produced by Erick Sermon and features 23 new tracks. Guests include George Clinton, Missy "Misdemeanor" Elliott, Method Man, and Scarface.

title: Grrr...
summary: This is the third full-length for the Brooklyn, New York, indie-rock band.

title: Uncanney Valley
summary: The first release in 12 years for the Washington DC rock quartet led by Travis Morrison was produced by the band's guitarist, Jason Caddell.

title: Stay Together
summary: The sixth full-length studio release for the British rock band was produced by Brian Higgins.

title: Something for the Rest of Us
summary: The Goo Goo Dolls worked with several producers--including Butch Vig, Tim Palmer, John Fields, and Rob Cavallo--on the ninth studio album for the rock band from Buffalo, New York.

title: So Amazin'
summary: Young Jeezy and the Three 6 Mafia guest on the R&B singer's third album.

title: New Danger
summary: 'New Danger' is the second solo hip-hop album (and Geffen debut) for the rapper and actor.

title: Education, Education, Education & War
summary: The fifth studio release for the rock band was produced by Ben H. Allen III and is its first without Nick Hodgson who left in December 2012 (Vijay Mistry takes over on drums).

title: Getting Over the Storm
summary: The second release with new lead singer Duncan Campbell for the reggae band includes covers of country classics as well as five original tracks.

title: Cosy Moments
summary: The sixth full-length release for the Seattle rock band is its first in over five years and its debut on the Kill Rock Stars label.

title: Roses
summary: Stephen Street produces the first album for the Irish rock band since 2001's Wake Up and Smell the Coffee.

title: Never Cry Another Tear
summary: This is the debut album for the rock band formed by three members of New Order, Jake Evans, and Blur's Alex James appears as a guest.

title: Under The Covers Vol. 2
summary: Sid 'n Susie (Matthew Sweet and Susanna Hoffs) team up together once again to cover the music of the 1970s.

title: Nostradamus
summary: Rob Halford leads the metal band's latest release, a concept album based on the prophet Nostradamus.

title: Welcome To The Dollhouse
summary: The sophomore album for MTV's "Making the Band 3" group features Missy Elliot on one track.

title: A Drink & A Quick Decision
summary: The second album from the UK duo.

title: Everyday I Said A Prayer For Kathy And Made A One Inch Square
summary: The Massachusetts band--now down to the duo of Scott Levesque (vocals, guitars) and Brendan Harney (drums)--returns with their first album in four years.

title: Hello Waveforms
summary: This is the artist/producer's first solo album in six years. Finley Quaye and the Sugababes guest.

title: Man Vs Machine
summary: This is the fourth album from the successful West Coast rapper.

title: Pain Is Love
summary: Released after a string of successful singles and albums (including 2000's 'Rule 3:36' LP), 'Pain Is Love' features contributions from Jennifer Lopez, Missy Elliott, and 2Pac.

title: Glitter
summary: Originally due in August 2001, Mariah Carey's debut for Virgin Records was delayed due to the singer's recent hospitalization, stemming from a nervous breakdown. It is her first album since 1999's 'Rainbow,' and it serves as the soundtrack to the movie of the same name (a 1980s period-piece also starring Carey). The disc includes two covers: "I Didn't Mean To Turn You On" and "Last Night a DJ Saved My Life."

title: Delta
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the British folk rock band was produced by Paul Epworth.

title: Lightning
summary: The fourth release for Brooklyn duo was self-produced and recorded in their former apartment in New York.

title: Dead Son Rising
summary: The album of songs that grew from unused demos from his previous works was produced by Ade Fenton.

title: New Eyes
summary: The debut full-length release for the British quartet known for its fusion of classical and electronic music features guest appearance from artists such as Jess Glynne, Love Ssega, Stylo G, and Elisabeth Troy.

title: This Unruly Mess I've Made
summary: The second full-length release for the hip hop duo features guest appearances from such artists as Anderson .Paak, Leon Bridges, Chance The Rapper, DJ Premier, Idris Elba, KRS-One, Kool Moe Dee, and Ed Sheeran.

title: In The Dark
summary: The third album for the Athens, Georgia rock band was produced with Ben Allen and  features new bassist Tim Deaux.

title: Recess
summary: The debut full-length release for the Grammy-winning electronic artist includes guest appearances from Chance the Rapper, Diplo, Ragga Twins, and Alvin Risk.

title: No Mercy
summary: Written while serving his nearly year-long stint in federal prison, the Atlanta rapper’s seventh studio album features contributions from Kanye West, Drake and others stars.

title: Born Villain
summary: The eighth studio album from Marilyn Manson was produced with Chris Vrenna.

title: America's Sweetheart
summary: The (we hope) ironically-titled 'America's Sweetheart' marks the solo debut for the former Hole leader, who co-wrote this album with Linda Perry and Elton John lyricist Bernie Taupin.

title: Counterfeit 2
summary: The Depeche Mode songwriter's second solo album is just like his first (1989's 'Counterfeit'): all covers. Here, he tackles Brian Eno's "By This River," The Velvet Underground's "Candy Says" (oh my), Nick Cave's "In My Time of Dying," Iggy Pop's "Tiny Girls," and seven other works by your favorite artists.

title: Level II
summary: The newly-reformed Teddy Riley creation returns with its fourth album.

title: Storytelling OST
summary: The Glasgow band's fifth album serves as the soundtrack to the Todd Solondz film of the same name--in theory, that is, as only a few minutes of this new material is actually used in the movie (in fact, much of the album was recorded after the movie was released). However, as with a typical soundtrack album, expect snatches of dialogue and numerous instrumental tracks interspersed with fully-developed songs.

title: Judgement Days
summary: This is the U.K. rapper's second album.

title: Ultra Payloaded
summary: The debut album for Perry Farrell's new band includes contributions from Peter Hook, Fergie, Thievery Corporation, Flea and John Frusciante.

title: Early 21st Century Blues
summary: The Canadian band's latest includes two originals and nine covers, including versions of songs by U2, Bob Dylan and Bruce Springsteen.

title: Let's Go Sunshine
summary: The fifth full-length release for the British indie pop band led by Luke Pritchard was produced by Brandon Friesen and Chris Seefried.

title: >Album Title Goes Here<
summary: The latest release from the Canadian electronic producer features guest appearances from Cypress Hill, Wolfgang Gartner, Imogen Heap, Chris James, and Gerard Way of My Chemical Romance.

title: Silesia
summary: The Swedish post-rock band blends ambient melodies with orchestral-like arrangements on its third release.

title: Liverpool 8
summary: Ringo returns to Capitol Records to work with long-time producer Mark Hudson. But after a falling out, David A. Stewart, formerly of the Eurythmics, ends up finishing the record.

title: Young Adults Against Suicide
summary: This is the debut LP for the Toronto indie-rap collective (excuse us, the "positive hardcore dance-rap band") led by Matt Collins.

title: Girl Who Got Away
summary: The fourth studio release for the British singer-songwriter was co-produced with her brother Rolo Armstrong and includes contributions from such artists as Brian Eno, Greg Kurstin, Kendrick Lamar, and Rick Nowels.

title: On My One
summary: The third full-length release for the British indie singer-songwriter features three songs co-produced with Jacknife Lee.

title: 200 Years
summary: This debut album is the collaboration between Ben Chasny of Six Organs of Admittance and Elisa Ambrogio of Magik Markers.

title: The Meth Lab
summary: The first full-length solo release for the Wu-Tang rapper in nine years features guest appearances from Carlton Fisk, Donny Cacsh, Chedda Bang, Dro Pesci, Eazy Get Rite, Hanz On, Hue Huf, Inspectah Deck, iNTeLL, Kash Verrazano, Killa Sin, Masta Killa, Mack Wilds, Raekwon, Redman, Streetlife, and Uncle Murda.

title: Lights And Sounds
summary: The emo-pop-punk-with-violin outfit expands their sound for their second major-label release. The Dixie Chicks' Natalie Maines guests.

title: LP1
summary: The UK singer-songwriter releases her fifth studio album of soulful songs, produced by Dave Stewart.

title: All At Once
summary: The Los Angeles quintet release their second album of indie folk rock.

title: Beta Love
summary: Produced by Dennis Herring, the third studio release for the New York indie band  shows a more synth pop sound on its first album without cellist Alexandra Lawn.

title: The Mirror Explodes
summary: The fifth album for the Los Angeles-based rock band was produced by Rod Cervera.

title: X Marks Destination
summary: This is the debut album for the Manchester quartet.

title: The Spine
summary: Now together over 20 years as a band, the duo of Johns (Linnel and Flansburgh) return with their 10th studio album (their first for adults in three years), reuniting with producer Pat Dillett (who worked on the pair's 1990 album 'Flood').

title: Origins
summary: The fourth full-length studio release for the Las Vegas rock band features production from Alex Da Kid, John Hill, Joel Little, Mattman & Robin, Jorgen Odegard, and Ido Zmishlany.

title: Laugh Now, Cry Later
summary: The rapper-turned-actor-turned-rapper's first album in six years features contributions from Scott Storch, Swizz Beatz and Snoop Dogg.

title: Fool Metal Jack
summary: The second release since the Brazilian psychedelic band reunited under original guitarist Sergio Dias in 2006, features a different lineup (Ani Cordero and Amy Crawford replaced Dinho Leme and Henrique Peters) than the one seen on 2009's Haih Or Amortecedor.

title: Exile
summary: This is the second full-length release for the British electro-pop duo of Theo Hutchcraft and Adam Anderson.

title: Evolution Theory
summary: This is the debut full-length release for the London-based dubstep quartet.

title: Keep Calm And Carry On
summary: The latest album for the Welsh rock band was produced with Jim Abbiss.

title: Earth Grid
summary: The second solo album for Asa Osborne, the Lungfish guitarist, was recorded in his house on cassette tape.

title: Riot City Blues
summary: Alison Mosshart (The Kills), Warren Ellis (Nick Cave & the Bad Seeds), and Will Sergeant (Echo and the Bunnymen) guest on the band's first album in four years, which ditches the aggressive, electronic elements of their previous two outings in favor of a more traditional blues-rock homage.

title: Ten Thousand Fists
summary: This is the third album for the alt-metal band fronted by David Draiman.

title: Relapse
summary: The Detroit rapper returns with his first album in five years, which features guest appearances by 50 Cent and producer Dr. Dre.

title: Happy In Galoshes
summary: The second solo effort for the Stone Temple Pilots singer was produced with Doug Green and Steve Albini.

title: This Modern Glitch
summary: This is the Liverpool trio's second album of eccentric indie rock.

title: Ways To Forget
summary: The debut full-length album for the British synth-pop band led by producer Guy Connelly.

title: Trapped Animal
summary: This is the first full-length album in over 25 years for the all-girl punk rock band.

title: ...it falls apart
summary: The fourth album from the Bay Area indie rockers (led by singer-guitarist Carlos Forster) is their first in three years.

title: Writers Without Homes
summary: The London-based collective is joined this time out by the likes of Simon Raymonde (Cocteau Twins), John Grant (The Czars) and Paul Anderson (Tram).

title: Cry
summary: This is the first new album in three years for the country superstar.

title: The Seventh Seal
summary: The rap artist releases his first solo album in ten years.

title: Leave This Town
summary: The American Idol contestant returns with his band's follow-up to its Grammy-nominated self-titled debut.

title: Mr. Brown
summary: This is the debut LP for the Atlanta-based singer best known for his work with OutKast and as a member of the Organized Noize crew.

title: Yeah Ghost
summary: The fourth album for Henry Binns and Sam Hardaker features a new singer, Eska Mtungwazi (longtime contributor Sia has branched off to her own solo career).

title: TheFutureEmbrace
summary: The Smashing Pumpkins/Zwan leader's solo debut includes a cover of the Bee Gees' "To Love Somebody." Jimmy Chamberlin and Robert Smith guest.

title: Bread & Circuses
summary: The latest album for the indie rock band was produced by Youth.

title: Unbroken
summary: Some of the third studio album for the former star of Sonny With A Chance and the Camp Rock movies was recorded after she sought treatment for self-harm and bulimia.

title: La Liberacion
summary: The Brazilian band releases their third album of party pop and electronic rock.

title: Midnight Memories
summary: The third full-length studio release for the British/Irish pop quintet is said to be more "rockier" and features songs written by the band as well as with such artists as Tom Fletcher, Danny Jones & Dougie Poynter of McFly, Jacknife Lee, Gary Lightbody of Snow Patrol, and Ryan Tedder of OneRepublic.

title: Equals
summary: The fourth full-length release for the British singer-songwriter was influenced in part by his marriage, the birth of his daughter and the death of a friend.

title: Night Train [EP]
summary: The British rock band releases its EP featuring K'Naan and Tigarah as guest artists, as well as one song with the band's Tim Rice-Oxley on lead vocals.

title: In This Light & On This Evening
summary: The third album for the British rock band was produced by Flood.

title: Echo
summary: The second album for the "X Factor" winner features production help from a variety of people including Justin Timberlake, Ryan Tedder, John Shanks, and Max Martin.

title: The Deadbeat Bang of Heartbreak City
summary: The fourth full-length release for the Philadelphia indie rock band led by James Alex features contributions from  former Replacements bassist Tommy Stinson.

title: I Love You
summary: The debut full-length album for Philadelphia-based rapper who is also involved with the groups Spank Rock and Sweatheart.

title: Title
summary: The debut full-length release (not to be confused with herr 2014 EP of the same name) for the pop singer-songwriter who gained fame with her single "All About That Bass," features guest appearances from John Legend and Shy Carter (on the deluxe edition).

title: Endlessly
summary: The funky and soul-filled Welsh singer's second album blends soft ballads with upbeat pop tracks, revealing a range of influences from the retro 1960's to modern day disco sounds.

title: BE
summary: The second release for the band led by Liam Gallagher was produced by Dave Sitek.

title: Unfamiliar Faces
summary: The California-born singer's follow-up to his 2006 record was produced by No Doubt guitarist Tom Dumont.

title: Remind Me Where The Light Is
summary: The second album for the Los Angeles indie-rock duo was produced with Michael Patterson and Nic Jodoin.

title: Love The Future
summary: The duo of D.A. Wallach and Max Drummey release their debut album on Pharrell Williams' label after a bidding war by Kanye West's and Jermaine Dupri's own labels.

title: Fast Man Raider Man
summary: The typically prolific Black returns with a 27-song, two-disc set produced by Jon Tiven. Among the many musicians lending a hand are Spooner Oldham and Levon Helm (The Band).

title: Sweet Disarray
summary: The debut release for the Liverpool-based singer-songwriter was self-produced.

title: Island Universe
summary: The second full-length release for the Orange County psych-rock band was produced by Hanni El Khatib and Johnny Bell of Crystal Antlers.

title: Anna
summary: The third full-length release from the Manchester indie rock band adds dance elements to their sound.

title: Again and Again
summary: The indie pop band from San Francisco releases another album of catchy, lo-fi tunes.

title: In Our Space Hero Suits
summary: The debut album for the Swedish all-girl indie pop band.

title: Getting Away With Murder
summary: The Northern California alt-metal band returns with a third album.

title: Flamingo
summary: Known as the frontman for Las Vegas-based rock group, The Killers, Brandon Flowers ventures out on his own with a solo debut that sounds achingly similar to the melodic, Vegas-themed music of his band but with a more self-conscious approach.

title: I Created Disco
summary: The debut album for the Scottish-born musician, who most recently worked on Kylie Minogue's comeback album.

title: Sequel to the Prequel
summary: Produced by Stephen Street, the third full-length studio release from the indie rock band led by Pete Doherty is its first release since 2007's Shotter's Nation.

title: Form & Control
summary: This is the second studio full-length album for the New York collective.

title: Soul
summary: Seal sings some classic soul songs on his sixth album produced by David Foster.

title: Mondo
summary: The debut full-length album for the Los Angeles-based indie duo of Asa Taccone (co-writer/producer of "Dick in a Box") and Matthew Compton was produced by Danger Mouse.

(Actually, he was feeling like that even before that happened.) Snoop Dogg and Sheryl Crow guest on a track apiece on this, his fifth album of new material.

summary: Emeli Sandé and Tinie Tempah appear as guests on the debut release from producer Timothy McKenzie.

summary: The Scottish rock band's second album was produced by Gil Norton.

summary: This is the debut album from the British post-punk quartet.

title: Animal

The vocals on one track were literally phoned in from prison, while production is handled by Kanye West, Swizz Beatz, Just Blaze and more.

title: Down To Earth
